title: super bowl dip
directions: Fry sausage and onions in skillet until meat is thoroughly cooked; drain.
Add chilies and tomatoes and cook uncovered for 15 minutes.
Add sour cream and cream cheese.
Simmer for 30 minutes, stirring often.
Keep warm when serving with chips.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Parboil potatoes 15 minutes.
Peel and cut in half lengthwise. Place in buttered baking dish.
Combine sugar, salt, butter and water.
Boil 3 minutes.
Pour syrup over potatoes. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Baste occasionally.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown and crumble bacon.
Dice and saut onion.
Brown ground beef.
Combine sugar, vinegar, ketchup, and salt in bottom of a crock pot.
Add ground beef, bacon, and beans.
Mix and cook on slow until hot.

title: pizza cups
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Stir in tomato paste, onion and seasonings (mixture will be thick).
Cook for 5 minutes and stir frequently.
Place biscuits in cupcake pans, pressing to cover the bottom and sides of the pan.
Spoon about 1/4 cup of sauce into the centers of the biscuits and put cheese on tops.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 cups (pizza).

title: perfect pumpkin pie
directions: Mix
brown
sugar, flour, pumpkin pie spice and salt in large bowl.
Stir
in pumpkin, evaporated milk and egg.
Pour into unbaked
pie
shell.
Bake at 350° about 30 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Thaw bread a little and roll out.
Salt and pepper and oil dough until soft.
Roll out the dough.
Place pepperoni on top. Put on cheese and sprinkle with some garlic salt and Parmesan cheese.
Spread thin layer of spaghetti sauce over top.
Roll like a jelly roll and seal edge by pinching.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Using a 3-quart casserole dish, layer first 6 ingredients in order listed. Top with cheese and bacon. Refrigerate at least 3 hours or overnight.

title: wine vinegar salad dressing
directions: Combine wine vinegar and olive oil (with other brands you may have to adjust the proportions according to taste).
Add minced garlic, chopped chives and pepper.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: meat loaf with vegetable stuffing
directions: Drain mushrooms, carrots and green beans.
Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium bowl, combine mushrooms, carrots, green beans, bread crumbs and 1 egg.
Set aside.
In large bowl, combine meat, onion, oats, 1 egg, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Spread half of mixture in bottom of ungreased loaf pan. Cover with vegetable mixture, spreading evenly.
Spread remaining meat mixture over vegetables.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: indian chicken curry
directions: Lightly brown onion and celery in hot oil.
Add flour and blend.
Add chicken stock and cook
until thick, stirring constantly.
Add tomato juice, Worcestershire sauce, seasonings and chicken; heat thoroughly.
Serve over hot rice.

title: carrot-ginger soup
directions: Cut carrots into 2-inch lengths.
Finely chop in food processor or by hand.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add onion, garlic and ginger; saute 3 minutes.
Stir in carrots, potato, broth, salt and pepper.
Simmer until vegetables are tender, 10 minutes. Puree in food processor.
Return puree to saucepan.
Add milk. Heat over low heat.
Garnish with chives, if you wish.

title: five spice powder
directions: Use equal amounts or as to taste.

title: sausage bread
directions: Roll out dough, then put a layer of sausage, a layer of cheese (use half), a layer of salami, layer of onions, layer of cheese (other half) and a layer of pepperoni.
Roll from the bottom, tucking in ends.
Be sure to seal with a bit of water.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: mushroom logs(makes 4 dozen)
directions: Separate crescent dough into 8 rectangles.
Press perforations to seal.

title: hello dolly's
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Sprinkle in crumbs; press down.
Pour milk over and layer rest of ingredients in order given.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, until lightly browned.
Cool thoroughly; cut into bars or squares.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Heat water, sugar and cornstarch until clear like glaze. Remove from stove and pour in strawberry Jell-O; mix well.
Add strawberries.
Pour in crust.
When cooled, refrigerate until firm.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and place in greased casserole.

title: orange pineapple salad
directions: Put jello and pineapple in pan and bring to a boil so jello is melted.
Stir so it doesn't stick.
Remove from the heat and let cool until it starts to set, then add container of Cool Whip.
Add cut-up banana.
(May also add nuts and cherries, if desired.) Pour into serving bowl and let set overnight.

title: layered coconut pecan dessert
directions: Layer 1:
Mix together the oleo, flour and nuts.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: nachos
directions: You will also need 1 long pan and grater for cheese

title: everest's cherry-strawberry cake
directions: Cream together the oil and margarine.
Add cake mix, lemon juice, baking powder, eggs and grapefruit juice, then mix for 3 minutes on low speed.
Pour half of the mixture into a well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread half of the pie filling over that and then the rest of the mixture on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 33 to 36 minutes. Cool and spread remaining pie filling over top.

title: elsa's spinach rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients (except tortillas and egg white). Refrigerate overnight.
Divide mixture and spread on tortillas. Roll tortillas and seal with egg white.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Remove and slice.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and flavorings thoroughly.
Gradually add sugar, taking time to thoroughly cream sugar into butter mixture.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with sour cream and milk. At this point, beat only enough to get ingredients well blended. Grease and flour bottom of a 10-inch cake pan.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in halves crosswise.
Remove yolks; mash and add cheese and seasonings.
Add enough butter to make mixture of right consistency to shape.
Make in balls the size of original yolks and refill whites.
Serve cold.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Melt the butter and add the lemon juice to the butter.
Remove from heat.
Butter may also be melted in microwave.
In a 9 x 12-inch baking dish, sprinkle a handful of bread crumbs.
Put chopped garlic or garlic powder on top of bread crumbs.
Layer shrimp on top of mixture.
Pour butter mixture over shrimp.
Pour bread crumbs to cover.
Bake covered at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes. Uncover for the last few minutes.

title: rum sauced peaches and raspberries
directions: Toss peaches with lemon juice and set aside.
In a large skillet, over direct, medium-high heat, melt together butter and sugar.
Add rim and stir until bubbling.
Add the peaches and cook, stirring for about 2 minutes or just until they are slightly softened; gently stir in raspberries.
Serve immediately over vanilla frozen yogurt or ice cream.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: carrot muffins
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Mix well.
Mix in a small bowl next 6 ingredients.
Stir with wire whip.
Add to dry ingredients. Mix slightly.
Add raisins.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 minutes. Makes 12 muffins.
Contains 120 calories and 3 fat grams.

title: praline cookies(club member: mindy daniels)
directions: Bring sugar, milk and butter to a rolling boil or boil for 3 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Add marshmallows and a dash of salt. Let marshmallows dissolve by stirring. Add vanilla, crumbs and pecans; mix well. Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet. Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate lover's fudge cake
directions: Blend cake mix, pudding mix, oil, water and eggs on medium speed 2 minutes.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes at 350° in tube pan.
Cool.

title: easy scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix ingredients and put in roaster or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 2 hours at 300°.

title: watergate beans
directions: Saute ground round and onion in a large skillet.
Drain.
Add to pinto beans, tomatoes, enchilada sauce and seasonings.
Cook on low heat for 1 hour.
Serve with corn bread. This works great in crock-pot.

title: apple butter
directions: Cook over low heat for 1 1/2 hours.
Pour into canning jars and seal.

title: congealed salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and chill.

title: old-fashioned pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar together.
Add 4 well beaten eggs to mixture.
Add flour and mix well.
Add remaining 2 eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Bake in a well-greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: old south dressing
directions: Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until well blended.
Add eggs, mix until blended.
Remove 1 cup of batter and set aside. Stir in pumpkin and spices.
Pour remaining batter into crust, top with pumpkin batter.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Refrigerate three hours or overnight.

title: "it won't last" cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 or 10-inch Bundt pan. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: brown cow shakes
directions: Smash bananas in a large bowl.
Stir in syrup, milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Place equal amounts in 2 big glasses.
Top each shake with 1 scoop of ice cream.
Makes 2.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, sugar and cinnamon together. Cut in margarine until it resembles cornmeal.
Combine molasses, hot water and baking soda. Add molasses mixture to moisten, working rapidly.
Pour into unbaked pastry crust immediately. Bake 40 to 45 minutes until filling is set.

title: whole wheat biscuits
directions: In medium bowl, mix all flour, sugar, baking powder and baking soda.
With pastry blender or 2 knives used scissor-fashion, cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.

title: baked rice and meat
directions: Cook cubed meat, gravy or stock, tomatoes, half the onions, Worcestershire sauce and other seasonings together for about 10 minutes.
Melt fat in separate pan.
Add rest of onions and uncooked rice.
Allow both to brown slightly, then add to meat mixture.
Turn all ingredients into buttered casserole and bake at 350° until rice is soft and has absorbed most of liquid, about 40 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Stir meat.
Cook meat and onions.
Add flour, chili powder and chili seasonings.
Add water if needed.
Add tomato paste and red pepper.
Season to taste.
Cook about 15 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix and put into loaf pan.

title: crunchy chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine everything, except cheese and chips, in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese, then top with potato chips.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Place berries and vinegar in covered kettle.
Boil hard for one minute.
Add sugar and boil hard for about 20 minutes.
(Check for sheeting after 15 minutes.)
Put in large bowl and let sit at least 12 hours, stirring occasionally for the first few hours.

title: baked squash
directions: Bake whole acorn squash at 400° for about 1 hour.
Cut squash in half and scrape out seeds.
Scoop out squash pulp and mix it with remaining ingredients.
Return mixture to shells and heat thoroughly before serving.

title: beef and onion stew
directions: Dredge meat in flour. Brown in butter in Dutch oven. Add the onion and garlic.
Cook, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes. Add broth, vinegar, tomato paste and seasonings.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Stir occasionally.
Serve over rice or noodles. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Boil chicken and debone. Saute celery and onion in margarine. Mix dry cornbread mix with chicken broth, mayonnaise, eggs and black pepper. Add onions, celery, soups and chicken. Pour into large Pyrex dish.

title: chocolate vinegar cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients in ungreased cake pan.
Make 3 holes in dry ingredients.
In 1st hole put oil.
In 2nd hole put vinegar and 3rd hole, vanilla.
Pour 1 cup cold water over ingredients and mix well.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Let cake cool and ice in pan.

title: ham rolls
directions: Split rolls in half.
Mix butter, mustard, onion powder, Worcestershire sauce and poppy seed together.
Spread each roll with mustard sauce, piece of ham and cheese.
Spread mustard sauce on opposite side of roll also.
Heat oven to 325°.
Heat rolls until cheese has melted.

title: waldensian onion soup
directions: Brown (saute) onions in olive oil until golden brown in large pot.
Add sauces, water, and bouillon to onions.
Simmer in covered pot for one hour.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Cream together 2
sticks butter, add 3 cups sugar.
Add 6 eggs, one at
a
time.
Sift
cups
plain
flour with 1/4 teaspoon soda.
Add
to
egg mixture.
Add 1/2 pint sour cream and 1 teaspoon lemon
extract.	Bake in tube pan 1 hour and 45 minutes at 325°.

title: favorite pecans
directions: Beat egg white and sugar until foamy.
Add sugar, cinnamon and salt. Mix in pecans.
Bake at 225° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: homemade mayonnaise
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together first. Have mixer bowl ice cold. Put yolks in and start beating. Add the first 6 ingredients while continuing to beat. Add the oil a little at a time so the mixture does not separate. After the mayonnaise is hard and formed, add the water and vinegar a little at a time until the mayonnaise is at spreadable stage. Refrigerate.

title: asparagus mold
directions: Drain asparagus, reserving liquid.
Puree asparagus and set aside.
Soften gelatin in the liquid over low heat, stirring occasionally, until dissolved.
In a mixing bowl, beat cottage cheese until fairly smooth; add buttermilk and dissolved gelatin. Add asparagus; mix in celery, onion and salt.
Turn mixture into mold until set.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix the butter and peanut butter.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix all together.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place the peaches in a 9-inch pie pan or shallow casserole dish and sprinkle with the lemon juice.
In a bowl, blend the dry ingredients.
Cut in the margarine with two knives or a pastry blender to make a coarse, crumbly texture. Spread over the peaches.
Bake about 30 minutes.
If desired, top each serving with a tablespoon of yogurt and a dash of cinnamon. Yield:
6 servings.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken until tender; set aside.
Peel and dice potatoes. Combine with other vegetable, bring to boil and simmer until tender.
Cut chicken into pieces and place in large casserole dish.
Drain potatoes and vegetables; add to chicken in dish. Season to taste.
Mix gravy mix and pour over other ingredients. Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix enough Bisquick to cover top of casserole dish.
Bake until crust is browned and done.

title: breakfast ham casserole
directions: Layer potatoes, onion, Cheddar cheese, ham and Mozzarella cheese in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Beat eggs in bowl. Add milk and salt; mix well. Pour over layers. Cover and chill 3 hours or overnight. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Let stand for 10 minutes before cutting into squares to serve. Serves 9 to 12.

title: carrot-pineapple bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients and add oil, carrots, drained pineapple, vanilla and eggs. Pour or spoon into 2 greased and floured regular size loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until toothpick poked into bread can be removed clean.
Cool on cooling rack.
(Excellent for freezing.)

title: fiesta bundt cake
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees. Grease and flour tube pan. Mix margarine, nuts and coconut. Spread in bottom of pan. Drain pineapple. Save syrup and 1 Tbsp. pineapple for glaze. Blend cake mix, water, eggs and oil. Pour 1/2 batter over nut mixture. Put drained pineapple over batter. Put the rest of the batter on top. Bake 45-50 minutes. Remove from pan and glaze with 1 cup confectioners sugar and enough juice to mix.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Skin chicken and boil in salted water for 15 minutes. Debone and cube chicken; set aside. Save chicken broth. Saute onions, bell pepper, garlic, celery and green onions in medium sized skillet over medium heat for 10 minutes. Add cream of mushroom soup. Add 1 cup of chicken broth; cook for 30 minutes over medium heat. Add chicken and simmer for 5 minutes. Stir in crumbled cornbread. Add more broth, if needed, to make mixture moist. Season to taste. Put mixture in large baking pan and bake at 450° for 20 to 30 minutes, or until slightly brown on top. Serve hot, while moist.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan or 10-inch tube pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes, or until tester comes out clean.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when done.

title: baked ziti
directions: Cook ziti according to package directions.
Drain.
Combine ziti, spaghetti sauce and Ricotta cheese.
Put in greased baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix well.
Dissolve 1 to 2 teaspoons in a cup of boiling water.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: In heavy 3-quart saucepan with wire whisk combine sugar, flour, milk and eggs until well blended.
Cook over medium-low heat, stirring frequently, until mixture thickens and coats spoon, about 30 to 45 minutes.
Do not boil.
Cover surface with plastic wrap. Cool completely, about 2 hours.
Pour cooled egg mixture and vanilla into a 5 or 6-quart ice cream freezer can.
Fill ice cream bucket 1/2 full of ice, 2 cups water and 1/4 cup rock salt.
Repeat layers, turn freezer on.
When can stops turning (about 30 minutes) ice cream is ready.
Enjoy!

title: chicken log
directions: Combine cream cheese, steak sauce and curry powder; beat with mixer until smooth.
Stir in chicken, celery and parsley.
Shape into 9-inch log.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Chill 4 to 5 hours.
Roll in toasted nuts.
Serve with choice of crackers.

title: muffeletta mix
directions: With steel blade, chop olives and capers separately in food processor, putting in large bowl as finished.
Next, chop celery and add to olive mixture.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate in glass jars.

title: reindeer snack
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Mix popcorn, snacks, cereal and pretzels in a large bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients; drizzle over popcorn mixture while tossing until evenly coated.
Spread in ungreased jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch).
Bake, uncovered, 15 minutes, stirring twice.
Cool. Store, loosely covered, at room temperature up to 2 weeks.
Makes about 9 cups of snack.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together. You may have to use your hands as the batter will be stiff. Pour into a tube pan and bake 1 hour and 45 minutes at 300°.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Cook chicken breasts, debone and cube meat.
Cook egg noodles in chicken broth. Drain noodles.
Mix soups, Ro-Tel tomatoes, chicken and egg noodles. Shred cheese and mix with chicken mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: brown sugar drop cookies
directions: Drop from spoon on baking sheet. Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: quick and easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Mix well by hand or spoon.
Form in small balls or drop from teaspoon on cookie sheet. (May or may not need light grease.)
Press each cookie with a fork, two ways, forming traditional crisscross (dip fork into water to avoid sticking).
Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove immediately to cool.

title: kim's baked beans
directions: Mix all together in a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 40 minutes, stirring once.
Yields 8 servings.

title: cole slaw
directions: Grate onion fine.
Grate carrot fine.
Cut cabbage in quarters and remove core.
Grate cabbage fine.
Dice pepper and celery; add to previous ingredients.
Mix well and season with salt and pepper to taste.
Add Miracle Whip to desired taste, but not too wet. Let marinate overnight for best flavor.
Serves 6.

title: norwegian stuffed onion
directions: Peel the onions and cut a 1/2-inch slice from the top of each. Put these aside to use for a topping.
Hollow out the center of the onion to form holes for the stuffing.
Save the center of the onion and chop them fine.
Melt the butter and brown the ground meat, salt and pepper.
Mix them well.
When the meat is brown, stuff the center of the onion with the meat mixture.
Place the top slices of the onions
back on and place toothpicks to hold them together.
Put the onions in a baking dish and pour the beef stock over them.
Bake at 345°
for 1 hour or until the onions are soft.

title: fudge treasure cupcakes
directions: In small bowl, make filling by combining cream cheese, 1/3 cup sugar, egg and chocolate chips.

title: spaghetti aglia d'olio
directions: Crush garlic and saute for 10 minutes in oil.
Strain garlic remnants from the oil after 10 minutes and add some (your call) oregano, basil and parsley to oil.
Add flavored oil to the well-drained spaghetti and toss well.
Top with grated Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add ham; divide crescent rolls into 4 rectangles and spread in a 12-inch pan.
Spread ham-onion mixture over dough.
Bake eggs at medium speed and add remaining ingredients.
Pour over ham mixture.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes until brown.

title: frozen chocolate torte
directions: Whip butter until creamy.
Add sugar.
Whip some more.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add chocolate; mix well and add vanilla.
Beat until very creamy.
Add nutmeats.
Spread over a graham cracker crust using a 8 x 10-inch pan.
Top with remaining nutmeats. Freeze.
Cut into pieces before it gets too frozen.

title: chicken and water chestnut souffle
directions: Arrange bread slices in buttered 8 x 8-inch baking dish. Layer chicken, mushrooms, water chestnuts and cheese in prepared dish.
Combine mayonnaise, margarine, eggs, milk and salt in bowl; mix well.
Pour over layers.
Spoon mixture of soup and pimento over all.
Chill, covered with foil, for 8 hours to overnight. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with bread crumbs mixed with butter.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes longer or until set. Yield:
4 servings.

title: sweet and sour green beans(club member: terah smith)
directions: Combine sugar and vinegar in saucepan or skillet. Add drained green beans. Cover and simmer 30 minutes (turn beans occasionally). Add bacon drippings. Remove from liquid and place in serving dish. Sprinkle crumbled bacon over top.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together, then add oil and eggs.
Mix well, then add nuts and chopped apples.
Pour into greased 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Dice apples. Mix with sugar. Beat in eggs. Add oil and vanilla. Mix together flour, cinnamon and baking soda. Add chopped walnuts. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: salmon balls
directions: Drain and reserve liquid from salmon.
To this liquid, add egg and enough water to total one cup liquid.
Flake salmon in bowl. Add to salmon the cup of liquid, flour and onion.
Mix well. Drop by teaspoonfuls into deep hot oil.
Cook until balls are brown and float to top.
Makes 25 to 30.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add rice.
Stir until brown. Take off. Add soup and consomme.
No salt. Stir. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Top with mushrooms.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease 3 loaf pans.
Sift flour.
Beat eggs.
Add rest of ingredients to flour.
Mix well.
Add zucchini and nuts.
Mix. Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove from pans.
Let cool

title: oriental dipping sauce
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Makes 1/4 cup.

title: potato cheese bake
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 20 minutes.

title: nora's baked beans
directions: *I use 2 or 3 different kinds, such as pork and beans, kidney beans, limas, etc.

title: apricot ham
directions: Place ham in baking dish.
Insert cloves.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Arrange apricots on ham.
Pour on juice.
Dot evenly with oleo.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli and cheese cornbread
directions: Mix and bake in iron skillet until done.

title: fudgy chocolate melt
directions: Combine all ingredients except ice cream and chocolate syrup in a medium bowl, stirring until blended. Pour into a greased 8-inch baking dish. (Mixture will be shallow in dish.) Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all together and roll balls about size of quarter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cook at 375° until light brown.
Cool and store in storage bags.
Keep sealed to keep crisp.

title: lasagna(easy-quick)
directions: Brown hamburger and drain grease.
Add tomato sauce, bell pepper, garlic and mushrooms.
Simmer, covered, 10 minutes.
Cook noodles.

title: apricot-sour cream
directions: Bring 1 cup nectar to boil.
Sprinkle on 1 package jello; stir until dissolved.
Stir in 1 cup cold nectar.
Pour into lightly oiled mold; chill until set.
Bring remaining cup of nectar to boil.
Sprinkle on remaining package of jello; stir until dissolved.
Stir in evaporated milk.
Spread sour cream on set layer in mold.
Pour jello and evaporated milk on top.
Chill until set.

title: fruit surprise(diabetic)
directions: Use non-nutritive sweetener equal to 1/4 cup sugar.
Wash and clean fruit.
Add sweetener.
Chill thoroughly.
This goes well on non-sweet shortcake.
Three-quarters of a cup equals 1/2 fruit exchange per serving.

title: scotchy treats
directions: Melt butterscotch chips in double boiler with peanut butter. When melted add Frosted Flakes.
Drop by spoonful on wax paper.

title: italian cheese ball
directions: Mix cheese, ham and salad dressing.
Shape into a ball. Roll in chopped pecans.

title: english walnut cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Blend in flour, soda, and salt.
Add walnuts and cherries.
Form into a roll 2
1/2 inches wide.
Wrap in wax paper;
chill several hours.
Cut into thin slices, about 1/8 inch thick.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in a 400 degree oven for 8-10 minutes until browned.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine ingredients. Mix well. Pour into greased loaf pan. May use 1 large loaf or 2 small loaf pans. Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: banana peanut butter pinwheels
directions: Spread peanut butter evenly over bread.
Place banana on one side of bread, roll up and slice jelly roll fashion.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water.
When soft, rub through strainer, or use 2 cups mashed potatoes.
Scald milk with onion; remove onion.
Add milk slowly to potatoes, mixing with a whisk or beater.
Melt half the butter.
Add dry ingredients; stir until well mixed, then stir into hot soup.
Boil 1 minute.
Add remaining butter; sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: marinated pork tenderloin
directions: Combine all ingredients in a shallow container.
Add meat; turn to coat.
Cover and seal.
Place in refrigerator for several hours.
Turn meat periodically.
Grill pork tenderloin for approximately 15 minutes each side with grill covered.
Baste during grilling.

title: pakistani chicken
directions: Remove skin and cut chicken into small pieces.
Fry onion in oil in a pot.
When it is nearly half brown, put pieces of chicken in the pot.
Add chili powder, salt, cumin seed, ginger and garlic in it.
Let it cook about 15 minutes on high heat.
When the chicken water is almost dry, then add crushed green pepper and tomatoes.
Cook for a little while on medium heat until tomato juice is dry and the chicken is tender.

title: chicken continental
directions: Saute chicken and mushrooms in oil for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, except rice, and bring to a full boil. Stir in rice, remove from heat; cover and let stand 5 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: brett's biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add milk and shortening; cut biscuits and arrange in pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°.
Makes 12 large biscuits.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook green beans until tender.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter; add flour, salt, sugar, onion, sour cream and Swiss cheese until it forms a sauce.
Place green beans in bottom of casserole dish. Pour sauce over top.
Cover with Pepperidge Farm crumbs.
Pour 3/4 cup melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese popcorn
directions: Mix the cheese with melted butter or margarine.
Pour the mixture over the pop corn and toss.

title: jello salad
directions: Place jello and crushed pineapple in saucepan on medium heat until dissolved.
Cool completely.
Add the buttermilk, stirring until mixed.
Fold in the Cool Whip and pour into flat type casserole or mold.
Cool in refrigerator 4 hours or overnight. Nuts can be added if desired.
Serve with lettuce leaf as salad. Serves 8.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cut chicken into small pieces.
Add almonds, celery and relish.
Mix in desired amount of salad dressing.

title: iced cucumber and mint soup
directions: Put yogurt in a bowl; add tomato juice, chicken stock and heavy cream.
Mix together.
Add garlic, salt and mint.
Mix again.
Add grated egg, shrimp and cucumbers.
Chill before serving for 1 to 2 hours.
Garnish with hard-boiled eggs (chopped) and chopped fresh mint.

title: brownies(yields 16 squares)
directions: Melt chocolate and shortening together in a saucepan.
Remove from stove; stir in the sugar, one egg yolk at a time, vanilla and the flour.
Add chopped nuts.
Spread the mixture in a shallow pan.
Bake in a slow oven at 325° for 45 minutes.
Cut into squares while still warm.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Layer cooked chicken in 13 x 9-inch dish.
Mix together soup and water.
Pour over chicken.
Pour peas and carrots over chicken.
Mix together flour, milk and butter;
pour over vegetables.
Pour chicken broth over top.
Do not stir.
Cook at 350°
until top is brown.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Combine in order given.
Beat until smooth.
Grease and flour cake pan(s).
Bake at 375° until done.

title: tex-mex casserole
directions: In medium saucepan, combine beans, mushroom soup and Ro-Tel. Heat until blended.

title: cheddar cheese soup
directions: Put vegetables and water in saucepan and cook until fork-tender.
Do not drain.
Set aside.
In another saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Slowly stir in milk. Continue stirring and cooking over medium heat until mixture starts to thicken.
Then stir in cheese and continue stirring and cooking until cheese is melted.
Pour cheese sauce over undrained vegetables.
Add ham and heat until ham is hot.
Makes six 1 cup servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Fix broccoli
as on package.
Heat soup with one can of water and bring to a boil.
Take off heat and add Minute rice. Let
set 10
minutes.
Mix all ingredients together and pinch bread on top. Bake for 30 minutes.

title: king ranch chickengroves, texas
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Saute onions and bell peppers.

title: spaghetti-meatballs
directions: Mix meat and ingredients.
Add a little more bread crumbs if sticky.
Roll into small, medium or large balls, depending how many you are serving.
Set aside until ready to drop into boiling tomato sauce.
Cover and simmer
3 hours.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Heat 1 cup of the pear juice to boiling; remove from heat and add gelatin.
Add cottage cheese and whip with electric mixer. Mash pears with a fork and add to whipped mixture.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour in an 8-inch square dish.
Chill until firm.
If desired, garnish with blueberries, which I do and makes it better.

title: tart and tangy tuna salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Enjoy this unique-tasting tuna salad in a sandwich or as a light meal on lettuce with soup.
Or, serve it on your favorite crackers as an appetizer or snack.
Serves 4.

title: polk salad with scrambled eggs
directions: Bass, both small mouth and large mouth, crappie and bream are all close in taste and texture, so recipes of these fish are usually interchangeable.
Trout is in a class by itself.
Salmon is a searun fish, usually caught by sportsmen in fresh water, so its meat is different than any listed here.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Take nice pork chops, remove all fat, wash and pound them; then season with salt and pepper.
Roll in beaten eggs and cracker crumbs and fry to a light brown.
Fry in a little grease.

title: sourdough hot rolls
directions: Mix dry ingredients, mixing well.
Stir in Sourdough Starter and oil.
Turn dough out on a floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic (about 8 to 10 minutes).
Shape dough into 2-inch balls.
Cover and let rise in a warm place (85°) free from drafts for about 30 minutes.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 17 minutes. It yields 15 rolls.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Mix first
3 ingredients to make the pie crust.
Pat in 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: rosy meat balls
directions: Shape into balls, brown on sides.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, pour in rice; pour water over rice.
Combine mushroom and celery soups and spoon 1/3 of soup mixture over rice.
Sprinkle dry soup mix over chicken and rice. Bake at 350° until casserole is hot and bubbly and chicken is done.

title: pastry for chicken
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Roll on floured surface; cut into thin strips.
Place strips into pot of boiling chicken (cooked and deboned) and broth from chicken.
Add additional seasoning and Country Crock to taste.

title: birthday cones
directions: Pour milk in a bowl and add instant pudding mix.
Beat with a wire whisk.
Wait 5 minutes; spoon pudding into cones.
Freeze 3 hours.
Top with prepared whipped cream and candy sprinkles.

title: wild rice and shrimp
directions: Saute onion and pepper in small amount of margarine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish, well-greased, and bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
It's wonderful!

title: greek spaghetti
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain and set aside.
Heat oil in a large skillet.
Add onion and garlic; saute 1 to 2 minutes.

title: aunt billye's peach cake
directions: Add dry ingredients into egg, vanilla and milk plus Crisco oil.
Mix well.
Spread on greased baking sheet with sides.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Spread chicken breast flat; fold cheese and ham slices to fit on top; fold breast over filling and fasten edges with toothpicks. On wax paper, mix flour and paprika.
Use mixture to coat chicken pieces.
In 12-inch skillet over medium heat in hot butter, cook chicken until brown on all sides.
Add wine and bouillon.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 30 minutes or until fork-tender; remove toothpicks.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Cream together the butter, flour and sugar.
Add egg yolks; mix well.
Add lemon rind and juice.
Stir in milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake for about 25 minutes at 375°.
Pie should be lightly browned and set.
When pie is cut, you have a creamy filling on the bottom and it is cakelike on top.

title: 1-2-3 pastry
directions: Heat oven to 450° for 1 crust (measurements in parentheses are for 2 crust pie).
Mix flour and salt.
Blend oil with fork.
Mix water in well.
Roll between 2 pieces of waxed paper.

title: yogurt marinated steaks
directions: Combine yogurt, oil, garlic, curry, Tabasco sauce and salt. Place steak in plastic bag. Add marinade.
Spread evenly over steak. Tie bag and marinate in the refrigerator for 6 to 8 hours (or overnight).
Remove steak from bag and grill.

title: coney island burgers
directions: Dig out a 12 x 12 foot pit and fill it with logs, which are burned and reduced to a hot ash.
Stretch woven fence wire over the pit.
Lay whole dressed gar on top.
Douse gar occasionally with barbecue sauce, applied with mops.

title: marinated olives
directions: Combine olive oil, vinegar, bay leaf and garlic in a small bowl.
Mix well.
Pour over olives.
Add lemon and mix.
Cover and refrigerate at least one day (2 or 3 are better).

title: crawfish in puff pastry
directions: Melt butter and saute vegetables until tender.
Wash crayfish and keep stock.
Season crayfish with red, white and black peppers. Add flour and cook five minutes.
Add stock and cool twenty minutes.
Add crawfish and cook 10 minutes.
Season and add parsley and green onions.
Cool before filling puff pastry.

title: swedish spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown together first 4 ingredients.
Then add stewed tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Cook and drain spaghetti.
Mix together and bake 45 minutes, covered.
Uncover last 10 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt butter; beat eggs well.
Add corn kit and melted butter and mix well.
Stir in cottage cheese, broccoli and onion.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sweet potato breakfast biscuits
directions: Mix well.
Roll out dough and cut with a cutter. Bake at 350° until brown. May glaze with powdered sugar and milk.

title: apple dumplings #2
directions: Peel, quarter and core apples to make 10 pieces.
Do not use any other brand of biscuits, or dumplings will be tough.
Stretch a biscuit out; put an apple piece in the center.
Pinch the biscuit together around the apple; place in a casserole dish. Continue until all 10 are finished.
Sprinkle with cinnamon to taste.
Heat the water, sugar and margarine to a boil; pour over dumplings.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Cut cheeses up into pieces.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Cook until cheese melts.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Cook hamburger meat.
When done, put spaghetti sauce in it. Then cook noodles.

Put a thin layer of sauce on bottom, then put 3 noodles, side by side, then put another layer of meat with a layer of cheese, then put the noodles on top of that and repeat as many times as necessary.
Then put in oven at 425° until cheese melts.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Wash and separate 12 large cabbage leaves from the head.

Drop in 2-quarts boiling water. Cook, uncovered, 3 minutes or until limp; drain well. Combine beef and remaining ingredients. Place about 1/2 cup meat mixture on each cabbage leaf. Roll leaf tightly and secure with toothpicks.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach; drain in sieve.
Press out as much moisture as possible.
Combine spinach and dressing.
Mix Parmesan cheese, eggs, margarine, salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly.
Roll into balls about 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze. After balls are completely frozen, remove and store in plastic bags in freezer.
To serve, place balls on cookie sheet; bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes (7 to 10 minutes for unfrozen) or until lightly browned.
Serve hot.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Cream together sugars, butter and eggs.
Add dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Roll into balls and coat with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and place 1 Hershey's Kiss in the center and return to oven for 2 to 5 minutes longer.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except only use 1/3 c. of tomato sauce.
Save the rest for later.
Pat meat mixture out on aluminum foil.
Roll into long rectangle approximately 3/4 inch deep then add mozzarella cheese on top.
Pat cheese down into meat to hold in place.
Raising the aluminum foil, start rolling meat, cheese mixture into a roll.
Pinch ends together sealing cheese inside and place in loaf pan.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.
Drain, then pour rest of tomato sauce over meat.
Cook 15 minutes.

title: cheese strata
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place bread cubes in the bottom. Spread grated cheese on top. Next, ham and/or mushrooms.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove cover from pan and bake 1 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Enjoy!

title: cream cheese pecan pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, egg, sugar, 1 teaspoon vanilla and salt until smooth and creamy. Spread in pie shell. Sprinkle with pecans on top. Mix pie filling, 3 eggs, sugar, Karo syrup and the last 1 teaspoon vanilla. Pour over cream cheese mixture. Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin nut muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and grease muffin pan well.
Sift together the first 6 ingredients.
Combine pumpkin, sugar, milk and eggs in mixing bowl.
Add dry ingredients and butter, mixing well.
Blend in nuts.
Fill each greased muffin pan cup 2/3 full and bake for 45 to 55 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Very moist.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed.
After mixing, place in serving dish and refrigerate.
Garnish with additional coconut or chopped pecans.

title: scalloped cheese potatoes
directions: In a well buttered 2-quart casserole pan, lay potatoes, onion and salt.
In a small saucepan, heat soup, milk and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over potatoes.
Cover and cook at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: calico salad
directions: Drain beans, peas and corn.
Add carrots, onion, pepper and pimento.
Set aside and make dressing.

title: hot ham and cheese rolls
directions: Combine ham and Cheddar cheese; then add remaining ingredients.
Spread on sliced hot dog or hamburger buns.
Wrap in foil and bake for 10 minutes at 400°.

title: norwegian pancake
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a casserole dish in 375° oven. Blend eggs 1 minute. Add milk and blend 1 minute. Add flour and blend 1 minute. Pour egg mixture into hot melted butter or margarine and bake until done. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.

title: chicken and mushrooms
directions: You will need small paper bag to mix ingredients.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Empty cans into bowl. Cut long noodles into short noodles. Add eggs. Grate cheese and add to mixture. Reserve some cheese for top of casserole.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes until brown on top.

title: jeff davis pies
directions: Mix all together and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 410°.
Reduce heat to 350° and cook 35 to 40 minutes.

title: no roll pie crust
directions: Mix oil and milk together.
Add other ingredients and mix until well blended.
Put into a pie plate and pat along edges and bottom of a 9-inch pan.

title: cottage cheese dip
directions: Blend ingredients together until smooth.
Serve with fresh vegetable sticks.

title: baked acorn squash
directions: Place squash rings in a single layer in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Add water; cover with foil.
Bake in a 350° oven for 60 minutes.
To serve, season with salt and pepper; dot with butter.
Makes 8 servings.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Blend oil and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add vanilla, flour, salt, baking soda, nutmeg and cinnamon after sifting. Add apples and nuts.
Bake in well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan at 325° for about 1 hour and 45 minutes.
(Check cake after 1 1/2 hours.)

title: kathy's no-fail fudge
directions: Heat condensed milk and chips until melted over medium-low heat.
Stir in salt and vanilla. Pour into 8-inch square buttered pan lined with wax paper.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Check pie filling can and follow directions with first five ingredients.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cake mix.
Do not mix.
Sprinkle on 1 cup chopped walnuts. Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: candy bar frosties
directions: In a blender combine Eagle Brand milk and other remaining ingredients. Blend until smooth. Serve immediately.

title: raisin bread
directions: To make starter dough, mix yeast, 1/4 cup milk, 1/4 cup flour, sugar and melted margarine.
Let stand 1/2 hour.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Bring following ingredients to a boil:	soup, vinegar, oil and sugar, add Tabasco (a few shakes).
Pour over drained carrots and cover.	Refrigerate overnight.	Keeps indefinitely.
Serves 8-10.

title: crab imperial ii
directions: In medium pan melt 1 Tbsp. butter. Mix flour slowly adding milk - stir constantly to keep mixture smooth.
Cook stirring over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil and thickens.
Mix onion, Worcestershire Sauce, and bread cubes.
Cool.
Fold mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
In another pan heat 2 Tbsp butter until lightly browned.
Add crab-meat and toss lightly.
Combine with sauce mixture.
Put mixture in greased casserole dish. Sprinkle paprika over top.
Bake 450° until hot and bubbly and lightly browned.
Makes 4 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla. Mix dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream.
Add bananas and pecans.
Mix well. Pour into a large loaf pan or 2 small loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
(Pans must be greased or sprayed with Pam.)

title: pam davis' savory crescent chicken squares
directions: Blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons margarine until smooth. Add salt, pepper, milk, onion, pimento and chicken.
Mix well.

title: ham ball
directions: Mix all ingredients; roll into ball and chill.

title: easy fruit salad dressing
directions: Add milk to vanilla pudding mix and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add pineapple juice.
Cool.
Add Cool Whip and whatever fruit you would like.
Dressing keeps well in refrigerator.

title: berry blender smoothie
directions: Blend until smooth. Store extra in air-tight container. Refrigerate.

title: half time rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water with 1 teaspoon of sugar; set aside. Heat milk.
Add cold water to cool.
Set aside.
Mix all ingredients together and let set for 10 to 15 minutes.
This is important.

title: lo-cal apple pie
directions: Thaw apple juice; mix 2 tablespoons juice with cornstarch in a small pan.
Heat remaining juice and blend in concentrate mix. Stir constantly until thick and smooth.
Stir in oleo and cinnamon.
Pour over sliced apples; toss gently to coat.
Pour into crust; cover with top crust.
Bake 50 minutes at 400°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease a 9-inch baking dish.
Mix sour cream and soup; pour into dish.
Take chicken off bone and cut up.
Put on top of soup and sour cream mixture.
Mix stuffing by directions on package; put on top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: glazed pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture alternating with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix until blended after each addition.
Stir in rum and coconut extracts.

title: lemon tea muffins
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt. Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Beat yolks until thick. Blend well with creamed mixture. Add flour mixture alternately with lemon juice. Beat egg whites until stiff. Fold whites and lemon rind into batter. Fill muffin pans 2/3 full. Combine 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle on top of muffins. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: tea cookies
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, salt and soda, dissolved in water.
Add butter and Crisco to flour and mix.
Add to other mixture.
Roll 1/4-inch thick and cut cookies.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix all fruit with Cool Whip.
Mix with Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice.
Pour into pie crust and cool about 3 or 4 hours.

title: champagne salad
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Mix in all other ingredients and put in 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.
Take out 1 hour before serving.

title: crawfish broccoli(microwave)
directions: Combine onion and bell pepper in butter and cook on High for 5 minutes.
Add broccoli and cook for 5 minutes.
Add all other ingredients and cook 10 minutes (including rice).
Stir once. (If reheat, this may help, as cheese would rise to top if reheated in stove oven.)

title: oven cubed beef
directions: Place cubed beef in deep pan.
Add seasonings to taste.
Place in 400° oven.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Leave about 1 hour or until brown.
Reduce heat to 250° and leave until meat is tender.
Meat juice may be thickened for gravy; stated oven time is for large amount, smaller amounts require less time.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together peanut butter, margarine, corn syrup, sugar, milk and vanilla. Make into small balls and roll in graham cracker crumbs. Chill in refrigerator.

title: vegetable quiche
directions: Bake crust 10 minutes at 350°.
Mix all ingredients together. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 10 minutes, then serve.

title: crock pot venison
directions: Cut venison into strips and put in crock pot with pepper and salt. Stir well to coat meat. Add remaining ingredients, cover and cook on low setting 8 hours or high setting for 4 hours. Serve over rice.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water together and cook until mixture threads. Add peanuts and stir continuously, cooking until syrup mixture turns light brown in color and peanuts are done. Remove from heat and add soda, salt and butter. Stir until thoroughly mixed and pour into a buttered cookie sheet. Spread as thinly as possible.

title: bob's favorite dessert
directions: Crush enough cookies finely to cover bottom of square or oblong pan.
Cover cookies with soft ice cream carefully.
Freeze. Mix evaporated milk, butter or margarine, unsweetened chocolate and sugar.
Cook and stir until thick.
Cool thoroughly.
Pour over top of refrozen ice cream.
Freeze again until firm.

title: chicken vegetable casserole
directions: Mix
the ingredients together (except crackers).
Crush crackers
and
mix	with
1 stick of melted margarine.
Spread half of cracker mixture in bottom of baking dish.
Add vegetables and chicken mix.

title: apricot "forever" salad
directions: Cook apricots in 1 1/2 cups water until very soft, using juice and adding water if necessary.
Stir apricots until almost a pulp.
Dissolve gelatin in hot water or juice.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until well mixed.
Pour into greased mold and congeal.
Serves 12.

title: chicken salad
directions: Chop chicken breasts into small bite size pieces.
Add lite Miracle Whip, sour cream, grapes, celery seed and pickle relish. Put on bed of lettuce.
Add your choice of fruits.
Makes an attractive fruit plate.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Make white sauce of butter, flour and milk; then add next six ingredients.
Remove from heat.
Add sherry.
Add little hot sauce to egg; then add egg to rest of sauce.
Add hot sauce, salt, pepper and crabmeat.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole; sprinkle top with bread crumbs, mixed with 1 tablespoon melted butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fluffy dinner rolls
directions: Boil butter and water in saucepan.
Add flour and salt.
Keep stirring fast as it thickens.
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: pizza pasta
directions: Brown pepperoni, onion and mushrooms.
Add spaghetti sauce, tomato paste, water and oil and blend well.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Add cooked mostaccioli; blend well.
Pour into 12 x 8 x 2-inch casserole; top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Beat well.
Bake in an 11 x 13-inch pan for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Spread a large jar of marshmallow cream over cake while hot.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine beans and onion in a bowl.
Stir in soup, milk and seasonings.
Spoon into 2-quart baking dish. Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and set aside.
Combine rest of ingredients in saucepan and heat until marshmallows are melted. Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan, greased and floured, and bake at 350° until done.
The cake is rich enough without frosting, but you may add frosting if you wish to.

title: beef tips stir-fry
directions: Cut beef into thin strips, 2 to 3-inches long.
Toss with 1/4 to 1/2 cup soy sauce and the meat tenderizer.
Cover with foil and refrigerate at least 2 hours or until ready to use.
Fry over medium heat until done.
Cut green pepper and onion into rings. Saute in 2 tablespoons butter and 1/4 cup soy sauce until tender. Saute rice in 2 tablespoons butter and 1/4 cup soy sauce until coated well.
Place rice on platter; layer onion and beef on top, then cover with beef tips.

title: creamed corn muffins(or cornbread)
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease 12 muffin cups (or muffin pan with 12).
Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add margarine.
Mix (if using oil instead of margarine).
Add oil to buttermilk and egg. Add corn.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Mix until moist.
Spoon into muffin pans and bake 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.

title: chicken cheddar bake
directions: Cook chicken breasts until done.
Tear meat off bone in bite size pieces.
Cook broccoli until half done, drain and put into square 8-inch baking dish.
In small saucepan, melt margarine, add bouillon cube and flour.
Cook 1 minute, then add milk, salt and pepper.
Stir over medium heat until thickened.
Add chicken pieces and mushrooms to this and spread over broccoli.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Makes about 1 pint.

title: cheezy noodle soup
directions: Prepare Ramen noodles as directed except before adding noodles, break an egg into boiling water.
Cook, stirring for 1 minute.
Add noodles.
When noodles are done, add both slices American cheese.
When melted, add flavor packet (good with any flavor).
Add soy sauce to taste.
Very good.

title: dump cake(favorite for the kids to do)
directions: Dump undrained pineapple in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread evenly.
Dump pie filling evenly over pineapple.
Dump dry cake mix over cherry pie filling.
Spread evenly.
Sprinkle pecans over cake. Slice butter into thin slices and lay on top.
Bake at 350° for 48 to 53 minutes.

title: bran date bread
directions: Grate 1 teaspoon of orange rind and set aside.
Remove remaining peel from orange; chop fruit in blender or food processor adding enough water to make 1 cup. Set aside.

In medium bowl, combine Shredded Wheat cereal, baking powder and salt; set aside. In another bowl, with electric mixer at medium speed, beat margarine, sugar and eggs until blended. Stir in reserved orange and orange rind.
Stir in flour mixture until well blended. Fold in dates or raisins.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Cool in pan on wire rack 10 minutes. Remove from pan and cool completely on rack.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Line bottom of 8 1/2 x 11-inch casserole dish with ice cream sandwiches. (Should take about 9 1/2 sandwiches.) Sprinkle 1/3 of the Heath Bar pieces on top of the sandwiches. Add a second layer of ice cream sandwiches. Poke holes in the sandwiches with a fork. Drizzle the Kahlua over the sandwiches. Sprinkle more of the Heath Bar pieces, saving a few for the top. Spread whipped topping on top and garnish with the remaining Heath Bar pieces. Keep frozen until serving. It is easiest to serve when frozen overnight. Serve on a dessert plate and drizzle with caramel sauce.
tags: vanilla ice cream sandwiches with chocolate outside

title: icebox pickles
directions: Mix well; do not heat.
Pour over cucumbers and store in airtight container for 5 days.
Do not open for 5 days.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Saute onion, add hamburger meat and cook until no longer pink. Remove from heat.
Add rice, Worcestershire sauce and tomato sauce.
Set aside.
Remove tops, membrane and seeds from bell peppers.
Drop the peppers into salted boiling water for five minutes.
Remove and cool in cold water.
Drain and then fill with meat mixture.
Place into a deep casserole and cover with tomato juice.
Bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: pineapple cream salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream together with mixer.
Fold in remaining ingredients.

title: tangy mustard chicken
directions: Remove skin and fat from each piece of chicken; pat dry with paper towels.
Cut each piece across thickness of breasts, 2 to 3 cuts.
Brush medium coat of mustard on both sides of chicken. Salt liberally with both seasoned salt and lemon pepper.
Place chicken in deep baking dish, bone side down.
Bake at 350° until tender and brown (do not cover).
Turn once to brown both sides. Cooking time is 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: breakfast potato pie
directions: Cover hash browns with 1 quart of hot water and let stand 10 minutes; drain.
Beat eggs.
Add potatoes and remaining ingredients.
Pour into well-greased pie plate.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Place cold pie plate (uncovered) in cold oven.
Turn heat to 350° and bake 35 minutes or until potatoes are tender and eggs are set.
Excellent idea for a brunch.
Bagels go very well with this dish.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Cook rice in large saucepan according to directions, using chicken broth instead of water. Add mushrooms before last 5 minutes. Stir in chicken, dressing and sour cream; spoon into lightly greased 2-quart baking dish. Bake at 325° in oven for 30 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Serves 6.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla; add flour, chips and nuts. Form into balls about 1-inch in diameter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press down with lightly floured bottom of small glass.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 14 minutes or until edges are golden.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Cook onions, peppers and hamburger in a frypan.
Pour off grease and put into a crock-pot.
Add catsup, water, salt, pepper, garlic salt, chili powder, sugar and mustard.
Simmer.
Place over hamburger bun with coleslaw.

title: orange sherbet mold or salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add sherbet and orange juice; beat slowly with hand mixer.
Increase mixer speed as sherbet melts.
Add pineapple and oranges.
Can be poured into a large greased mold or a very large bowl.
Refrigerate until firm. Run knife around edge of mold to loosen.
Serve topped with Cool Whip if you like.
This recipe can be halved.

title: pepperoni bites
directions: For the filling, in a bowl, combine Mozzarella cheese, pepperoni and pizza sauce.
Set aside.
Then separate biscuits. Flatten biscuits to 3-inch circles.
Place about 1 rounded tablespoon of filling in the center of each circle.
Bring the edges of the dough together; pinch to seal.
Place, seam sides down, on greased baking sheets.
Brush with milk.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes until brown.
Serve warm.
Makes 20.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in casserole.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in 325° oven.
Last 10 minutes, sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Toss apples with cinnamon.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.

title: virginia's peach pie
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour and baking powder with milk.
Do not overmix.
Pour into hot melted margarine.
Scatter fruit over top of batter.
Do not mix.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: rosemary roasted potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and either half or quarter them.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, pour in olive oil to cover bottom of pan (about 1/8-inch). Roll potatoes in oil.
Strip the leaves off the rosemary and sprinkle on top of the potatoes.
Heat oven to 400° and roast until golden brown, stirring occasionally, 30 to 45 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: chicken and asparagus roll-ups
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pound chicken breast to 1/8-inch thick. Place 4 asparagus spears, ham and slice of Swiss onto flattened breasts and roll up.
Roll each roll-up into flour, garlic, salt and pepper mixture to coat.
Place each roll-up in baking dish. Pour chicken broth over roll-ups.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes. Uncover and bake until golden brown.
May be garnished with slices of tomato or ring of onion and parsley.
Serves 4.

title: hot cross buns
directions: About 4 1/2 hours before serving or early in day: In bowl, combine yeast, sugar, potato flakes, salt, nutmeg and 1 1/2 cups flour.
In saucepan, heat milk, margarine and 3/4 cup water until very warm (125°).
With mixer at low speed, beat liquid into dry ingredients.
At medium, beat 2 minutes.
Beat in 2 eggs and 1 cup flour; beat 2 minutes.
Stir in currants, raisins, orange peel and 2 1/2 cups flour.

title: e. g.'s broiled pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place water in bottom of broiling pan. Place sheet of aluminum foil on broiling pan.
Arrange pork chops and potatoes on aluminum foil.
Pour corn on top of pork chops and potatoes.
Sprinkle dry ingredients to taste.
Pour Heinz 57 over mixture.
Shake Worcestershire to taste.
Cover with aluminum foil and seal closed.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheesy garlic bread
directions: Mix mayonnaise, cheese, onions and garlic.
Spread on bread halves.
Cover with foil, refrigerate 1 to 2 hours or freeze. Unwrap before baking.

title: whipped cream frosting
directions: Mix milk and flour into a paste. Cook over low heat until thick. Remove from stove and cool. Beat butter and Crisco for 4 minutes, then add sugar. Beat 4 minutes more and add to cooled paste. Beat 4 minutes more and fold in vanilla; spread on cake. Makes enough frosting for 2 cakes. Store in refrigerator.

title: chili
directions: Cook and drain meat. Add other ingredients and simmer for hours. (The more, the better.)

title: cheesy scalloped potatoes and sausage(crock-pot)
directions: Cut smoked sausage into bite-sized slices.
Put in water and boil; drain.
Spray crock-pot with no stick spray.
Starting with potatoes, layer all ingredients except milk.
When all is layered, add milk.
Cover crock-pot.
Cook on high until done, about 4 hours.

title: sock-it-to-me cake
directions: Mix all ingredients (except brown sugar and cinnamon) together. Pour 1/2 of mixture into stem pan.
Sprinkle a layer of brown sugar and cinnamon over mixture.
Pour in remaining batter.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: bundle of beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Divide beans into 8 bundles.
Wrap with slice of bacon and pin with toothpick.
Place in baking dish.
Combine sugar, garlic and juice and pour over beans. Bake for 35 minutes.

title: christmas eve mushroom soup
directions: Combine
water,
mushrooms,
cup butter and broth. Bring to boil and lower heat.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Meanwhile, in small pan, brown 2 tablespoons butter, flour and onion to make roux. Add
to soup.
If desired, add 1/2 cup sauerkraut juice for a tart flavor.
Boil noodle egg drops and add to soup just before serving.
Soup
freezes
well;
do
not add noodles if freezing. Serve with cabbage turnovers.

title: easter eggs
directions: Mix together thoroughly with your hands.
Shape into eggs. Chill thoroughly.
Eggs should be cold when covered with melted chocolate.

title: four-cheese fettuccine
directions: Heat butter and half and half in a 2-quart saucepan over low heat until butter is melted.
Stir in Gruyere cheese, Parmesan cheese, salt, pepper and garlic.
Cook, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and chop potatoes.
Combine onions, bouillon, parsley flakes, salt, water, margarine, pepper and evaporated milk in Dutch oven.
Mix well. Cook on low heat for 2 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: beef roll-ups
directions: Pound both sides of steak.
Sprinkle one side with garlic; set aside.
Cook bacon to the "almost" crisp state.
Top meat with bacon and roll up jelly roll style.
Fasten with toothpicks to hold and slice to desired thickness.
Marinate by package directions. Barbecue to desired doneness, basting with marinade.
Good hot or cold.

title: pineapple cream cheese sandwich spread
directions: Soften cream cheese, then mix with all of the ingredients. Makes a good sandwich; not too sweet.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix ingredients and beat for a minute. Bring to a boil. Cook until thick. Add 1/2 stick margarine. Cool and pour into a 9-inch baked pie shell.

title: pig-lickin' cake
directions: Mix all these together well and bake in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: meringue for pie that won't weep or shrink
directions: Cook cornstarch, sugar and water until clear. Set aside.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine milk, soup and pepper; pour over beans.
Add 1/2 can onions; pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Garnish with remaining onions and grated cheese.
Bake 5 minutes longer or until cheese melts.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chilliquilles
directions: In heavy skillet, brown ground beef, stirring with fork to break up.
Add onion and garlic; cook until onion is clear. Drain.
Add 2 cans of drained tomatoes and can of tomatoes with chilies to meat mixture.
Let simmer, stirring occasionally, approximately 3 to 4 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Remove from heat.
Place a layer of tortilla chips overlapping in bottom of 2-quart casserole.
Top with meat and tomato mixture, then a thick layer of cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese.
Cover and heat in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes until hot and bubbly around edges.
Uncover and spread with sour cream.
Sprinkle with paprika and
chopped green onion.

title: sugarless cake
directions: Take one man,
one
woman;
blend
with lots of Love, a true understanding
of each other's needs, a sincere desire to do God's will in
all that you do and trust Him for everything you need and God
will	richly bless your life, which makes a happy life.

title: parmesan green beans
directions: Saute onions in a tablespoon of the bacon grease.
Stir in beans and add chopped bacon bits.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Toss Parmesan cheese through the beans.
Place in casserole dish and garnish with French onion rings.

title: new orleans style barbecue shrimp
directions: Peel and devein 1 pound shrimp.
In small bowl, blend first 7 ingredients together.
In large skillet, heat 1/4 pound unsalted butter and 1 tablespoon minced garlic.
Add the shrimp and spice mixture and saute over medium heat, 1 to 2 minutes per side (this still should be slightly opaque down the middle of the spine).
Add and simmer briefly, Worcestershire and beer.

title: squash casserole (slow cooker)
directions: Combine squash, onion, carrots and soup. Mix together sour cream and flour, stir in vegetables. Toss stuffing mix with butter, spread half in bottom of slow cooker. Add vegetable mixture, top with remaining crumbs. Cover and cook on low for 7-9 hours. Makes 4-6 servings.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients altogether for 5 minutes.
Drain, then add cream of chicken soup and sour cream.
Melt oleo with seasoning from stuffing mix.
Mix in stuffing crumbs.
Put half in bottom of pan.
Pour vegetable mixture over that and add stuffing crumbs to top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: southern pie crust
directions: Add salt to flour.
Cut in shortening.
Add ice water, stirring until all flour is moistened and forms a ball.
Handling the dough as little as possible, roll out pastry for 9-inch pie crust.
Bake at 450° for about 10 minutes.
Cool completely before filling.

title: pie crust
directions: Sift flour, salt and sugar.
Cut in Crisco.
Mix egg, water and vinegar.
Add to flour mixture.
Divide in 4 parts.
Keep chilled until rolled.
Bake at 425° for 12 minutes.
Yields 4 (9-inch) crusts.

title: barbecue
directions: Saute ground beef until red is gone.
Add onion, green pepper and celery.
Keep stirring.
Add vinegar, mustard, sugar, ketchup and chili sauce.
Stir all together and let simmer.
Add more ketchup and chili sauce if it is not red enough.
Cook for about an hour.
For more beef just double the recipe.

title: raspberry applesauce
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Stir in applesauce and chill.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cut zucchini and carrots into pieces.
Cook until tender.
Mix 1 cup sour cream with 1 can Campbell's cream of chicken soup.
Add to vegetables and mix.

title: sticky buns
directions: Place frozen rolls in Bundt or angel food pan; sprinkle pudding over the top.
Mix melted margarine and brown sugar and pour over the frozen rolls. Cover pan with damp cloth and let rise overnight.
Set oven to 350° and bake for 30 to 35 minutes. Remove from oven and put into a large serving dish.

title: custard pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and salt.
Add milk and vanilla; pour into pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Lower temperature to 350°; bake for 30 minutes, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: pumpkin-chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat shortening at medium speed until fluffy; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add egg and pumpkin, mixing well.
Combine flour and next 4 ingredients; add to pumpkin mixture.
Stir in vanilla, chocolate chips and pecans.
Drop by tablespoons onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 13 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool completely.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook and drain the spaghetti.
Add Season-All and oil.
Let cool.
Add remaining ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: cucumber cream relish
directions: In stock pot, place cucumber, onion, water and salt.
Soak overnight.
Drain.
Mix flour with 4 cups of vinegar.
Add to cucumber.
Mix along with remaining ingredients.
Mix well and boil until thick.
Seal in hot, sterilized jars 1/2-inch from top. Makes 8 pints.

title: boiled oatmeal cookies
directions: Drop on wax paper.
Be very careful to cook 1 1/2 minutes and work fast or they will get too dry to handle.

title: cornbread
directions: Add liquid mixture to dry ingredients, mixing just enough to moisten.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan (greased or coated with vegetable spray).
Bake at 375° until lightly browned, about 25 minutes.

title: tortellini with crab gorgonzola
directions: Pick over the crab meat to remove any lingering shell fragments.
Set aside 1/3 crab for a garnish.
Crumble the cheese. Saute the shallots in butter over low heat until softened. Add wine and cream and heat to a boil. Add crumbled cheese and 2/3 of the crab.

Reduce the sauce over high heat for 1 minute. Add the tortellini and continue cooking over high heat for another 2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper and remove to dinner plates. Garnish the tortellini with reserved crab and sprinkle with chopped parsley.
Serves 2.

title: easy nachos(microwave)
directions: You will need a microwave platter covered with waxed paper.

title: pecan rolls(club member: christy hosey)
directions: Melt butter, marshmallows and condensed milk. Combine crushed graham crackers, coconut and pecans (saving small amount of crackers to roll mixture in). Combine liquid and dry ingredients; mix well. Divide into 2 rolls. Wrap in waxed paper. Refrigerate and eat.

title: gary crowder's favorite pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and shortening together until coarsely crumbled.
Add cold water.
Mix until dough is easily handled. Divide and roll into 3 pie crusts.
Makes 3 (9-inch) crusts.

title: ham and cheese sandwiches
directions: Soften margarine; add next 3 ingredients. Spread on split buns. Add ham and cheese. Wrap each sandwich in foil. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: bell pepper dressing
directions: Brown meat in heavy roaster.
Add vegetables; saute until onion is clear.
Add soup, water, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.
Turn fire up to get mixture hot.
Add rice; stir with fork.
Turn heat off.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover tightly until cheese melts.

title: potatoes and herbs
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Wash potatoes.
If potatoes are bite size, leave whole.
If larger, cut into quarters or eighths.

title: parmesan oven fried chicken
directions: Mix together egg and milk.
Set aside.
Mix together Parmesan cheese, flour, paprika and seasoned salt.
Dip chicken in milk and egg mixture.
Roll in cheese and flour mixture.
Place in baking dish or pan.
Pour 1/4 cup liquid butter over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Mixture can be doubled for larger chicken pieces.

title: candied cherry cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar and egg; stir in remaining ingredients except candied cherries.
Divide dough in half; stir red cherries into one half and green cherries into other half.
Shape each half into roll, 1 1/2 inches in diameter; wrap.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours.

title: ranch oyster crackers
directions: Combine all ingredients together except crackers; whisk until well blended.
Pour mixture over crackers, tossing to coat.
Place on a baking sheet or two and bake at 275° for 15 to 20 minutes. Yield: 11 to 12 cups.

title: savory salmon
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Arrange salmon in a buttered baking dish.
Spread 2 tablespoons of the salad dressing over each steak. Sprinkle with the dill and parsley.
Bake until the fish flakes easily, when tested with a fork, 10 to 15 minutes.
Place under a broiler for 45 to 60 seconds to brown.
Serve with lemon wedges.

title: beef steak and creamy gravy(lower fat)
directions: Cut meat into 4 serving size pieces.
Mix in small bowl 2 tablespoons flour and pepper.
Pound flour mixture into meat. Spray large skillet with nonstick spray coating.
Over medium heat, brown meat on both sides.
Add water and bouillon granules to skillet.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 1 hour or until meat is tender.

title: gingerbread boys and girls
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and mix well.
Add dry pudding mix, flour and spices.
Mix well.
Roll or pat out dough and cut with cookie cutter.

title: shrimp in sour cream
directions: Cut large shrimp in half.
Saute mushrooms and onions in butter.
Blend in flour.
Add shrimp, soup, sour cream, lemon juice and lemon pepper.
Serve over toast triangles.

title: aunt eva's soda cracker pie
directions: Roll crackers to fine crumbs.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add slowly 1 cup sugar, as for a meringue.
Add baking powder, vinegar, vanilla and walnuts to meringue; fold in.
Add cracker crumbs and fold in.
Pile into well-greased pie pan and bake about 40 minutes at 300°.
When cooled, can be refrigerated, even until next day.
An hour or so before serving, whip cream and spread on top.
Put in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: meringue kisses
directions: In small bowl, beat egg whites.
Add 2/3 cup sugar.
When it stands in peaks, add vanilla and remaining sugar.
Place wax paper on cookie sheet.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on sheet.
Add color, if desired. Bake at 250° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 30 to 40 kisses.

title: angel pie
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add cream of tartar; continue beating, gradually adding the sugar, until the mixture is stiff. Fold in pecans.
Spread over 9-inch baked pie crust and bake in 300° oven for 1 hour.

title: spinach-rice salad
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Rinse and drain. Set aside.
Combine salad dressing, soy sauce and sugar in a large bowl.
Stir in rice.
Cover and chill 2 hours.
Stir spinach and remaining ingredients into rice mixture.
Serve immediately. Serves 6 to 8.

title: punch with a "punch"
directions: Chill ingredients.
Mix in punch bowl adding champagne or 7-Up last.
Add ice cubes; garnish with orange slices.
Serves 25.

title: summer punch
directions: Mix all ingredients, except water and 7-Up.
The other juices can be frozen and when ready to serve, add the water and 7-Up.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mash avocados well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Serve with warm corn tortilla chips.

title: garlic pickles
directions: Put first 5 ingredients in layers and cover with ice cubes. Let stand 3 hours and then drain.
Mix next 5 ingredients and pour over cucumber mixture.
Let simmer until good and hot through. Put in jars and seal.

title: angel food dessert
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients until creamy.
Tear the angel food cake into bite-sized pieces and layer with the creamed mixture. The last layer should be the creamed mixture.
Top with the pie filling of your choice.
(I recommend blueberry or cherry.)
Chill and serve.

title: pepper cabbage
directions: Chop fine cabbage, green pepper and onion.
Add sugar in a bowl.
Bring the following to a boil:
vinegar, salt, oil, dry mustard, 2 tablespoons sugar and celery seed.
Remove from heat and cool.
Pour over cabbage.
Refrigerate overnight.
Do not stir.

title: chops in a soup
directions: Rub chops with salt and pepper, brown in skillet with butter. Remove chops and brown onions.
Place potatoes in 2-quart baking dish (greased).
Arrange chops on top.
Add soup and milk to onions in skillet.
Blend until smooth.
Pour mixture over chops. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover.
Continue baking for 30 to 40 minutes until potatoes are done.
Serves 6.

title: wanda's poke and pour chocolate caramel cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed on package and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Remove from oven and poke holes in cake with a wooden spoon handle.
Pour sweetened condensed milk into holes.
Then pour ice cream topping over that.
Frost with whipped topping and sprinkle with crushed candy bars.
Refrigerate.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt
the butter and stir in the brown sugar, syrup and salt. Cook
minutes.
Add
soda
and vanilla.	Pour over 2 pans of corn.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir 3 or 4 times.

title: watermelon pickles
directions: Trim pink pulp and skin from rind and cut into 1-inch square pieces.
Add alum to 1 cup water and pour over rind.
Add enough water to cover rind; cover vessel with plate and let stand for 12 hours.
Measure into kettle sugar, vinegar, water and spices. Heat rind (still in alum water) to the boiling point.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Let stand until thoroughly cold.
Drain and dry. Boil vinegar mixture until a thin syrup forms.
Ad rind and cook until rind is transparent and tender.
Ladle into clean sterile jars; cover with sugar and seal while hot.

title: vegetable beef soup(serves 8)
directions: Combine beef,
tomatoes,
soup and onion in cooker. Add water, beans and vegetables. Add salt, pepper and other spices of preference. Stir
well.
Cook
at lowest setting for 4 to 6 hours.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: You can add a little vinegar from the peppers.
Mix all together and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: strawberry ice cream pie
directions: Bake pie crust first.
Mix together the hot water, jello and ice cream; chill for 1/2 hour, then add the strawberries.
Top with whipped cream.
Put in refrigerator, and it's ready to serve.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips, butter and peanut butter over low heat, stirring constantly.
