Pour over Corn Chex and stir until covered. Let dry.
Pour powdered sugar in a large paper sack.
Pour chocolate covered Chex in a bag and shake.
(Will look dusty.) Yield 4 cups.

title: lemon clam spaghetti
directions: Heat 3 tablespoons of the butter and oil in a heavy pan. Saute onion and garlic until tender.
Add liquid from clams, lemon juice, parsley, lemon peel, pepper and bay leaf.
Simmer until liquid is reduced to about 1 cup.
Remove bay leaf.
Stir in clams and heat thoroughly.
Add remaining butter, stir until melted.

title: portuguese white sour pudding
directions: In a saucepan, put water and sugar until sugar dissolves.
Add gelatin and let this cool for a while.
Add sour cream, vanilla and mix.
Next, add whipped cream and mix again very well.
Pour it in a mold and refrigerate for several hours.
Serve with the sauce and fresh fruit.

title: pancake for two
directions: Beat eggs.
Slowly add flour, salt, sugar, milk and cooled oleo.
Pour into lightly sprayed skillet.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Will puff, but fall when cut.
Serve with warm syrup.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Prepare the eggplant before starting your meal in the following manner:

Peel the eggplant and cut it into 2 to 3 inch cubes. Cover it with salty water and let it soak for about 30 minutes. Drain the eggplant thoroughly and put the eggplant, onion, celery, and the packet of seasonings from the Stove Top stuffing in a large pot with 1 1/2 cups of water.

Boil it slowly for about 30 minutes. Remove from heat and add corn bread stuffing and pimentos (if mixture is too dry, add water and if it is too wet, add old bread). Dump mixture into a greased baking dish.
Cover with cheese and bake in a 375° oven for about 15 minutes.

title: chicken-fried pork chops
directions: Whip the eggs with 3 tablespoons water in order to make an egg wash.
Mix the remaining ingredients except the oil together and place on a plate.
Dip the chops into the egg wash and then into coating mix.
Pan fry in a bit of oil over medium heat until golden brown and done to your taste.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken and Italian dressing.
Chill 1 hour.
Add other ingredients.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Combine prepared dressing with sugar and sour cream.
Mix well. Pour over cucumbers and tomato.
Refrigerate for 1 hour before serving.

title: nut date bread
directions: Cut dates; add water and soda.
Let stand while preparing the other ingredients.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add melted butter and egg, well beaten.
Last, add chopped dates and water, walnuts and vanilla.

title: chicken victoria with cream sauce
directions: Heat cream until hot, not boiling.
Using 1/4 cup butter and 1/4 cup flour, make white sauce, stirring in hot cream.
Stir until thickened.
Set aside.
Combine remaining flour with salt and pepper and coat chicken.
Heat 2 tablespoons butter.
Saute chicken until brown.
Keep warm.
Heat 2 tablespoons butter and saute mushrooms.
Add shrimp.
Cook until pink.
Stir in crabmeat and wine.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat.
Stir in cream sauce and 3/4 cup cheese.
Keep warm.
For each serving, put 3/4 cup sauce onto plate.
Top with chicken and 1 tablespoon cheese.
Serves 6.

title: microwave hash
directions: Combine oleo, peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Microwave about 2 1/2 minutes.
Stir.
Pour mix over 1 large package of Rice Chex.
Stir until mixed.
(Use a large bowl.)
Shake in grocery sack in powdered sugar.
Stack in covered plastic bowl.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Knead
flour, butter and pecans with hands.
Press into a
9 x
13-inch casserole dish.	Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Whip vanilla,
Dream
Whip and cold water until peaks appear. Cream the
powdered sugar and cream cheese and add to whipped mixture. Pour
over	cooled	crust.	Top with 1 can blueberry filling and refrigerate.

title: almond fried chicken
directions: Combine flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
In separate bowl, combine milk and eggs.
Dip chicken first in flour, then milk mixture, then flour, then milk mixture, then roll in almonds. Melt 2 tablespoons butter in bottom of pan.
Place chicken in melted butter.
Melt rest of butter and pour on top of chicken. Bake 1 hour at 400°.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix and bake until thick at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chocolate peanut butter cups
directions: Line small muffin pan with 1 1/4 x 1-inch paper cups.
In medium bowl, blend peanut butter and syrup.
Add sugar slowly, turn onto a smooth board and knead until smooth.
Press to 1/2 inch thickness.
With a 1 inch round cookie cutter, cut out circles.
Melt chocolate.
Spoon 1 teaspoon chocolate into paper cup.
Place a peanut butter round on top; press gently.
Top with 1 teaspoon more chocolate.
Chill until firm.
Store in refrigerator.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Cool and debone; reserve broth. Place half of dressing mix in buttered casserole.
Layer 1/2 the chicken.
Combine broth, soup and seasonings from dressing mix; pour half of this over chicken.
Repeat layers.
Dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand for a few minutes before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sweet 'n' creamy iced coffee
directions: In a heat-proof pitcher, dissolve the coffee granules in the hot water. Add the sweetened condensed milk. Mix well. Allow to cool slightly, then serve in tall glasses over ice. Makes 6 to 8 servings (about 2 quarts).

title: zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs, oil and sugar. Add zucchini, cinnamon, salt, baking soda, baking powder and flour.
Mix well, then add chopped nuts. Place in greased 9 x 12-inch pan or two 9-inch round pans. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: crunchy taco bake
directions: Brown the ground beef.
Add the onion; drain.
Stir in chili or refried beans, tomato sauce, tomato paste, chili powder and salt. Cook until heated and flavors blended.
Sprinkle 1 cup corn chips on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon on meat mixture. Top with remaining chips. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake until cheese melts at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: hot dip
directions: Brown hamburger meat and sausage.
Add broccoli.
Cook until thawed.
Cut Velveeta into chunks.
Either add cheese while cooking to melt it or put all ingredients into crock-pot on low for 3 or 4 hours until melted.

title: seafood creole
directions: Prepare roux by melting margarine in large skillet.
Over medium heat, blend in flour and stir constantly until roux is dark brown.
Be careful not to scorch.

title: cheese cake
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Add sour cream and vanilla.
Put into graham cracker crust.
Top with sliced strawberries.

title: pickled beans
directions: Cook beans in water until tender.
Mix water, salt and vinegar. Drain beans and pack in jars, cold or hot.
Pack in jars; put a pod of hot pepper in each jar on top.
Cover beans with liquid.
Seal cold.

title: chicken divan
directions: Place uncooked broccoli (thawed and drained) in bottom of an 11 x 7-inch casserole dish.
Cut chicken in slivers and place on top of broccoli.
In small bowl, combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice; pour over chicken and broccoli.
Top with cheese and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese; add garlic, then Heinz 57.
Add a little over half the pecans; mix until well blended.
Shape into ball. Roll ball in remaining pecans until all pieces are used and ball is covered well.
Make a day before planning to serve it.
Put in small bowl to keep its shape in refrigerator.
Serve with thin crackers.

title: yogurt chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat egg whites, brown sugar, yogurt and vanilla until well blended. Gradually add the mixed dry ingredients until moistened. Pour into 8-inch square pan that has been sprayed with cooking spray and dusted with flour. Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes. Cool pan on rack for 20 minutes. Put on plate and dust with powdered sugar. Serves 6.

title: seafoam candy
directions: In heavy 2-quart saucepan, combine sugars, corn syrup and water.
Cook, stirring, until sugar dissolve.
Continue cooking until a small amount forms hard ball in cool water.
Set aside and cool slightly.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water; mix and pour into mold. Chill until firm, then put mold into hot water until it comes loose into plate.

title: spicy pork
directions: Cut pork into strips.
Mix all other ingredients and add pork strips; let stand in cool place for 24 hours.
Cut as much meat as needed for 1 meal into cubes and brown in oil.
Add chile sauce and simmer 1 hour.
This meat can be dried and used later.

title: date pudding (cake)
directions: Add soda to hot water and pour over dates.
Let stand until cool.
Blend sugar and eggs.
Add dates and other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in an 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Serve with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: quick and yummy mini pizzas
directions: Split the hamburger buns into 4 halves.
Place the 4 halves, flat side up, on a cookie sheet.
Broil until the tops are lightly browned (about 2 to 3 minutes), but be careful not to burn them. Remove from oven.
Spread 1 tablespoon pizza sauce evenly on each half bun.
Sprinkle cheese evenly on top of sauce as desired. Apply pepperoni, if desired.
Set oven to 350° and bake pizzas for 4 to 5 minutes, or until cheese is lightly browned.
Makes 4 pizzas.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix by hand.
Roll in chili powder or nuts.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut hard-cooked eggs in half, lengthwise.
Remove yolks and mash
with
fork.
Add other ingredients until smooth and fluffy. Refill whites of eggs.
Garnish with paprika.

title: coconut flake cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients. Drop on cookie sheet by teaspoon.
Bake at 375°, about 12 minutes.

title: midwest chowder
directions: Combine potatoes, carrots, celery, onion, salt and pepper. Add the water and simmer, covered, for 10 minutes. Do not drain.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and rice as directed on each package. Drain any juice that is left after cooking. Combine with all other ingredients and turn into a 3-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with paprika and bake at 350°.

title: speedy chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: In a medium bowl, combine peanut butter and chocolate syrup. Stir in graham cracker crumbs.
Lightly spread butter or margarine onto the palms of your hands, then form dough into 1-inch balls. Roll each ball in chopped peanuts.
Chill in refrigerator until firm.
Makes about 16 cookies.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all together and put in greased pan.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: fried tuna and potato patties
directions: Mix tuna, potatoes, curry powder, parsley, celery and onion salt together.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Form into patties and dredge in flour; dip in beaten egg and fry in hot oil until well browned on both sides.
Serves 4.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and mix at low speed for 2 minutes. Pour into a 9x13-inch greased pan.
Cut rhubarb in small pieces and mix with sugar and cream.
Pour over top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
(Glass Pan bake at 325°.)

title: onion rings
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Slice and separate onions.
Dip onion rings and fry in 2 inches of oil until golden on each side (grease temperature should be medium-high).

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spoon onto cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: marinated noodle salad
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over noodles.
Marinate overnight.

title: pizza cups
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spread each biscuit in each of 10 muffin cups which have been lightly greased with shortening. Brown ground beef.
Season with salt and pepper. Drain grease off. Add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Mix and simmer for 5 to 6 minutes. Spoon beef mixture into dough lined muffin cups.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until crust looks done.
Remove from oven and top with cheese.
Return to oven until cheese melts. Serve warm.

title: lemon salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cold water when partially set.
Add pie filling.
Mix.
Add Mandarin oranges and pineapple tidbits.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix mandarin oranges, eggs and oil; beat 2 minutes on highest speed of mixer.
Reduce speed to low and beat 1 minute.
Pour batter in 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes, then remove and cool completely.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Allow chicken to cook until tender. Mix cream of chicken, cream of celery, and 1 cup of chicken broth. Allow to cook until soup is no longer lumpy. Allow chicken to cool and debone. Place chicken into pie crust. Pour vegetables over chicken and then soup over vegetables. Take 2nd pie crust and cut into strips and place over chicken. Cook until pie crust is brown on 350 degrees.

title: lemon bars
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until light.
Gradually add flour, blending well.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° approximately 15 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press into a pizza pan 1/2 to 3/4 roll of sugar cookie dough and bake according to directions.
Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Pour over cool cookie dough crust.
Place your choice of fruits over the top (strawberries, kiwis, bananas, pineapple, mandarin oranges, etc.).
Cut into wedges when ready to serve.

title: easy coconut cream pie
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees. Remove clear insert from crust. Brush crust with 1 beaten egg white. Bake 5 minutes on cookie sheet. Remove from oven, cool completely. Gently remove cooled crust from tin. Carefully place crust in bottom of pie plate. Set aside. Pour milk into a bowl and add pudding mix, 3/4 c. coconut and spice blend. Beat with wire whisk 2 minutes. Gently stir in 1 c. of the whipped topping. Pour into crust. Refrigerate for 4 hours or until set. Spread remaining whipped topping on pie, cover and place back in refrigerator.

title: applesauce fudgies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter together.
Mix applesauce, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Stir dry ingredients into applesauce mixture. Stir until blended.
Add chocolate and stir well.
Pour into well greased 9-inch pan (square).
Sprinkle with walnuts or pecans. Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Cut into 2 1/4-inch squares and cool in pan on rack.
Makes 16 squares.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Beat eggs and add all of the rest of the ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares for hors d'oeuvres.
Serves 12 to 18 large pieces or 36 to 48 small size. Serve hot or cold.

title: biscotti (italian cookie)
directions: Cream shortening and sugar in mixing bowl. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Stir in vanilla. Add flour and baking powder a little at a time. Mix until dough holds together, then knead until smooth. Form into balls or finger shapes. Place about 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 350° until light brown, about 10 minutes. Cool. Ice with confectioners sugar frosting.

title: festive fruit salad
directions: Core, rinse and thoroughly drain lettuce.
Refrigerate in plastic bag or crisper.
Cut cantaloupe and remove seeds and rind. Cut cantaloupe in chunks.
Remove outer leaves from lettuce and line large basket or platter.
Cut remaining lettuce into chunks and arrange with fruit.
Serve with Honey Yogurt Dressing.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Mix flour and shortening thoroughly.
Add remaining dry ingredients and mix.
Add water and knead until smooth, about 10 minutes.
Divide dough into 18 balls.
Roll each ball into a circle.
Cook on each side until they have golden brown spots.

title: quick and easy quiche
directions: Layer the first 3 ingredients.
Mix milk, eggs and Bisquick. Pour over ingredients.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt and cocoa.
Blend milks and egg yolks; add butter and vanilla.
Gradually stir into sugar mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Use egg whites to make meringue for pie.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Boil breasts until done.
Cook rice according to package.
Add rice to cream of chicken and cream of mushroom soups.
Add water and salt.
Place chicken breasts on bottom of casserole.
Pour rice mixture over chicken.

title: hot wings
directions: Salt and pepper the chicken wings.
Flour the wings and fry in hot oil until brown or fry your way.
Dip hot wings in hot sauce, enough to coat completely.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough on greased pizza pan.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes and let cool.

title: german chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together in mixing bowl.
Add eggs, flavoring and buttermilk.
Sift next 2 dry ingredients together. Add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Melt chocolate in top of double boiler.
Stir into batter, blending well.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Wrap in aluminum foil until cool.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: baked beans
directions: Put bacon in skillet, when bacon begins to sizzle, add onion and garlic; cook.
Stir often.
When onions
are clear, stir in remaining ingredients and pour into a 3-quart baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375° or until hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until thick.
Add small box strawberry jello.
Cool and add 1 pint strawberries.
Pour into baked pie shell (graham cracker crust is good).
Top with whipped cream.

title: pear preserves
directions: Wash, peel and cut fruit into good-size chunks.
Cook with 1/2 cup sugar to 1 cup fruit.
Wash and cut ends from 1 lemon.
Cut in half and juice.
Remove all seeds and put lemon hull and all in with fruit mixture.
Cook over medium heat until fruit is transparent.
Can immediately.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, onions and peppers in the 3 cups salted boiling water until tender.
Drain a little water off.
Add 1 quart rich milk.
Bring to a boil and add 1/3 cup margarine with 1 tablespoon flour mixed to a paste.
Stir into potato mixture.
Cook until thick.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend together and refrigerate!
Serve with assorted fresh fruit tray.

title: choo choo's quick meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Cook for 1 1/4 hours.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs; beat well.
Add flour and vanilla, then pecans and apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: special k bars
directions: Heat Karo syrup and sugar just long enough to melt the sugar. Add peanut butter and pour over Special K cereal.
Pat into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Melt package of chocolate chips and frost.

title: just like fried ice cream
directions: Make four 1/2-cup scoops ice cream.
Place on cookie sheet or shallow pan.
Cover and freeze until firm.

title: rich rolls or bread
directions: Combine warm milk and cake of yeast.
When yeast is dissolved, add shortening.
Beat in large bowl of mixer the eggs.
Add and beat well the sugar and salt.
Add and blend the milk mixture.
Add flour, one cup at a time, continuing to beat until enough flour is added to make a stiff batter.
Let batter rise in mixer.
Then beat well.
Do this two or three times.
Turn out on well floured board and knead until smooth.
Shape into rolls or loaves.
Put in well oiled pans, turning to grease both sides.
When it rises enough, bake as other bread at 400°.
Bake the loaves about 40 minutes, the rolls about 25 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream oleo, white sugar, brown sugar, vanilla and egg together.
Add in chocolate chips.
Then add sifted flour baking soda and salt together.
Mix well and add to wet ingredients. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet.

title: hot spiced apple cider
directions: Heat all ingredients together. Do not boil.

title: stewed flounder
directions: Fill large skillet, to cover bottom only, with water.
Place flounder in skillet.
Cut onion in very thin circles and add to top of flounder in skillet pan.
Cut lemon in half and squeeze juice onto flounder and onion (evenly).
Cut butter into slices and add all around top.

title: cheese grits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, bring broth to a boil.
Add grits; cook according to package directions.
Remove from heat; stir in cheese.
In bowl, combine eggs, milk and Tabasco sauce; stir the mixture into grits.
Pour into lightly greased casserole.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.
Let set 10 minutes before serving.

title: easy lime pie
directions: Combine milk, lime rind and juice in large bowl. Fold in whipped topping and food coloring, blending well. Spoon into crust and chill 2 to 3 hours. Garnish with lime slices, if desired.

title: brisket(barbecued)
directions: Coat brisket with liquid smoke.
Let sit for 30 minutes.
Add barbecue sauce.
Cook at 275° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours, tightly covered.
Uncover for the last 30 minutes.
Pour off fat.
Add additional sauce.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Cook macaroni using package directions; drain.
Saute onion in 1/4 cup margarine in skillet.
Add ground beef, salt and pepper. Cook until ground beef is brown and crumbly, stirring frequently; drain.
Layer macaroni, ground beef mixture and cheese in baking dish.
Combine soup and milk in bowl; mix well.
Pour over layers. Top with mixture of bread crumbs and 2 tablespoons margarine. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: chicken salad
directions: Stir curry powder and mayonnaise together.
Mix all together; chill.
Better if made several hours before serving.
Good summer dish.

title: applesauce donuts
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, applesauce, salt and soda. Sift flour. Add spices and baking powder.
Add to first mixture and mix well. Fry in deep fat at 375°.
Roll in sugar.

title: avocado dressing
directions: Combine in blender; blend smooth.

title: baked red snapper
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place onion slices in lightly oiled shallow baking dish.
Arrange fillets on top.
Pour oil and vinegar over fish.
Season with salt and paprika.
Bake 20 minutes or until fish flakes readily.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix and heat 15 minutes.
Serve warm with crackers to dip with.

title: green pea casserole
directions: Mix green peas, water chestnuts, onion, pimentos and mushroom soup.
Place in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Then top with cheese.
Melt butter and mix with cracker crumbs and put on top.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 400°.

title: blueberry sauce for pancakes, waffles
directions: Combine sugar, water, cornstarch, lemon juice and blueberries in saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick and clear. Simmer 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in 1 tablespoon butter or margarine.
Very good.

title: fresh blackberry pie
directions: Place berries in pie shell.
Combine 1 cup sugar, 1/3 cup flour, salt, eggs and sour cream until well blended.
Pour over berries.
In separate bowl, combine 1/2 cup sugar, 1/2 cup flour and 1/4 cup butter.
Mix until crumbly and sprinkle over pie.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes until light brown.

title: parmesan potato wedges
directions: Do not peel potatoes.
Scrub well and quarter lengthwise. Melt margarine and moisten wedges.
Combine all dry ingredients in a small bag.
Coat potatoes by shaking a few at a time in bag. Place potatoes in a 13 x 9-inch buttered baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until golden brown.
Turn once during baking time. Serves 6.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Prepare rice according to directions.
Mix all ingredients. Cover and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake 15 more minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mash 1/2 of the strawberries in pot. Stir in cornstarch, lemon juice and sugar. Cook over mild heat, stirring until thick. Cool. Cut remaining strawberries in half or quarters and add to cooled mixture. Pour into precooked pie crust. Refrigerate. Add whipped topping, if desired.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix tuna, milk and soup together.
Cook noodles until tender. Mix all ingredients together and place in a greased casserole dish.
Cover with bread crumbs and bake at 350° until brown.

title: swiss steak for two
directions: Cut meat into 2 pieces.
Mix flour, salt and pepper; coat meat in flour mixture.
Heat oil in 8-inch skillet.
Brown meat over medium heat, about 15 minutes.
Add tomatoes to skillet.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add green pepper, onion and salt.
Cover; simmer until meat is tender, 30 to 45 minutes.
(Add small amount of water, if necessary.)
Makes 2 servings.

title: lenten fruit cocktail cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except for brown sugar and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into a floured loaf pan.
Sprinkle top with brown sugar and nut mixture.
Bake at 375°
for 40 minutes.

title: cocoa drops
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and egg.
Stir in buttermilk and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and stir in.
Add nuts. Chill 1 hour.
(Can be left overnight.)
Drop by teaspoonfuls on baking sheets.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Pour in corn bread mix and cheese; mix well.
Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour mixture over melted margarine.
Bake at 350° approximately 40 to 45 minutes.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes and peel.
Do not overcook!!
Slice lengthwise when cool.
Melt 2 sticks of butter in electric frying pan. Stir in half of the brown sugar.
Bring to boil.
Add water as needed. Cook until thick.
Lay sweet potatoes in single layers into syrup.
Turn until coated.
Serve hot.
You will need to replenish mixture at least twice.

title: onion casserole
directions: Pam dish; add onion rings and almonds.
Pour soup over.
Add crushed corn flakes and pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: herb shaker #1
directions: Mix in a dry, tightly fitted jar.
Spoon this mixture into an empty salt shaker.
Use at your table or in cooking instead of salt.
You may shake it over meats, fish, rice, noodles, potatoes, vegetables, salads and soups.

title: zucchini bread(the best)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, mix the eggs, oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla. In another bowl, combine the flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon. Add to the egg mixture; stir in the nuts and raisins. Turn into 2 greased 8 x 4 loaf pans and bake for 50 to 55 minutes, until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Don't overbake.

title: bubble solution
directions: Pour the water into an empty 1 gallon container.
Add the dish soap and glycerine.
Shake gently to mix.

title: cheesy spinach dip
directions: Saute mushrooms and onion in 2 tablespoons butter. Add artichokes, soup and cheese. Heat on medium until mostly melted together. Add spinach and heat through. Best if served warm with tortilla chips.

title: chilled fruit salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream together first four ingredients.
Add zucchini.
Add dry ingredients.
Add nuts and raisins, if desired.
Pour evenly into 2 greased and floured bread loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix well whole eggs and sugar.
Add milk and corn flakes and mix again.
Add pumpkin and remaining ingredients and mix well. Mix with mixer, if needed, however corn flakes do not need to be fine.
If using can sweetened pumpkin, cut down 1/2 cup white sugar.

title: wild rice overnight
directions: Bring 2 cups chicken broth and salt to a boil; add 1 cup wild rice.
Cover.
Turn on low heat 40 minutes.
Turn off heat and let stand overnight.
Do not peek.
Next morning, add butter, mushrooms and onions.
Mix.
Cover.
Bake in casserole at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients well.
Add pecans.
Bake 15 minutes at 350° and then 30 to 40 minutes at 300°.
Makes two pies.

title: gumbo
directions: Cook the meat in the water on the stove for 30 minutes.
Add the flour and cook until it turns brown.
About 1 hour.
Put the rest of the stuff in it and cook for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Serve it over rice.

title: batter rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Stir in sugar, salt and margarine; cool to lukewarm.
Measure warm water into large warm bowl.
Sprinkle or crumble in yeast, stirring until dissolved.
Add lukewarm milk mixture, egg and 2 cups flour, beating until smooth.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make soft dough.
Cover and let rise in warm place, free from draft, until double in bulk; approximately 30 minutes.

title: rainbow fruit bowl
directions: In a glass serving dish, mix orange juice, lime juice and sugar.
Add grapes, kiwi, blueberries, oranges, banana and rum. Stir very gently.
Sprinkle red berries over top of fruit.
Cover bowl and refrigerate.
(Fruit may be mixed the day before serving.)

title: hay and gravel bars
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in brown sugar.
Add egg and milk.
Stir together flour and baking powder in a small bowl.
Stir all ingredients together and mix well.
Spread into greased 11 x 17 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, until toothpick comes out clean.

title: eclair dessert
directions: Layer graham crackers on bottom of Pyrex dish.
Mix pudding and milk until smooth.
Blend in Cool Whip and sour cream.
You can use 16 ounces Cool Whip and no sour cream.
Layer pudding and crackers until all pudding is used.
End with layer of crackers. Heat frosting in microwave for about 1 minute.
Pour over crackers and refrigerate.

title: butterhorns
directions: Combine yeast, 1 tablespoon sugar and water.
Let set 10 minutes.
Mix flour, butter, salt and 1/4 cup sugar.
Beat eggs and milk and add to dissolved yeast mixture.
Pour over flour mix and stir until mixed well.
Store in fridge overnight.

title: green pepper steak
directions: With sharp knife, cut beef across grain into thin strips 1/8-inch thick.
Combine soy sauce, garlic, ginger and beef; toss and set aside while cutting vegetables.
Brown meat over high heat until brown.
Taste meat.
If it is not tender, cover and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes over low heat.
Turn up heat and add vegetables; toss until vegetables are tender-crisp, about 10 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with water; add to meat.
Stir and cook until thickened.
Add tomatoes; heat thoroughly.
Serves 4.

title: wormy stuffed apples
directions: Mix peanut butter, Rice Krispies and grated carrots.
Core apples and stuff with the peanut butter mixture.
Poke hole in one end of apple and tuck one end of gummy worm in hole.

title: sprinkle salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, pouring dry jello in and mixing well. Chill and eat.
You can add nuts, if you want.

title: diabetic banana bread
directions: Grease 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Beat ingredients together with a spoon.
Pour into pan.
Bake 65 minutes at 350°.

title: flaky pie crust
directions: Mix the ingredients with fork and by hand.
Wet counter top and place a strip of Saran Wrap down.
Place dough on surface and place a piece of Saran Wrap on top of dough.
Roll dough.
Bake at 425° for 8 minutes or until brown.	Watch closely.

title: aunt peggy's asparagus casserole
directions: Layer asparagus, peas and mushrooms in a baking dish.
Mix mushroom soup and evaporated milk together and pour over layers. Sprinkle salt over top.
Break up toast and lay over the top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: k.f.c.  slaw
directions: Mix cabbage and carrots together. Combine sugar, salt, pepper, milk, mayonnaise, buttermilk, vinegar and lemon juice. Beat until smooth. Add to cabbage mixture; mix well. Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours before serving.

title: leigh's breadsticks
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll out on floured surface to size of jelly roll pan (large 1-inch deep cookie sheet).
Melt 1 cube margarine. Put half (1/4 cup) in cookie sheet.
Cut with roller pizza cutter into strips lengthwise (about 1-inch strips), then into thirds, about 6 inches long.
Brush with remaining margarine and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Let rise until puffy.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook all raw
vegetables until tender.
Add peas, corn, margarine, bacon drippings,
salt to taste and macaroni.
Turn on medium heat, stirring often to keep macaroni from sticking. Let set awhile before
serving
to make broth thick and tasty. This is good way
to
use leftover vegetables.
Also hamburger meat can be used
to
make
this
a wonderful wintertime meal. Serve with cornbread or crackers.

title: chocolate coconut chews
directions: Boil all ingredients (except marshmallows and cereal) for 2 or 3 minutes until forms a ball in cold water.
Add marshmallows and reheat.
Stir until blended.
Pour over cereal mixture.
Put into 10 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: thumb print cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, add vanilla, flour, salt and mix well. Shape into balls (about 1 tsp. to form balls).
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and indent center of balls with thumb.
Fill with preserve.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400° oven.

title: heavenly salad dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; add cream cheese and beat until melted.
Add pineapple.
Let set until congealed.
Whip jello, fold into Dream Whip.
Add nuts and marshmallows.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: chicken-cheese chowder
directions: Saute carrots and onions in butter in large saucepan until tender, but not brown.
Stir in flour and cook until smooth and bubbly.
Add milk and chicken broth.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Stir in chicken, wine, celery seed and Worcestershire.
Heat through.
Add cheese.
Stir until melted. Garnish with snipped chives.

title: georgia peach crumble(makes 8 to 10 servings)
directions: Drain
peaches, reserving syrup.
Add nectar to measure 2
1/2 cups total liquid.

title: quick trick fruit cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Combine date mix with hot water in large bowl; to this mix, add eggs, flour, baking powder, molasses and spices; blend well. Fold in S & W Glace cake mix, walnuts and raisins.
Mix thoroughly and pour into prepared pan.
Bake about 1 hour and 20 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool and wrap well.
Store in refrigerator.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: In medium saucepan, combine catsup and jelly.
Heat until jelly is completely dissolved.
Let cool.
Combine chuck, milk, oatmeal, eggs, salt and garlic powder.
Form small balls.
Pour catsup mixture over meatballs and bake at 350° for about an hour.
Check for doneness after an hour.
It may take longer depending on the size of the meatballs.

title: never fail drop cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients, then add flour.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chocolate chip peanut butter cups
directions: You will need 2 to 4 mini muffin pans for this recipe.

title: pepe's salsa
directions: *In winter, substitute 2 cans of whole tomatoes (chopped) and add 1 fresh tomato to keep chunky.

title: almost tacos dip
directions: In a large bowl mix cheese, sour cream, seasoning, tomatoes, lettuce and olives.
Place bowl on large tray and arrange chips on the tray around the bowl.
Garnish with onion.

title: ham and cheese casserole
directions: Grease 2-quart baking dish.
Cover bottom of greased baking dish with 4 bread slices.
Place 1 ham slice and 1 cheese slice over each bread slice.
Top each with bread slice.
Mix eggs, milk, mustard, salt and pepper in mixing bowl.
Pour over bread. Place in refrigerator for 4 hours.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: garlic cheese grits
directions: Cook grits in salted water. Once cooked, stir in milk and cook a few more minutes. Add butter, garlic, Velveeta cheese, cheddar cheese and Worcestershire sauce. Stir until butter and cheeses have melted. Place in a greased casserole dish and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15-20 minutes. Great for breakfast or supper! (If you like, omit garlic.)

title: wild rice dressing
directions: Toast and cube bread; it should be slightly moistened.
Brown sausage and drain and reserve grease.
Saute onions and celery. Cook wild rice as directed on box.
(All seeds will completely pop open.)
Combine all ingredients and bake, covered, 1/2 hour. Remove cover and bake until slightly brown (325°) for 15 to 20 minutes or more.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine cooked squash and all ingredients, except crackers and butter.
Put into buttered casserole dish.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Chop 1/3 stick butter on top of crackers.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cold pizza
directions: Layer in order of listings of ingredients.
Chill and eat on crackers or chips.

title: garlic cheddar biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees.
Lightly grease a cookie sheet. Mix together, bisquick, cheese, and water.
Drop in large spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake for 10-12 minutes.
Meanwhile, melt butter and combine with garlic and other seasonings.
Brush melted butter over hot biscuits.
Serve warm.

title: ruby's pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 300° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: taco tater skins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake potatoes at 375° for 1 hour or until tender.
When cool enough to handle, cut lengthwise into quarters.
Scoop out pulp, leaving 1/4-inch shell (save pulp for another use).

title: cranberry salad
directions: To boiling water add other ingredients.
Pour into mold and chill until firm.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Combine milk, sugar, biscuit mix, eggs, butter and vanilla in blender for 3 minutes.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie pan.
Let stand for 5 minutes, then sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: quick yeast rolls
directions: Add half flour and remaining ingredients in water-yeast mixture.
Beat well.
Add rest of flour and stir with wooden spoon until smooth.
Let rise 40 minutes.
Grease muffin pan.
Spoon into muffin pan.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 20 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Bake in 350° oven until center is set.
Garnish with whipped cream, if desired.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Barely cook broccoli and onion with salt and pepper in just enough water to cover.
Drain.
Arrange in bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch casserole pan.
In mixing bowl, beat egg; add soup, milk, lemon juice and mayonnaise; stir to blend; add to broccoli in pan, making sure to cover; mix cheese and stuffing making sure stuffing is covered by sauce.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Refrigerate with cover any leftover (there won't be, it's too good!).

title: welch cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add milk.
Sift dry ingredients together into creamed mixture.
Mix and add raisins. Chill dough, then roll it out and cut with round cookie cutter or a glass.
Cook in an electric frypan at slow temperatures until lightly browned.
Grease frypan lightly with Crisco each time.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Boil until threads run from spoon.
Add food coloring (if desired) and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour over approximately 4 quarts of popcorn.
Makes 12 to 15 popcorn balls.

title: poppy seed cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Blend in sifted flour.
Stir in poppy seed.
Chill dough for 1 hour.

title: cranberry christmas steam pudding
directions: Cut cranberries in half and mix with flour.
Add molasses and mix.
Dissolve soda in water, then add to mixture.
Add sugar. Beat eggs and add to mixture.
This will be thick and sticky. Butter a 2-pound coffee can.
Put mixture in can.
Place covered can on a rack in a large kettle with water in the bottom.
Cover kettle and steam for approximately 2 hours.

title: fat rolls
directions: Sift first 3 ingredients and put in bowl.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add oil.
Pour liquid over dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour out onto floured board.
Knead 20 to 30 times.
Add flour as needed.

title: "water whip" pie shell
directions: Add the boiling water and the milk to the shortening.
Whip with a fork until smooth and thick like whipped cream.
Sift in the flour and salt.
Stir quickly with round-the-bowl strokes into a dough that "cleans" the bowl.
Shape into a smooth, flat, round ball.
Roll between wax paper and fit into pie shell.
Fill and bake at 425° for about 45 minutes.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix all together.
Store in tight container.
For each cup of hot water add 1 1/2 to 2 tsp. of tea.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat cream cheese and marshmallow cream together until smooth. Store in refrigerator. Serve with any kind of fruit.

title: icing
directions: Mix together brown sugar, milk, coconut, pecans and oleo or butter.
Mix well and pour over the baked cake and brown under the broiler.

title: tortilla egg casserole
directions: Brown turkey sausage.
Heat oven to 350°.
Arrange tortillas to cover bottom and sides of greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with browned sausage and cheese.
Beat eggs slightly. Add milk and seasonings.
Mix well.
Pour over sausage and cheese. Bake 40 to 50 minutes, until knife comes out clean.
Serve salsa, sour cream and onion in side dishes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Shake quarters in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Drop into Bundt pan.
Mix brown sugar, margarine and pecans; pour over sugar and cinnamon quarters mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hot lime jello salad
directions: Mix jello with water and vinegar.
Let cool.
Spread vegetables over 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle with sugar and chopped chili.
Pour jello over salad after jello is cool. Refrigerate until set.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix flour, salt and cut in shortening until pieces are pea size.
Mix well with the water until dough comes together and can be shaped into a ball.
Roll out.
Pour filling (recipe follows) into pie shell. Cut little pieces of butter on top of the apples. Cover with top crust.
Place slits into the top crust.
Seal and flute.
Cover edge with 2 or 3 inches of foil to prevent excessive browning.
Remove foil for the last 15 minutes of baking. Bake at 450° for 40-50 minutes or until crust is brown and juices begin to bubble through the slits in the crust.

title: baseball stew
directions: Put meat in greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Add layer of onion, potatoes and carrots.
Salt and pepper.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and V-8 (shake).
Pour over vegetables.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 4 hours at 250° to 275°.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well; add coconut and pineapple and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake until center is firm at 350°, about 45 minutes.
It should be slightly brown on top.
Quick, easy and good!

title: orange jello
directions: Heat juice; add to Jell-O and gelatin.
Add buttermilk and chill until thickened.
Add fruits and chill.

title: baked vidalias
directions: Peel onions and scoop out a small hole in the top of each. Fill the cavity with a bouillon cube topped with a pat of butter, salt and pepper.
Wrap each onion in aluminum foil. Bake in a 350° oven about 45 minutes, or until tender or grill on hot coals for about 30 minutes, turning frequently. Yield: 6 servings.

title: sweet potato souffl
directions: Combine all ingredients (except topping) with electric mixer. Add the eggs, one at a time. Beat into mixture with electric mixer. (The mixture can be beaten by hand, but the souffl will not be as light.)

title: easy upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts and coconut on bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix according to directions.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Melt margarine and add to cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Beat well.
Pour this over cake mix batter.
Bake for 55 minutes at 350°.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (use 325° for glass dish).
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt butter.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter. Pour sweetened condensed milk over crumbs.
Top evenly with chocolate morsels, coconut and nuts.
Press down gently.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until lightly browned.
Cool thoroughly before cutting.

title: tom wayman's chili
directions: Brown meat in 1/2 cup butter.
Add liquid and remaining ingredients.
Cook, covered, for 1 hour and uncovered about 3 1/2 hours.
Very good!

title: no bake cookies
directions: Put raisins, dates and honey into a bowl.
Crush crackers with rolling pin on waxed paper.
Add crumbs to bowl, fruit and honey. Stir until dry enough to roll into balls.

title: crabmeat casserole(appetizer)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with crackers.

title: chocolate peanut crunch
directions: Melt chocolate chips.
Add peanut butter.
Stir until all melted (double boiler works best).
Cook until all dissolved. Remove from heat.
Put corn flakes in mixing bowl, then add melted chips and peanut butter mixture.
Mix carefully.
Refrigerate for a few minutes until cool.
Drop by tablespoons on cookie sheet or waxed paper.
Keep refrigerated.

title: pepsi roast
directions: Place roast in a roasting pan.
Pour other three ingredients over roast.
Cover.
Cook in a 350° oven for 2 hours or more, depending on size of roast.
Makes a delicious, very tender roast and terrific gravy.

title: breaded artichoke hearts
directions: Drain artichoke hearts and cut into halves.
Dip pieces into egg and coat in crumbs on all sides.
Place artichoke pieces on a nonstick cookie sheet and heat until broiler until brown on all sides, about 15 minutes.
Remove.
Season and let cool.
Serve.

title: chicken almond pie
directions: Combine 3/4 cup cheese and 1/2 cup almonds.
Set aside. Combine remaining ingredients, put into pie shell and top with set aside cheese and almonds.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in 400° oven.

title: biloxi cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese and dressing mix.
Form into a ball.
Roll in black pepper.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: icebox fruitcake
directions: Crumble crackers, mix with melted oleo, chopped fruit and pecans.
Mix all ingredients together.
Line graham cracker box with wax paper and pack entire mixture in box.
Seal securely. Store in refrigerator (the longer the better).
Drain cherries and discard juice.

title: hearty minestrone
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan over medium heat, heat oil.
Add potatoes, carrots, celery, onion, red bell pepper and garlic; cook, covered, about 10 minutes, until vegetables are almost tender, uncovering to stir occasionally.
Stir in chicken broth and bay leaf.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat to low; simmer, covered, about 10 minutes.
Add kidney beans, tomatoes, peas, grated Parmesan, vinegar, crushed red pepper and salt.
Cook about 5 minutes longer, until heated through and flavors are blended. Remove bay leaf before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: southern macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until almost done; drain.
To macaroni add milk, beaten eggs, cheese, butter, salt and pepper; stir well.
Pour mixture into greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle paprika on top. Bake at 350° uncovered for 1 hour or until done.

title: don't peek chicken
directions: Mix the rice with soups and 1/2 or more cans of water.
Pour into a buttered 15 x 11-inch baking dish.
Layer the carrots and chicken on top of rice mixture.
Sprinkle with dry soup mix.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown pork chops.
Then, where you have browned them, add the onions and garlic and brown.
Put all in large roaster and add tomato paste with 3 cans of water to each can of paste.
Add salt (a lot) and cook over medium to low heat 4 or more hours until thick.
Take out bones before pouring over cooked spaghetti. (Also great with chicken breast, cut in strips.)

title: easy trifle
directions: Cut or tear
the
cake	into
1-inch cubes.
Place in a large serving bowl (I
use a clear glass fruit bowl).
Mix the pudding according
to package directions. Add whipped topping; mix well. Pour this over the cake, tossing lightly.
Pour the pie filling (cherry
or
blueberry)
gently
over
the	above mixture.	Chill. Serves 8 to 10 generously.

title: country fried chicken
directions: Combine flour, garlic salt, pepper and paprika in plastic bag. Shake chicken pieces in the mixture.
Combine milk and egg.
Dip chicken pieces in milk mixture.
Shake pieces a second time in seasoned flour to coat evenly.
Pour oil in skillet 1/2 to 1-inch deep.
Heat to 365°.
Brown chicken on all sides.
Reduce heat to 275° and continue cooking until chicken is tender, about 30 to 40 minutes.
Do not cover.
Turn chicken several times during cooking.

title: tuna tetrazzini
directions: Cook onion in small amount of hot fat until tender, but not brown.
Add soup, milk and cheese; heat and stir.
Break tuna in chunks; add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese and paprika. Bake in a 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: grandma silvestris meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl (clean hands work best).
Roll and fry in oil of your choice (I usually use vegetable or olive oil).
Add a chopped clove of garlic to oil for extra flavor.
Drain on paper towels and add to your favorite sauce or eat 'em as is.

title: red cinnamon apple pie
directions: Peel and core apples.
Slice into bowl with sugar, flour, candies and salt; mix well.
Fill pie shell with mixture; dot with butter.
Put on top crust.
Slit for steam.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil for 7 minutes, beating and stirring constantly or until required stiffness results.
Now add the 1 teaspoon vanilla and ice cake immediately.
Makes enough to frost 2 layers.

title: lobster casserole
directions: Cook lobster (may use microwave).
Break cooked lobster into bite-size pieces.
Combine beaten egg, milk and melted butter; pour over soft bread crumbs.
Add lemon juice, onion, mustard and salt, mixing well.
Fold in lobster; spoon into buttered 1-quart baking dish; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° until top is well browned, about 20 minutes.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: hearty navy bean soup
directions: Rinse and sort beans.
Cover with cold water and soak overnight.
Drain beans and place in large soup kettle.
Add tomatoes with juice, onion, ham hock, broth, water, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until beans are tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Add more water, if necessary.

title: brownies
directions: Cream oleo, cream cheese and sugar.
Mix flour and cocoa.
Add eggs, then flour mixture, then add nuts and vanilla.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-Os in hot water.
Add cold water.
Add crushed pineapple, bananas and marshmallows.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and set in refrigerator.

title: goulash
directions: Brown hamburger over medium heat; add onion and reduce heat. Simmer until brown.
Add salt and pepper to taste, tomato soup, chili powder and paprika to taste.
Pour juice from beans into mixture and simmer for 1 hour.
Cook macaroni; drain.
Combine macaroni and beans with sauce and simmer another 1/2 hour. Sprinkle with cheese.
Stir and simmer a while longer.
Serves 4.

title: easy chicken casserole pan
directions: Mix stuffing according to instructions on package and set aside.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Line 1 (9 x 13-inch) pan with the chicken.
Pour soup mixture over the chicken.
Top with stuffing.
Cover with 2 cups chicken broth.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: crab meat with shrimp dip
directions: Crumble shrimp and crab with fingers.
Add lemon juice and pepper; mash well with cream cheese.
Place in baking dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: best pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, syrup, melted oleo and pecans.
Mix and pour into unbaked pie crust.
Heat oven to 400° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake 30 minutes.
I make 2 pies from this recipe.

title: orient chicken and broccoli
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium high heat in hot oil, cook chicken (1/2 at a time) until brown.
Add peppers and onion; cook 5 minutes or until vegetables are crispy tender.
Stir in soup, water and soy sauce,
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes or until vegetables are cooked.
Serve over rice.

title: unbelievable cookies
directions: Beat egg.
Add sugar, peanut butter and vanilla.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press out and bake at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes.

title: chutney
directions: Cut circles out of bread.
Put on slice of onion.
Mix 1/2 cheese and 1/2 mayonnaise mixture.
Spread on top.
Bake under broiler until brown and bubbly.

title: peanut butter and chocolate chip sandwiches
directions: Lay the slices of bread on the table.
Take a knife and spread the peanut butter on both sides.
Then stick the chocolate chips in the peanut butter.
Put the 2 slices of bread together and enjoy.

title: dolores' peanut brittle
directions: In a 2 quart measuring cup or casserole dish mix sugar and corn syrup.
Microwave, uncovered on High for 4 minutes, stirring at half time.
Mix in the peanuts and butter and microwave, uncovered on High for 3 1/2 to 4 minutes, until pale
brown. Quickly stir in the vanilla and baking soda.
Pour onto a buttered baking sheet and spread as thin as possible with a buttered spatula.
For extra thin brittle, cook 4 to 5 minutes.
When cold, crack into pieces.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Note:
Some like to add 2 tablespoons melted butter to the batter.

title: individual ham loaves
directions: Use 1/2 or 3/4 cup for each loaf.
One-half makes about 20. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: quick summer salad
directions: Cook broccoli and cauliflower until tender; drain and cool. Add red wine vinegar to cover.
Mix together and chill overnight. Makes up to 8 servings.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add oil and milk or water to make soft dough.
Knead like biscuit dough.
Roll out or cut and put in greased pan and put damp towel over the pan.
Let stand in a warm place to rise, about double in size.
Bake like regular biscuits.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix in 1/2 cup sugar and pretzels.
Press into 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes; cool.

title: sour sauce
directions: Combine in saucepan the onions, vinegar and water.
Cook 10 minutes.
Blend together butter, egg yolks, flour and salt.
Pour hot liquid over butter mixture.
Blend thoroughly.
Simmer 1 minute to make mixture smooth.

title: sherbet and ginger ale punch
directions: Let sherbet sit in punch bowl until soft,
chill ginger ale and pour over sherbet right before serving.
Makes a beautiful punch for a bridal or baby tea.

title: broccoli, ham and rice casserole
directions: Cook onion and broccoli in butter until done.
Add soup, rice, ham and melted cheese.
Cook in oven for 20 minutes or until it bubbles.
Be careful not to cook too long.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour into a greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° until done.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brush bottom and sides of crust evenly with egg yolk.
Bake on baking sheet until lightly brown, about 5 minutes.
Remove crust from oven.
Combine sliced apples, 1/2 cup sugar, 1/4 cup brown sugar, cinnamon, salt, nutmeg and flour.
Mix remaining flour, sugar, brown sugar and butter with fork until crumbly.
Sprinkle topping mixture evenly over apples.
Bake on baking sheet until topping is golden and filling is bubbling, about 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool thoroughly on wire rack (at least 4 hours).
Serve at room temperature.
Serves 8.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Chop green pepper, celery and onion very fine.
Put into beef and brown.
Add 2 quarts water and spices.
Bring to boil and simmer 2 hours.

title: caramel oatmeal bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Add margarine;
mix until crumbly. Reserve 1 cup of topping;
press remaining mixture onto bottom of prepared pan.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Top with nuts and chocolate chips.

title: chille rellenos(mexican stuffed peppers)
directions: Cook the peppers on a hot pan until the skin is burnt all the way around them (yes, let the skin burn). Place peppers in a plastic bag and let them sweat. After they have set for a while take them out and the skin should come right off. Cut a slit length-wise in the peppers and fill with mixture of cheese, onion and tomato. Hold the peppers together with toothpicks. After peppers have been stuffed, roll them in flour and then dip them into beaten eggs and fry on medium heat until the egg is done. Goes great with Spanish rice.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Precook broccoli until tender. Combine broth, salt, pepper, garlic salt and basil.
Add onions, broccoli, half and half and milk.
Add flour or cornstarch to thicken.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add	syrup
and
stir until mixed well.
Add eggs and mix
well.
Add
margarine
(melted).
Add
flour and mix. Add lemon
juice; mix.
Add vanilla flavor.
Add pecans. Pour into unbaked pie
shell	and
bake 10 minutes at 450° and cut to 350° for 45 minutes.

title: one dish ham bake
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix broccoli, soups, 1 cup milk, ham and onion powder.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix Bisquick and milk.
Pour over soup mixture.
Bake 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: aunt mary's cake
directions: Cream butter well; add sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Alternate milk with flour sifted with baking powder.
Add vanilla, then fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes in 350° oven. Ice with vanilla or orange icing.

title: party fruit punch
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients, stirring well; chill.

title: apple pie
directions: In large bowl combine apple slices, sugar, tapioca, cinnamon, and nutmeg.
Pour mixture into unbaked pie shell and top with the other shell. Cut small slits in top shell and bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Marinate chicken and onion in marinade of soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce, oil and cumin for 1 hour.
Grill over charcoal fire for about 4 minutes on each side.
(Place onion to outside as they will not need as much cooking time.)
Brush with marinade before and after turning.
Cut chicken into thin strips and separate onion into rings.
Fold into warm tortillas and top with guacamole, sour cream, grated Cheddar cheese and salsa.

title: oatmeal sugar crisp cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, brown sugar and white sugar. Add the eggs and vanilla. Sift together the flour, soda and salt and add to mixture. Combine well and add oats.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: old fashioned candied yams
directions: Combine all ingredients in an iron skillet. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, about 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Remove the cover, increase the temperature to medium and cook until the syrup has thickened, possible another 15-20 minutes.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes conventionally or in microwave.
Cut lengthwise in halves; scoop out into large bowl and crush.
Add margarine, salt to taste, onion and Parmesan cheese, reserving a small amount.
Mix well.
Stuff potato shells (skins) and sprinkle reserved Parmesan cheese on tops.
Place under broiler until golden brown.

title: ham and asparagus roll-ups
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over medium heat.
Stir in flour. Gradually add milk while stirring constantly. Add salt and pepper if desired.
When sauce is thickened, stir in cheese and blend well.
Set aside.
Roll 4 spears of asparagus up in each slice of ham with seam side down.
Place rolls close together in oblong baking dish.
Pour cheese sauce over all and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until sauce is lightly browned.
Serves 6.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli spears in a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Place chicken pieces over broccoli.
Place 1/8-inch slices of cheese over entire pan.

title: fudgy brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat chocolate and margarine in a 2-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly, until melted.
Remove from heat.
(Can melt chocolate in microwave according to directions on package, then add margarine and microwave until margarine is melted).
Add eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour and salt.
Spread in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Watch carefully, so you do not overbake!!

title: oven fried catfish
directions: In a shallow bowl, beat egg and milk together. In another shallow bowl, combine corn meal and other dry ingredients. Dip each fillet in egg mixture and coat thoroughly in the meal mixture. Spray a shallow pan with cooking spray and add the olive oil making sure bottom of pan is coated. Place fish in a single layer in the pan. Bake at 500° about 12 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork.

title: rolls
directions: Mix together and put in small muffin pan for luncheon.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Also can be put in large muffin pan.

title: camper's stroganoff
directions: Saute hamburger and onions until meat loses red color. Add flour and seasonings. Cook 2 to 3 minutes. Add soup and mushrooms. Simmer 10 minutes. Add sour cream. Heat and serve on noodles.

title: eat - more dinner
directions: Brown meat, pepper and onion in skillet.
Cook spaghetti, drain and mix with browned ingredients.
Put all in baking dish, salt to taste and bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Lightly grease a large baking sheet. Stir together flour, salt, soda and baking powder in medium bowl.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook, drain, but do not rinse, vermicelli.
Pour Italian dressing over warm spaghetti.
Cool.
Mix well and refrigerate overnight.
Add vegetables and Salad Supreme.
Mix well.
Chill and serve.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill in a bowl.
Roll in chopped nuts. Chill and serve with crackers.

title: microwave twice-baked potatoes
directions: Prick potato skins with a fork.
Microwave on High for 8 minutes; turn potatoes over.
Microwave on High for 8 minutes longer.
Slice hot potatoes lengthwise; scoop out insides, saving shells.
Whip potatoes, margarine, cheese, onion, salt and pepper together.
Blend in milk gradually.
Spoon potato mixture into shells.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes longer.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: aunt jackie's cauliflower salad
directions: Chop or break cauliflower & broccoli into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients well and garnish with fresh mushrooms.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Put half ripe bananas in skillet.
Add honey and brown sugar (amounts vary according to desired sweeteness).
Add approximately 1/2 cup rum.
May add raisins, if desired.
Cook on low heat. Serve over French vanilla cake or ice cream.

title: sweet potato or pumpkin pie
directions: Beat egg.
Melt butter.
Add all remaining ingredients to egg and butter.
Mix well.
Pour into raw pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for additional 30 minutes.

title: divinity
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water.
Cook slowly until 1/3 teaspoon forms a hard ball when dropped in cold water.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into syrup mixture.
Gently fold in vanilla and pecans.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper; allow to harden before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix melted butter and stuffing.
Put a layer of stuffing, then chicken, then a layer of celery soup and one can of broth, mixed. Redo the layers, ending up with a layer of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: millie's coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on package.
Mix together first 3 ingredients; set aside 1 cup mixture.
Divide the two cake layers.
Between the 3 layers (the first layer is placed on plate), place the mixture of coconut, sour cream and sugar.
Mix Cool Whip with the reserved 1 cup of mixture.
Frost top and sides of cake. Cover and refrigerate for 3 days.
May be frozen.
Quick, good and easy to do ahead.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: old-fashioned gingerbread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten egg, molasses and then dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Add hot water last and beat until smooth.
The batter is soft.
Bake in greased shallow pan for 35 minutes in moderate oven (325°).
Makes 15 generous portions.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Add flour and salt; stir well.
Stir in potato chips and pecans.
Drop from a spoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
With spoon dipped in water, flatten each cookie.
Bake for 15 minutes at 325°.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: sugar cream pie(microwave)
directions: Melt margarine in microwave.
Add flour and stir to get lumps out.
Add sugar and milk and microwave until thick, approximately 7 to 9 minutes.
Stir halfway through this time period and again at the end of time.
Pour into a cooled shell and sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: dirty rice
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish, then add ingredients in order as directed.
Do not mix.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients into a casserole dish.
Mix cheese, butter, Cheez-Its and put on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: bleu cheese vinaigrette
directions: Mix vinegar and mustard in a small bowl.
Whisk in both oils in a thin stream. Add cheese, shallots and pepper.
Let stand at least 30 minutes to blend flavors.
(Can be prepared 1 day ahead and refrigerated.)

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Stir together and
drop in blobs on cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375° to 400°.

title: low-fat lasagna florentine
directions: Combine spaghetti sauce and tomatoes with their liquid and water in bowl.
Stir to blend and break up tomatoes.
Set aside.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Cream oleo, sugar, eggs and salt.
Add pineapple and mix.
Add bread.
Bake in an ungreased 1-quart dessert dish at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: fresh creamed corn
directions: In a saucepan, combine corn, margarine, sugar and salt.
In a cup, blend flour and milk to form a thin paste.
Pour into corn. Cook on medium heat for 10 minutes after getting hot.
Stir often to prevent sticking.

title: casey and rebecca brown's scalloped potatoes
directions: Layer potatoes, onion, pimentos and cheese in a greased baking dish.
Season each layer with salt and pepper.
Blend soup and milk; pour over potatoes.
Bake at 300° for two hours.

title: german delight
directions: Mix sauerkraut with applesauce.
Place in bottom of casserole dish.
Sprinkle the instant mashed potatoes on top of that. Sprinkle top with caraway seed.
Place ribs on top.
Bake at 350° uncovered for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon until crispy; add bacon grease, mustard, catsup, syrup and onion.
Mix well.
Crumble bacon and add.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: fresh pepper relish
directions: Coat a nonaluminum saucepan with cooking spray.
Place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add carrot and next 5 ingredients; saute until crisp-tender.
Stir in vinegar, sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and let simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Let cool to room temperature, cover and chill thoroughly.
Serve with pork or poultry.
Yields 2 cups (11 calories and 8% fat per tablespoon).
Protein 0.2, fat 0.1 (saturated fat 0), carbohydrate 2.8, fiber 0.3, cholesterol 0, sodium 20.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Mix together.
Store in airtight container.
Put 2 teaspoons of mixture to 1 cup of boiling water per individual.

title: key lime cake
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake in tube pan for 45 minutes at 350° until straw comes out clean.

title: dill pickles
directions: You will need 4 (1-quart) jars.

title: bonnie's crab dip
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and spread on a plate; mix next 4 ingredients and spread over cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with 1 pound of lump crabmeat.
Serve with crackers.

title: halloween ghoul-ade
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar and water.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Serve over ice if you want.

title: thunder cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add vanilla and cream together.
Add egg yolks.
Add water.
Add tomatoes.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into mixture.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Cream the Crisco, sugar, soda and buttermilk.
Beat for 3 to 4 minutes.
Put in one egg at a time with some flour, until all eggs are used.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan and bake for 1 hour at 350° or until done.

title: buckeyes
directions: Melt paraffin and chocolate chips in double boiler.
Mix melted margarine, peanut butter and sugar.
Form this into walnut size balls.
Stick toothpick in balls and dip in chocolate.
Stick on wax paper to dry.

title: potato salmon chowder
directions: Cook potatoes and carrots in salted water until tender.
Add frozen peas.
Bring to boil and cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat, cut do not drain.
Cook onion in butter until lightly browned. Add flour and stir until smooth.
Cook 1 minute.
Add half the milk, stirring constantly.
Cook over low heat until sauce boils and thickens.
Flake salmon.
Add with the liquid to the vegetables.
Add hot sauce, celery and Worcestershire sauce and rest of milk to vegetables and salmon.
Serve hot.

title: pesto sauce
directions: Place all ingredients in blender for a few minutes.
Can be stored in jar in refrigerator.
Cover with oil.
Makes enough sauce for about 2 pounds pasta.

title: chicken acapulco
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Debone and chop chicken into bite-size pieces.

title: one step lasagne
directions: Use a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Add 1/2 cup water and cooked ground beef to spaghetti sauce.
Cover bottom of pan with 1 1/2 cups sauce.
Cover with uncooked noodles, then 1/2 the Ricotta cheese.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons Parmesan and Mozzarella cheese. Repeat layers until all used.
Top with sauce; sprinkle Parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil and place on jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until knife inserted in center goes through noodles easily.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: In medium saucepan, combine sugar, flour and salt.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thick.
Beat eggs slightly; add to mixture.
Bring to gentle boil.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, margarine and coconut.
Pour filling into pie shell.
Let cool.
Spread Cool Whip on cool filling; sprinkle 1/2 cup coconut on top.
Keep pie chilled.

title: norwegian cole slaw
directions: Combine cabbage and salt.
Let stand for 2 hours.
Boil together sugar and vinegar.
Take off stove and add mustard seed, celery seed, celery, green pepper and onion.
Pour cooled vinegar syrup over cabbage and let stand in refrigerator before serving.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream shortening
and
sugar.
Dissolve soda in coffee. Add soda-coffee mixture and the rest of the ingredients to the creamed shortening.
Bake in
a
large loaf or tube pan for 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: steak dijon
directions: Brown steak in skillet in butter until done, turning once. Remove.
Keep warm.
Reduce heat.
Add gravy, half and half and mustard.
Heat, stirring until bubbly. Add meat to sauce. Sprinkle with parsley.
Cover.
Simmer on low for 10 minutes. Serves 4.

title: mama's pineapple pie(microwave)
directions: Beat egg yolks; mix together all ingredients.
Cook on High 3 minutes (in microwave); stir.
Cook 1 minute; stir.
Cook 1 minute; stir until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix butter and Ritz crackers; pour half of mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Saute celery and onion in skillet; put in larger mixing bowl.
Stir in Veg-All vegetables, mayonnaise and Velveeta. Pour over crackers.
Top with half of crackers.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: no-weep perfect meringue(for cream pies)
directions: Put egg whites and cream of tartar in small size mixer bowl. Combine white sugar, cornstarch and salt; mix well.
Add water and put in microwave bowl.
Microwave on High until mixture becomes clear, then add enough mini marshmallows just to cover the mix. Cook just long enough to let the marshmallows puff up; remove and stir the mixture well.
It will be hot.
Beat egg whites until very foamy, not dry, and add the cooked mixture, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating on high power.
Add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla last.
Beat 2 minutes longer.
Spread over pie filling and brown at 400° for 5 to 6 minutes or until it browns sufficiently to your liking.

title: shrimp dip 'n bread
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Using Hawaiian or sourdough bread, cut out middle top portion of bread in a cone shape.
Put dip in cut out portion of bread.
Break off pieces of bread and dip into shrimp mixture.

title: seafoam candy
directions: Boil
the brown sugar and water for 2 1/2 minutes.
Pour over the egg whites and beat until it creams.

title: chicken breasts supreme
directions: Combine sour cream, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, celery salt, paprika, salt and pepper.
Add chicken; coat well.
Let stand covered overnight.
Remove next day; roll in bread crumbs, coating evenly.
Arrange in pan.
Melt butter and shortening together; pour half over chicken.
Bake uncovered for 45 minutes at 350°.
Pour remaining butter-shortening mixture over chicken and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer until tender or browned.

title: monkey bread
directions: In a plastic bag mix sugars.
Shake several quarters in sugar mixture.
Place in a Bundt pan.
Raisins may be added after each layer.
Melt oleo and pour a little over each layer of biscuits. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let stand in pan for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove and you may glaze.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter and cocoa together; cool slightly. Beat eggs until foamy. Gradually add sugar, beating after each addition. Add chocolate mixture and blend. Stir in flour and nuts. Add vanilla. Spread batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: corn muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl; pour into muffin pans. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, onion, celery, salt and pepper; heat water and margarine together until melted and add to the first mixture. Line large casserole dish with half of stuffing mix. Pour in chicken mixture and spread evenly. Beat eggs and milk together; pour over chicken mixture. Place in refrigerator overnight. Before baking, spread 1 can mushroom soup and top with remaining stuffing mix. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, uncovered. Serves 8.

title: cheese krisp
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet; flatten with fork.
Bake at 350°
for 25 to 30 minutes. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In an ovenproof skillet, lightly brown pork chops in oil over medium heat.
Layer sauerkraut and pie filling over pork chops.
Place pepper rings over pie filling.

title: tom's tamale casserole
directions: Brown ground beef (pour off all fat).
Blend in 2-quart casserole the beef, chili powder, garlic powder, tomato paste, tomatoes and green chilies, corn, water and jalapenos.
Cover with lid and microwave on High for 8 minutes or until steaming hot.
In a mixing bowl, beat milk and egg, then stir in the muffin mix. Press the cubes of cheese into the surface of the meat mixture and spoon on the muffin batter to cover the top.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until the corn bread tests done.

title: chocolate delite
directions: Mix together; press in bottom of 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 250°.
Cool.

title: pickled zucchini
directions: Scrub zucchini well; cut off both ends and slice thinly.
Do not pare off outer green.
Cover with cold water and salt.
Soak for 1 hour.
Mix all other ingredients; bring to a boil.
Add drained zucchini.
Turn off flame/burner; let stand 1 hour longer. Bring to a boil; cook for 3 minutes.
Refrigerate in covered container.
Serve as you would pickles.

title: blueberry yum yum
directions: Mix graham crackers and sugar together and pour just enough melted butter to hold it together when patted in the bottom of dish.
Spread blueberry pie filling over graham cracker crust.
Mix softened cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar together and spread over pie filling.
Chill and serve.

title: holiday yams
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch; blend well.
Stir in orange juice and salt; simmer over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Place yams in lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tortilla soup
directions: In a large
pot,
saute
onion in oil, then add rest of the ingredients,
except
tortillas
and
cheese.
Bring
to a boil; lower heat
and simmer 1 hour.
Remove from heat and add tortillas and cheese.
Serve in 5 minutes.

title: double boiler frosting(7 minute)
directions: Combine egg whites, sugar, cream of tartar and water in the top of double boiler.
Place over boiling water and beat with rotary beater until mixture holds its shape.
Fold in vanilla. Beat until cool, then spread.

title: susan's slaw(serves 8)
directions: *Prepare the mayonnaise with sugar and vinegar.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Mix gelatin, tapioca and pudding mix with water and bring to a boil until dissolved. Cool completely. Fold
in pineapple and whipped topping. Chill and serve.

title: diabetic date nut loaf
directions: Cream margarine and add sweetener, egg and vanilla.
Beat together.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients and applesauce gradually to margarine mixture.
Beat at medium speed 3 to 4 minutes.
Fold in dates and nuts.
Pour in 1 1/2 pound pan. Bake one hour at 350°.

title: buttermilk-herb dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a jar; cover tightly and shake to blend.
Chill overnight or for several hours.
Shake well before serving.
Can be stored in refrigerator, tightly covered, for about one week.
This is a very thin dressing; may add mayonnaise or yogurt for a thicker consistency.
Yield:
1 cup.
Approximate calories/serving:
1 tablespoon = 5.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook 2 cups of noodles (macaroni pasta).
Mix in your fresh vegetables.
Pour Hidden Valley Ranch dressing over all.
Chill. Very good when cold.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, except nuts.
Mix until well blended. Add nuts.
Serve with slices of apples.

title: jello mold
directions: Mix first box of jello according to directions.
Refrigerate until set in a ring mold.
When jello is set, blend cottage cheese and cream cheese in a blender until smooth.
