Pour over jello layer. Mix remaining jello according to directions.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Pour over cheese layer and chill well before unmolding.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add crabmeat.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot with crackers, chips or vegetables.

title: zeppelies
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and cheese, then combine remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon into hot oil.
Roll in powdered sugar or honey.

title: ham loaf
directions: Combine meat, crumbs, pepper, eggs and milk.
Mix thoroughly. Place in loaf pan.

title: lemon pepper chicken
directions: Place chicken in greased baking dish.
Spread margarine, soy sauce and lemon pepper on each piece of chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 4 to 6.

title: shirley's waffles
directions: Measure dry ingredients into bowl.
Blend.
Combine egg yolks and milk.
Stir into dry ingredients.
Stir in egg whites.
Do not overmix.
Pour 2/3 cup batter on preheated grill and cook until golden brown.

title: christmas morning rolls
directions: Place rolls in greased tube pan.
Sprinkle dry pudding over rolls.
Cook butter, brown sugar and cinnamon until it bubbles and sugar dissolves.
Pour over rolls.
Cover tightly with foil and let sit on counter overnight, or 6 - 8 hours.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer for 10 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 cups sauce.
Used as a marinade for chicken or any meat which is cooked outdoors.

title: mother's easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt oleo
in 9 x 13-inch pan.	Mix flour, milk, sugar, vanilla, salt
and cinnamon.
Pour mixture in pan over butter. Pour sliced
peaches,
with juice, on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° until	golden	brown.	Recipe	can be changed by omitting cinnamon and using sweetened cherries or blackberries.

title: magic pumpkin pie
directions: In large size mixing bowl, blend together all ingredients. Turn mixture into pie shell.
Bake at 375° until knife inserted near the center comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool.
This recipe is simple to make.
Made with 1 egg, 1 bowl and no sugar.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Toast pecans in microwave for 2 minutes. Stir, then microwave another 2 minutes; stir and microwave another minute. Sift together sugar and flour. Add remaining ingredients. Bring to soft-ball stage boil. Remove from heat. Add pecans and stir. If not hard enough, add 1/4 cup milk and cook again. Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: confetti macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Combine macaroni, meat, cheese, green pepper and onion.
Stir and chill.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in pie shells of your choice.
Chill well.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix ingredients and spread in a pretty pie plate or quiche plate.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: two layered lunch salad
directions: Mix first four ingredients with mayonnaise.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Cool.
Add to tuna mixture and spread in 8 x 8 x 2 pyrex dish.
Refrigerate.

title: funnel cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, milk and eggs together.
Heat oil on medium to high heat.
Pour mixture into hot oil.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on cakes when done.

title: refrigerator biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients; cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk and yeast that has been dissolved in hot water.
Put in oiled bowl in refrigerator.
You don't have to wait for rising.
Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
It is better the second day.
The dough will keep a week in the refrigerator.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In a medium bowl, combine flour and sugar; cut in butter until crumbly (easily done in a food processor).
Press firmly in ungreased 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: pee wee cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well.
Then add baking soda, salt, flour, oatmeal, cornflakes, chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop small spoonfuls of dough on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: smothered pork chops
directions: Place chops in shallow baking dish.
Combine jelly, soy sauce, catsup and garlic.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until tender.
Remove chops to warm platter.

title: yeast rolls
directions: In measuring cup, mix first 4 ingredients.
Let set 20 minutes. In large mixing bowl, mix next 3 ingredients.
Mix all together, then add flour.
Cover and refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.
Pinch out for rolls.
Do not knead.
Cook at 360° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Sift last 4 ingredients together.
Cream together margarine, sugar and eggs (add 1 at a time).
Beat well until fluffy.
Add sifted ingredients alternately with the sour cream to the egg mixture.
Add vanilla.
Drop by spoonful; sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: shrimp fettuccine
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions. Meanwhile in a non-stick skillet, saute onion, mushrooms, peppers and garlic in oil until tender. In a small bowl combine flour and milk until smooth. Add to vegetable mixture. Stir in seasonings. Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened. Reduce heat; add shrimp and basil. Simmer uncovered for 3 minutes or until shrimp turn pink. Drain pasta; place in large bowl. Add shrimp mixture and toss to coat.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon, reserve bacon grease.
Brown chopped onion in bacon grease.
In large sauce pan, stir pork-n-beans, brown sugar, molasses, onion, crumbled bacon, ketchup, mustard over medium heat until bubbly.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: celery casserole
directions: Microwave Recipe:
Cook on High.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in a microwave-safe 2-quart casserole dish.
Add celery to butter; cover and cook for 9 minutes.
In a medium size mixing bowl, combine the undiluted soup and water chestnuts.
Gently stir in the cooked celery and butter.

title: copper penny carrots
directions: Combine carrots, onion and green pepper.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over vegetables.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Can be used as a hot vegetable or a cold salad.

title: lemon mousse salad
directions: Mix together jello, sugar and salt.
(I cut the sugar to 1/4 cup.)
Add boiling water; stir until dissolved.
Stir in
frozen lemonade concentrate.
Chill until mixture is jelly like.
Fold in whipping cream (whipped) into lemon mixture.
Pour into ring mold.
When unmolded, fill center with fresh fruit.

title: selby's hot sweet mustard
directions: Mix dry mustard and vinegar together and let stand overnight. Beat in eggs, sugar and salt and cook in double boiler until thick.
Cool.
Beat in mayonnaise and refrigerate.
This makes about 1 quart and keeps well.

title: holden's irish-italian spaghetti
directions: Brown ground meat and onion.
Salt and pepper and add chili powder.
Add soup and 3/4 can of water.
Pour into prepared noodles and stir.

title: jolly good nut mix
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Line jellyroll pan with parchment paper.
Combine sugar, Cajun seasoning, salt and pepper.
In large bowl, beat egg whites until frothy.
Add nuts; stir until coated. Sprinkle with sugar mixture.
Toss.
Using slotted spoon, transfer nut mixture to pan; spread in single layer.
Bake 30 minutes, stirring occasionally until toasted.
Cool completely.
If necessary, break nut mixture into pieces.
Toss with candies.

title: cheese salad
directions: Stir together pineapple and sugar.
Boil for 5 minutes. Dissolve gelatin in 1/3 cup of cold water.
Add gelatin to pineapple.
Add 1 teaspoon vinegar.
Grate 1 cup Cheddar cheese. Beat 1/2 pint whipping cream.
Fold in cheese and whipping cream. Chill.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar and butter in a saucepan and heat until butter melts. Then let boil for 1 minute. Turn off stove and add other ingredients. Mix well and spread in buttered pan or drop on waxed paper and let cool.

title: mezetti
directions: Heat shortening in skillet on medium heat. Add meat, pepper and onions.
Cook until slightly brown. Add chili powder and sprinkle (dry) noodles on top.
Mix water and soups.
Add to skillet. Cover and bring to steaming. Turn to low and cook 25 minutes. Sprinkle cheese on top and cook 5 more minutes.

title: strawberry heaven
directions: Place bottom cake layer on serving platter.
In mixing bowl, stir crushed strawberries and milk into 1 cup cool whip.
Spread half of strawberry mixture onto cake layer.
Top with second cake layer.
Frost the top and sides with remaining cool whip. Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.
Serves 12.

title: pluckin' bread
directions: Melt margarine.
Quarter biscuits.
Add sugar and cinnamon to margarine.
Dredge biscuit pieces in margarine and sugar mixture. Put a layer of biscuits into tube pan.
Sprinkle 1/3 of nuts and raisins over biscuits.
Repeat layering.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: no knead rolls
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Do not knead.
Let rise once until double in bulk.
Form into rolls or refrigerate until ready to make into rolls.
Let rise and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: peach kuchen
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut margarine into dry cake mix until crumbly.
Mix in coconut.
Pat mixture lightly into ungreased oblong pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch, building up slight edges.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Arrange peaches on warm crust.
Mix sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle on peaches.
Blend sour cream and egg yolks; drizzle over peaches.
(Topping will not completely cover peaches.)
Bake 25 minutes or until edges are light brown.
Do not overbake.
Serve warm.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: bean and bacon bake
directions: Remove bacon from skillet and all but 1 tablespoon of the drippings.
Add ground beef to skillet (cook until no longer pink).
Add onions (cooked until tender).
To the mixture, add the beans, mustard, sugar, catsup and Worcestershire.
Mix well. Place in a casserole and heat in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add round steak that has been cut in bite size pieces.
Cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and cook for a few minutes to blend flavors.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Beat the eggs; add melted butter, sugar, salt and milk to yeast mixture.
Mix in flour and let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down and roll in shapes as desired.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: ma's stick to your ribs
directions: Brown the ground beef.
Add the pork and beans and tomato soup.
Heat until hot.

title: diet chocolate mousse
directions: Mix Jell-O instant pudding mix with 3 cups of milk.
Add cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: sausage in sauce
directions: Melt jelly into ketchup.
Add hot dogs and simmer for about 20 minutes.
Let cool and put in refrigerator overnight so that all the flavors have a chance to blend together.
Heat before serving.
Great for appetizer or parties.

title: salmon pie
directions: Drain salmon and reserve juice; add enough milk to make 1 cup. Flake salmon and add all other ingredients.
Bake in pie plate 45 minutes at 375°.

title: rainbow fluffy-wiches
directions: Prepare whipped topping mix as directed on package.
Divide into 4 parts, 1/2 cup each.
Leave one part plain.
Add peppermint extract and red food coloring to one part, almond extract and green food coloring to another part and lemon extract and yellow food coloring to the last.
Divide toppings among 12 of the wafers; spread evenly and top with remaining wafers.
Freeze about 3 hours.
Wrap and store in freezer.
Serve as a frozen sandwich or as a dessert topped with chocolate sauce, if desired.
Makes 12 sandwiches.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large mixer bowl, cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, beating until smooth.
Combine dry ingredients; gradually add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in mince meat.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto greased baking sheets.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes about 6 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: ham roll-ups (appetizer)
directions: Spread ham slices with cream cheese.
Place pickle spear on ham slice.
Roll lengthwise.
Cut into bite size pieces and secure with toothpicks.

title: poor man's reuben burgers
directions: Brown ground beef; drain grease.
Add onion and garlic.
Add sauerkraut, caraway seed and salad dressing.
Mix well.
Add cheese.
Spread on pumpernickel bread slice and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: steak au poivre
directions: In a heavy duty plastic bag or 2 sheets of waxed paper, crush all peppercorns and fennel seeds coarsely, using the bottom of a heavy skillet, or rolling pin.
Pat steaks dry and coat both sides with peppercorn mixture.

title: cheryl's calico beans
directions: In a crock-pot, place the hamburger, bacon and ham.
Add (liquid and all), lima beans, pork and beans and red kidney beans. Mix together, then add the sugars, catsup, vinegar and mustard. Cook on low all day.

title: potatoes
directions: Do not peel potatoes, only scrub.
Put in a plastic bag.
Add oil.
Add dry onion soup.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan which had been covered with foil on bottom.
Bake at 450° for 40 minutes.

title: barbecued steak
directions: Combine all ingredients except steak in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil and simmer about 5 minutes.
Pound round steak to break connective tissue.
Cut into serving size portions.
Place pieces in large roasting pan.
Pour hot sauce over meat and bake, covered, at 325° for about 2 hours.

title: chicken nachos
directions: Saute chicken with cumin until cooked through.
Lay nacho chips on a cookie sheet.
Pour taco sauce (not salsa) over the chips.
Put cut up, cooked chicken over the top of the chips and sauce.
Slice black and green olives and put over the top of the chips, sauce and chicken.
Spread the shredded Cheddar cheese over the top of the chips and other ingredients.
Bake in oven at 400° until cheese is melted.
Serve with sour cream.

title: impossible pie
directions: Butter 9-inch pie plate.
Put in blender or mixer all of the ingredients and blend until smooth.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: cherry pie salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk; add cherry pie filling, pineapple and nuts.
Mix well.
Let set overnight in serving dish in refrigerator.

title: pear honey
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook in kettle, stirring occasionally about 15 minutes or until spreading consistency.
Pour into sterilized 1/2 pint jars within 1/2-inch of top.
Prepare lids by following directions on box.
Screw band down firmly tight and process in boiling waterbath 5 minutes.
Yield:
5 half pints.

title: bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease or paper line twelve 2 1/2-inch muffin cups.
In a medium bowl combine eggs, milk, oil and cereal. In a large bowl combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add cereal mixtures to flour mixture, stirring just until moistened. Divide evenly among muffin cups.
Bake 20 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef, peppers and onions.
Drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer at least 1 hour.
The sauce can be frozen.

title: quick lye soap
directions: Dissolve lye
and
warm
water	together in enamel pan. Let cool.
Add	ammonia,
Borax
and grease.
Stir until thick with wooden spoon.
When
nearly cold, cut into blocks or pour into individual	molds.	Store
in
cardboard
box
with cloth cover for 3 or 4 days before using.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Combine
all the ingredients, except cracker crumbs and place in	casserole.
Cover with cracker crumbs.	Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: beef casserole
directions: Mix all these together.
Leave enough cheese for the top. Crumble soda crackers over the top.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and bake for a few minutes.

title: california chicken
directions: Combine cranberry sauce, soup mix and dressing. In a 3 quart baking dish, marinate chicken in the mixture for 2 to 3 hours. Turn chicken once while marinating. Keep chicken in mixture and bake at 350 degrees for 1 to 1 1/2 hours uncovered. Turn once while baking. Serve with rice or noodles

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add the other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar in large bowl.
In saucepan, add margarine, cocoa, water and Crisco.
Bring to a boil; add to flour and sugar mixture.
Add buttermilk, soda, vanilla and eggs. Bake in large broiler pan @ 350° for 25-30 minutes.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine 1 cup sugar, cornstarch, salt and milk in a double boiler.
Cook over boiling water until thickened, stirring constantly.
Stir a small amount of hot mixture into beaten egg yolks.
Stir egg yolks into hot mixture.
Cook for 4 minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, coconut and coconut flavoring.
Pour into pie shell.

title: mexican chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender; remove from water (save water).
Cook spaghetti in chicken water (may have to add more water).
Drain spaghetti; put back in pan.
Dice Velveeta.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and diced chicken; cook until cheese melts, stirring constantly.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake at 375° until bubbly.

title: chips meat loaf
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients lightly, but thoroughly.
Shape in loaf in baking pan; pour sauce over top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: blueberry pancakes
directions: Rinse blueberries and drain.
Combine muffin mix, egg, milk and orange rind.
Beat until well blended.
Fold in blueberries. Fry on greased griddle until top bubbles.
Turn and brown other side.
Serve with blueberry syrup.

title: bread pudding
directions: Place brown sugar in bottom of buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Cut up bread into cubes.
Place on top of brown sugar. Sprinkle raisins.
Combine milk, salt, eggs and vanilla.
Pour this over bread.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Place baking dish in pan of hot water and bake in slow oven at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve warm or cool.
Garnish with heavy cream poured on top of each portion.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Bake at 300° for 10 to 15 minutes, no longer.

title: pot roast in foil
directions: Line a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan with aluminum foil.
Place meat in pan.
Pour soup over meat.
Add onion soup mix.
Cover and seal meat securely.
Cook in a 300° oven for 4 hours.

title: cheesy cheese ball
directions: Combine cheeses, onion sauce and sugar.
Mix well and roll into a ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.

title: josie's chicken salad
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well.
Serve with your favorite crackers, or fresh bread, and fresh fruit for an excellent meal.

title: quick & easy spinach pie
directions: Spray 8 inch square baking dish with cooking spray.
In a medium bowl stir together the next nine ingredients.
Lay 1 sheet of phyllo dough in baking dish.
Spray completely with cooking spray.
Repeat with 4 more sheets of phyllo dough, spraying and alternating the direction of each sheet.
Spoon spinach mixture into phyllo lined dish.
Lay 1 sheet phyllo dough on top of mixture.
allowing edges to drape over pan.
Spray and layer remaining sheets as you did for bottom layer.
Turn edges to form a rim.
Spray rim and top layer.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35-45 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before cutting.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Mix all beans together add 1 jar BBQ sauce.
Simmer in crock pot for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve hot over tortilla chips, crushed up, in a bowl.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Let the first 4 ingredients stand 1 hour, then drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook 20 minutes.
Put into hot sterilized jars.

title: pumpkin drop cookies
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and pumpkin together. Add salt, vanilla and egg. Sift together dry ingredients and add to mixture. Add chips and nuts. Drop on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Raisins may be substituted for chips. Also, may be frosted but are very good left unfrosted also.

title: special k cookies
directions: Mix ingredients and heat over a very low heat until it bubbles well, then add: 12 oz jar of peanut butter (I like to smooth, but you can use peanut butter with nuts).
Add: 5 cups of Special K cereal.
Stir together and drop by tablespoon full or the size of cookies you want, on buttered foil or wax paper. These are wonderful cookies to keep in a covered container.

title: tomato lima bake
directions: Fry bacon.
Brown onion in bacon drippings. Combine bacon and onion with soup and beans.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with buttered crumbs. Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: scalloped chicken casserole
directions: In large bowl, combine soup, milk and cheese.
Add chicken, macaroni and eggs.
Stir in 1/4 cup melted oleo.
Put in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight.
Toss bread crumbs with remaining oleo.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes or until bubbly and golden brown.
Serves 12.

title: taco dip
directions: Put cheese on top.
Put tomato on top of cheese.
Put olives over tomato.
Top with green onions.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Cook chicken in oven for 1 hour.
When done, remove and let cool.
Cook macaroni and cheese as directed on box.
Cut chicken into small pieces.
When macaroni is done, add chicken and macaroni into a casserole dish.
Pour in rotel and mix well.
Top with cheese and bake 15 minutes on 350°.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Mix in oil.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add carrots.
Cook 35 minutes at 350°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Stir once after 15 minutes.

title: basic pie crust
directions: Mix flour salt and shortening with a fork until shortening is the size of peas.
Add cold water and mix until dough forms a ball.
Divide in 1/2 and roll out on floured board or counter top. Makes 2 (9 inch) crusts.
For prebaked crust place in pie pan and trim edges, prick bottom with a fork and bake at 425° for about 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Saute onions in oleo; add rice and saute for a few more minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Cover and place in 400° oven for 20 minutes (do not stir).
Remove from oven; take out bay leaf.
Additional oleo may be added if needed.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Prepare brownies according to directions.
Let cool.
Prepare pudding according to package directions.
Crumble half of brownies in bottom of serving dish.
Spread with half of pudding.
Sprinkle with half of crumbled Heath bars.
Repeat with brownies, pudding and Heath bars.
Spread Cool Whip over top.

title: stay-crisp slaw
directions: Mix shredded cabbage and carrots, green pepper, and onion. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup cold water.
Chill.
Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water.
Mix sugar, vinegar, celery seeds, salt and pepper in saucepan; bring to boil.
Stir in softened gelatin.
Cool slightly until thickened; beat well.
Gradually beat in oil. Drain vegetables.
Pour dressing over top.
Mix until all vegetables are coated.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Layer in order; repeat layers.
Pour milk on top until you see it.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Stir in eggs, corn and milk.
Mix all ingredients.
Drop by tablespoonfuls into deep hot oil (375°). Fry until golden brown, turning once.
Drain on paper towels. Serve hot with honey.

title: favorite sour cream cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, then sour cream and vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Chill dough an hour or two, or even overnight.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: coffee pot cider
directions: Place filter in coffee basket and fill with brown sugar, allspice, cloves, cinnamon stick, salt, nutmeg and orange wedges. Pour apple cider into coffee pot where the water usually goes. Brew and serve hot.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Place sheets of foil on countertop for cooling cookies. Combine peanut butter, shortening, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl. Beat at medium speed until well mixed. Add egg. Beat until blended. Combine flour, salt and baking soda. Mix with creamed mixture. Drop by heaping teaspoonful 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten slightly in crisscross pattern. Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: slaw salad
directions: Toast almonds and sesame seed in microwave for 3 to 4 minutes. Mix toasted almonds and sesame seed and other ingredients.

title: brownies
directions: Beat
eggs
well.
Add	oil
and
vanilla.
In separate bowl, mix dry ingredients.
Add to eggs, oil and vanilla.
Add nuts. Bake
at 350° for 40 minutes.
Spread marshmallow cream on top immediately after removing from oven.

title: whole wheat pancakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Then stir in wet ingredients just until moistened.
Fry in oil on a hot griddle until golden brown.
Turn when bubbles appear and the edges are firm.
Top with your favorite fruit sauce.
Healthy and delicious!

title: peanut butter dessert
directions: Crumb Mixture:
Melt margarine on cookie sheet at 350°. Watch.
Add flour, brown sugar and nuts.
Mix.
Bake 5 minutes. Take out and crumble.
Put back in oven and bake 7 minutes (not too brown).
Crumble mixture on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan (save some of mixture to put on top).

title: pecan brittle
directions: Combine syrup, sugar, vinegar and water in iron skillet on high heat.
After sugar melts, add nuts, let boil until it turns a caramel color.
Remove from heat, add soda, stir briskly and spread on marble slab (a buttered cookie sheet will work).
When cool, break into pieces and enjoy.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Simmer tea bags, cloves and cinnamon in 2 cups water for 15 minutes.
Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in 2 more cups of boiling water.
Remove tea bags and spices from tea mixture.
Combine tea mixture, Jell-O mixture and pineapple juice in a gallon jar. Finish filling with water.
Heat to serve.

title: elizabeth's coconut cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions. You can add the 4 egg yolks that will be left over from the Coconut Divinity Icing recipe listed below. Pour into 3 round pans and bake according to pkg. directions. Allow to cool before icing.

title: microwave hash brown casserole
directions: Defrost potatoes in microwave by making a small slit in bag and cook in microwave on Defrost for 3 minutes.
Melt margarine in 3-quart casserole.
Add potatoes, onion, 1 cup cheese, soup, sour cream and salt.
Cover with wax paper and cook on High for 20 minutes, stirring once.
Uncover and sprinkle remaining 1 cup cheese and paprika over top and cook 3 minutes or until cheese melts.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.
Good for covered dish dinners.

title: beef in wine sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
Stir together well, cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: tiger butter
directions: Melt almond bark and peanut butter in microwave at 50% power. Stir and check often.
Put in foil lined cookie sheet and spread evenly.
Next, melt chocolate chips and drizzle over top of white mixture and swirl.
Chill, then break into pieces.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into strips about 1/2 inch wide by 3 or 4 inches long.
Brown steak in butter.
Remove from pan; add flour to pan. Add more butter if necessary to dissolve.
Add catsup.
Dissolve bouillon cube in one cup of hot water.
Add catsup and soy sauce to pan.
Stir until slightly thickened.
Add browned meat, onions and enough water to cover meat.
Cook 1 hour.
Add sliced peppers. Cook until tender.
Add mushrooms.
If sauce is too thin, thicken with cornstarch dissolved in water.
Serve with rice, noodles or mashed potatoes.

title: western lima bake
directions: Cook bacon and onion until tender.
Add green chili peppers, chili powder, tomato sauce and tomatoes.
Place beans, tomato mixture and cheese in alternating layers in a 2-quart casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: moussaka
directions: California Dip:
Mix onion soup with sour cream; stir 1 tablespoon flour and beaten eggs into this mixture until smooth; set aside.

title: chicken and celery
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Dip chicken in this mixture and brown lightly in oil.
Saute onion and celery with chicken.
Add broth and simmer 1/2 hour, until tender.
Thicken with cornstarch mixed with a small amount of water.

title: lasagna
directions: In frying pan, brown sausage and hamburger together.
Mix cottage cheese, egg and 3/4 can Parmesan cheese.
Set aside.
Cook lasagna noodles al dente; put salt and oil in water.
Drain and rinse.
Layer in 10 x 13-inch pan:
sauce, lasagna, cottage cheese mixture, meat and Mozzarella cheese; repeat.
Top with sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour, until bubbly and cheese is melted.

title: sour cream cheddar potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with 2 cups crushed corn flakes; drizzle with 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: barbecued frankfurters
directions: Mix all ingredients all together, then pour over the hot dogs, broil until brown.

title: meat cobbler
directions: Dust cubes with seasoned flour.
Brown in oil with onion.
Add tomato juice, garlic and bay leaf.
Bake, covered, in 350° oven for 2 1/2 hours.
Add more juice, if needed.
Lay canned biscuits on top and cook until browned.

title: chicken in a skillet
directions: Dredge chicken in seasoned flour.
Brown chicken on all sides in butter in a large heavy skillet.
Place precooked carrots and onions over chicken.
Mix soup, celery, sour cream and poultry seasoning.
Pour over chicken and vegetables.
Heat to boiling; cover and simmer for about 45 minutes or until chicken is tender. Top with parsley.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion until tender.
Drain.
Add other ingredients, put in casserole.
Top with bread or cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Crumble sausage into a large saucepan; cook over medium-low heat.
Add onion; cook and stir until transparent.
Drain, discarding all but 2 tablespoons of drippings.
Stir in flour; cook over medium-low heat about 6 minutes or until mixture bubbles and turns golden.
Stir in milk.
Add seasonings; cook, stirring until thickened.
To serve, slice biscuits and spoon gravy over halves. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Beat sugar and eggs.
Add oil and vanilla; mix well.
Combine dry ingredients.
Gradually add to sugar mixture.
Stir in apples and walnuts.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool on rack. Frost.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix these ingredients together well.
Pour the batter into greased and floured pans, two or three according to size of the pans.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: pizza dip
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and put in bottom of square or rectangular pan.
Next spread pizza sauce on top.
Top with pepperoni.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, then top with Mozzarella cheese and put back in oven until cheese melts.
Serve with crackers.

title: kool-aid play dough
directions: Mix flour, salt, alum and Kool Aid in a large bowl.
Add boiling water and oil.
Knead until cool.
Store in an airtight container.
Will keep for 3 to 4 weeks.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Stir in water gradually. Cook until clear.
Let boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add jello and butter.
Cool slightly and stir in berries.
Pour into cooked pie shell and chill before serving.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: lite sausage primavera
directions: In medium skillet, heat oil.
Add sausage and remaining ingredients, except spaghetti.
Stir-fry until sausage is browned and vegetables are tender.
Add spaghetti; toss to coat.
Heat through.
Serve immediately.

title: beet salad(rodbette salat)
directions: Drain beets.
Peel and core apple and chop along with beets, onion and allspice.
Add vinegar and sugar and refrigerate overnight.

title: ruby hoop tomato soup
directions: Cook all vegetables and run through food mill.
Cream butter, sugar and flour.
Add to puree.
Stir and cook until thin gravy. Put in jars and process 10 minutes at 5 pounds pressure.
At serving time, add 2 pinches of soda.
Makes 10 to 11 pints.

title: fried pie crust
directions: Roll real thin.
Put on fruit and fold over together.
Fry slowly.

title: tomato casserole
directions: Fry bacon and onion together; toss with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil butter beans until done; this takes about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Place Veg-All, okra and butter beans in about 6 cups of chicken broth.
Boil for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add chicken.
Place mixture in large casserole dish.

title: fish rarebit
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, mix flour, mustard and pepper.
Whisk in the beer and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir in the cheese.
Add the haddock, tossing well to coat; pour all into a well greased 9-inch pie pan.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake for 10 minutes.
Uncover and bake another 5 minutes or until sauce is bubbly and fish is cooked through.
Ladle the rarebit over whole wheat toast or brown rice.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Boil salt, vinegar, sugar, oil and celery seed.
Pour boiling liquid over vegetables.
Refrigerate, stirring occasionally. Serve well chilled.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread coconut and nuts to cover the bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix according to package directions.
Pour into pan.
Combine cream cheese and butter; mix well.
Add powdered sugar.
Place dollops of mixture onto cake mix.
Do not touch sides of pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Needs no icing.

title: garlic chicken
directions: Mix garlic powder, seasoned salt, milk and egg together and soak chicken overnight.
Flour chicken and deep fry until golden brown.
(It ain't no ordinary chicken!)

title: quick fix shrimp barbecue style
directions: Mix all ingredients, but shrimp in bowl. Add shrimp; cover and place in refrigerator and let marinate at least 2 hours. Place grill sheet on top of grate over medium fire. Place shrimp on grill sheet and cook 2 to 4 minutes on each side or until they are pink in color.

title: homestyle tuna pie
directions: Line pie pan with crust.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into pan.
Top with remaining crust.
Seal and crimp edges.
Slit top of crust to vent.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: popcorn candy
directions: Melt oleo.
Add sugar and syrup.
Bring to a boil.
Add salt and nuts; cook 15 minutes.
Add to popped corn; mix well.
Spread on lightly greased cookie sheet.
When cooled, break into pieces.

title: quick stuffed peppers
directions: Cut top off green peppers; clean out insides.
Combine remaining ingredients and fill peppers with mixture.
Put into casserole and cover.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until peppers are tender.

title: mother's banana nut bread
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs and beat well. Stir in bananas.
Mix well.
Add nuts.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to mixture. Stir well.
Pour into greased loaf pan or Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: strawberry surprise
directions: Break cake into pieces.
Place in large Pyrex dish.
Dissolve jello with 2 cups boiling water. Chop and sweeten strawberries. Pour over cake. Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate for 4 hours before serving.

title: rick's favorite tuna salad
directions: Add
equal amount of dry oatmeal to the tuna.
Then add mayonnaise,
hard-boiled eggs and diced pickles.
This is good for cold
sandwiches,
on
crackers,
or
spread on bread and topped with cheese, then toasted in the oven.

title: hush puppies
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Place cornmeal and flour in bowl.
Add buttermilk and stir until mixed thoroughly. Add beaten egg, onion and dissolved yeast mixture.
Mix thoroughly and drop from teaspoon into deep hot oil.
Cook until golden brown.
Serve immediately.
Yields 10 servings.

title: grape-nut dessert
directions: Beat pudding and milk until thick. Add cereal and Cool Whip. Cover and refrigerate.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw, chop and dry good the spinach.
Mix together.
Is best if made 1 day in advance.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Flour chicken the night before and store in paper bag in refrigerator. Fry wings in 1-inch oil to light brown. Cool. Mix soy sauce, sugar, garlic, oil, sesame seeds and onions. Dip wings in sauce and place on cookie sheet. Warm in oven to set sauce and reheat wings.

title: sugar-free banana pudding
directions: Follow directions on pudding mix. Add bananas and sugar-free vanilla wafers in layers.

title: never fail divinity
directions: Cook 1 cup sugar and 3/4 cup water until it spins a thread. Slowly add to stiffly beaten egg whites, beating with electric mixer on medium speed.
Cook remaining sugar, water and corn syrup until brittle when tested in cold water.
Add slowly to egg white mixture, beating constantly until stiff.
Add vanilla and nuts. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
When cool, cut into 1-inch squares. Store in a tight container.

title: 10 layer salad
directions: Cut up lettuce and spread in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Chop cauliflower and spread over lettuce.
Chop bell pepper and spread over cauliflower.
Chop onion and spread over bell pepper.
Spread frozen English pas over bell pepper.
(Do not thaw English peas.) Spread mayonnaise over English peas.
Sprinkle dry Italian seasoning mix over mayonnaise.
Sprinkle sugar over seasoning mix. Spread cheese over seasoning mix.
Spread bacon bits over top of cheese.
It is best to make the night before.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chicken pastry
directions: Cook and debone chickens.
Add water to broth to equal to 3 to 4 quarts. Bring to a boil and drop pastry, one piece at a time, to prevent sticking together.
Cook about 12 to 15 minutes without stirring. Add chicken before serving.

title: roasted sweet potatoes with brown sugar and black pepper butter
directions: For butter:
Using electric mixer, beat first 4 ingredients until light and fluffy.
Season with salt.
(Can be prepared 4 days ahead.
Cover and refrigerate.)

title: squash casserole
directions: Mash squash.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Melt butter; mix into cornbread stuffing.
Add 1/2 of this into squash.
Place into a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Top with remaining mixture.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: golden potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes; cool, peel and grate with coarse grater.
Add sour cream, cheese, onions, milk, salt and pepper.
Turn into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine 2 tablespoons melted butter and 3/4 cup bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 300° for 50 minutes.

title: brownie pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine brownie mix, flour, water oil and egg. Beat 50 strokes by hand.
Pour into 15 inch pizza pan and spread to 14 inch circle.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
DO NOT OVER BAKE!!
Take from oven and immediately sprinkle with marshmallows, chips and nuts.
Allow to cool 20 minutes, then drizzle with caramel topping. Cool completely before cutting.

title: mincemeat
directions: Combine all ingredients and add water or cider to moisten until sloppy. Simmer until meats and fruits are tender and flavors are blended. Pack in jars and seal.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla; blend well.
Add combined dry ingredients.
Do not beat.
Fold in zucchini and nuts.
Spoon batter into 2 well-greased 8 x 4 x 3-inch pans.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: chicken king ranch
directions: Combine chicken soup, mushroom soup, tomatoes (use only 1/2 can if you don't like real hot food) and chicken broth for sauce. Grease a large flat casserole (13 x 9-inch or similar size).
Fix in casserole a layer of chicken, layer of tortillas, onion, then cheese and sauce.
Then repeat your layers again, but this time end up with cheese.
Cover the dish with foil for the first 30 minutes while baking at 350°.
Uncover for the last 30 minutes.

title: green beans mac cheese casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese per package directions.
Heat green beans (use microwave) and add to macaroni and cheese.
Top with crispy onions.
Serve hot.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all together; chill and serve.

title: rouladen
directions: You will need white sewing thread.

title: fruit punch
directions: Blend pineapple, strawberries, orange and sugar in a blender. When ready to use, add ginger ale and ice.
Great for parties and buffets.

title: chocolate "biscota" cookies
directions: Mix together like pie crust and add about 1 cup milk.
Roll into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pecan pancakes with spiced syrup
directions: Combine pecans, vanilla, cinnamon and pumpkin pie spice in a small bowl.
Mix until pecan pieces are well coated with flavorings.
Add dry pancake mix and stir to combine.
Slowly whisk water into pancake mix until smooth.
Preheat nonstick skillet to 375° over medium-low heat.
Pour 1/4 cup of batter per pancake onto lightly greased skillet.
Flip when pancakes begin to bubble (1-2 minutes per side) or until golden brown.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix together, chill.
Use as a dip for carrot sticks, celery, cauliflower, etc., or on crackers.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix together flour, yeast, sugar and soda.
Cut Crisco into flour until mixture resembles small peas.
Add buttermilk and mix well.
Dough will be sticky.
You can shape into biscuits, rings or whatever.
Bake at 450° for about 10 minutes.
When making biscuits, make sure the sides of each touch slightly.
You can refrigerate this dough, covered for up to 7 days, using it as you wish.

title: chicken salad supreme
directions: To toast sliced almonds, saute until golden in small amount of margarine.
Combine all ingredients; toss lightly.
Serve as salad on lettuce leaf or use as a sandwich spread.

title: linda's quick vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat; rinse with hot water and add rest of ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer.
Ready to eat in as little as 15 minutes.
Great with cornbread.
Makes 4 to 5 quarts.

title: mom's taco bean dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in the bottom of a square pan.
Spread beans over cream cheese.
Pour salsa over beans.
Sprinkle cheese over salsa.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve with nachos.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Mix sugar and butter together until creamy.
Add peanut butter and mix well.
Add one egg at a time and mix after each one.
Put baking powder and flour in dish and mix.
Then alternate flour and milk until all in the batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: german sour cream potato salad
directions: Chop warm potatoes in large bowl.
Add eggs and onion.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Retain the bacon grease.
Put bacon over the potatoes.
Add to the grease the salt, pepper, vinegar, sugar and sour cream; bring to boil, stirring to combine ingredients.
Pour over potatoes.
Serve warm or cold.
Makes 8 servings.

title: easy peanut butter cookies(yields 5 dozen)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, blend sweetened condensed milk, peanut butter, egg and vanilla extract and beat until smooth.
Add biscuit mix and mix well.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls; place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheets and flatten with fork.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until lightly browned (do not overbake).
Cool and enjoy!

title: zucchini-hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat with onion.
Cook or steam sliced zucchini until tender.
Arrange in layers in 2-quart casserole dish as follows:
rice, zucchini, ground meat and onion, mushrooms, stewed tomatoes and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes, enough to melt cheese.

title: bread pudding
directions: Place bread cubes in greased 1-quart casserole.
Combine eggs, sugar, salt, cinnamon, vanilla and milk; beat well.
Pour over bread crumbs.
Set casserole in baking pan with 1 inch hot water. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Serve warm.
Serves 4.

title: wrapped chicken
directions: Wrap dried beef and partially cooked bacon around chicken breast or smaller pieces if desired.
Place in casserole dish. Pour soup over chicken.
Add sour cream and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: corn dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate awhile.

title: snowballs
directions: Combine butter, sugar and vanilla.
Separately combine flour and salt.
Combine all ingredients and chill for an hour. Roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes. When cool enough to touch, roll in powdered sugar, then again when cooled. Makes 4 dozen.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients except dressings, preserves, and vinegar in large bowl.
Mix thoroughly; if mixture seems a little dry, add a few tablespoons of water.
Shape into walnut -sized balls.
Place meatballs on ungreased baking sheet and bake for about 20 minutes in 350 degrees oven or until meat juices are clear.
Drain meatballs on paper towels (meatballs may be frozen or refrigerated at this point).

title: quick dutch cake
directions: Mix like cake; sprinkle generously with brown sugar.
Dot with butter and cinnamon.
Bake 1/2 hour at 375°.
Bake in 1 layer cake pan.

title: easton's eatable animal cracker necklace
directions: Will also need 8 yards of ribbon, cut into 1 yard lengths.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels with butter and put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: ranch dip
directions: Layer as follows: sour cream and Ranch dip mixed, Parmesan, Mozzarella, Cheddar, green onions, bell pepper, tomato, Parmesan and sliced olives. Serve using restaurant style chips.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Add half the nuts (1 cup). Refrigerate until firm.
Roll in remaining nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: nacho casserole
directions: Grease 2 quart baking dish.
Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Line bottom with taco chips, then meat, mixture, 1/2 taco sauce. Repeat in layers.
Drip remaining sauce over top.
Top with cheese and scallions.
Bake for 25 minutes at 375°.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Fold together the cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Sprinkle dry Jell-O over the mixture and stir well.
Mix in orange slices and chill.

title: italian egg croquettes
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs (moist batter as in pancakes). Drop into hot oil in skillet until shaped and firm.
Turn and fry on second side.
Drop croquettes into hot spaghetti sauce.
Cook about 2 hours.
(If batter thickens, add milk to thin.)

title: linda's chicken casserole
directions: Mix stuffing and margarine.
With half of stuffing mixture, cover bottom of a 9 x 15-inch (you can use two 8 x 8-inch) baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over stuffing mixture in dish.
Cover with remaining stuffing mixture and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Let stand for 10 to 20 minutes before serving.
If making two casseroles, one can be frozen.
If baked frozen, bake 1 hour.

title: peachy dessert
directions: Mix jello and hot water.
Add fruit.
Let set 1 hour in refrigerator.
Mix in cool whip. Refrigerate.

title: overnight lettuce salad
directions: Wash and break lettuce into pieces.
Add green onions and celery.
Sprinkle water chestnuts and peas on top.
Spread mayonnaise on top; sprinkle with sugar and cheese.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, fry bacon. Cut in small pieces and drain.
Cook eggs, chop and put on top of salad.
Thinly slice tomato and top.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Grind all ingredients, except meat, in blender.
Mix in meat and shape into balls (size of walnuts).
Bring the catsup and ginger ale to a boil and drop meatballs into sauce and simmer for 20 minutes uncovered.

title: blintz bubble ring]
directions: Cut cream cheese into 20 pieces.
Roll each into a ball.
Roll out each biscuit to about 3-inch diameter.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Place 1 cheese ball and 1 teaspoon of cinnamon mixture in center of each biscuit.
Bring dough to top and pinch to seal. Pour melted butter into the bottom of a 5-cup ring mold.
Sprinkle half the pecans and half the remaining cinnamon mixture into the mold.
Place half the rolls atop the mixture, seam side up. Repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Immediately invert pan on serving platter.

title: snowball cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water and add cold water.
Mix Dream Whip as directed on box.
Add remaining ingredients, except cake and coconut.
Put cake in layers, then mixture, ending with mixture.
Sprinkle top with coconut.
Chill several hours to set. Better made a day ahead.
(I have omitted the pineapple, nuts and cherries and used 3 to 4 cups fresh strawberries, sweetened with 3/4 cup sugar.)
Serves 12.

title: chicken with apple saute
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon butter in pan.
Add apples; saute for 30 seconds to 1 minute.
Remove apples; add another tablespoon butter to saute onions over medium flame until translucent.
Add chicken breasts over onions; add sherry or apple juice.
Cook for 5 minutes on each side, covered over medium heat.
Add heavy cream to remaining sauce for 5 to 7 minutes, until thick.

title: deep dish apple crisp
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together. Add melted butter. Beat well. Fold in flour, baking powder and salt. Add vanilla.
Spread mixture over apples and bake in 350° oven until apples are done and top is crisp, about 45 minutes.

title: souper chicken with rice
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil and brown chicken.
Drain.
Add soup mix and salt blended with water; bring to a boil, then stir in uncooked rice.
Simmer, covered, stirring occasionally, 45 minutes or until chicken is done and rice is tender.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour.
Remove from pan.
While hot, mix 6 tablespoons apricot nectar and 1 1/2 cups powdered sugar; pour over cake while hot.

title: joyce's vegetable dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Better if kept overnight in refrigerator before serving.

title: chocolate oaties
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan; add sugar, cocoa and milk.
Bring to a boil on medium heat.
Cook 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool 1 minute.
Add vanilla, salt, peanut butter and oatmeal. Mix well quickly.
Drop by teaspoons on waxed paper and cool for 30 minutes.

title: snicker bars
directions: Soften yogurt and mix all ingredients together. Pour into 8 x 8 pan and freeze. Makes 8 servings.

title: red rice 2
directions: Saute celery, onion, and bell pepper in bacon grease for 10 minutes.
In a separate pan combine water, salt, and butter. Bring to a boil.
Add rice and other ingredients.
Cook on low heat for 10 minutes.
Put in a casserole dish and bake at 350 for 45 minutes.

title: blueberry torte
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan on bottom with mixture.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt and flour thoroughly.
Beat eggs slightly and add with margarine to dry mixture.
Mix. Add syrup, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°. Serves 8.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease cookie sheet. Beat shortening and sugars until creamy. Add eggs and vanilla. Mix well. Combine flour, baking soda and salt. Add to shortening mixture; mix well. Stir in oats, nuts, raisins and chocolate chips. Using rounded tablespoonfuls, roll into balls and place 2-inches apart. Flatten with fork and bake 10 to 12 minutes. Let stand 1 minute before moving to rack.

title: fettucini supreme
directions: Combine fettucini, butter, ham and mushrooms in a saucepan. Beat half and half, egg, nutmeg and pepper until foamy.
Add to fettucini mixture and stir.
Stir in Parmesan cheese and parsley. Heat slowly until thickened.
Serve on plates and sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4.

title: cinnamon ornaments
directions: Mix ingredients and spread on waxed paper.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Put a small hole at the top of each shape, using a small straw.
Allow ornaments to set until dry.
After set, put a ribbon through the ornament.

title: bacon cheddar eggs
directions: Slice boiled eggs lengthways; remove yolk and set whites aside. In a bowl, mix egg yolks, mayonnaise, bacon, cheese, honey mustard and black pepper. Spoon (or pipe) yolk mixture into the hollow egg whites.

title: doughnuts
directions: Mix and put in doughnut maker; fry in hot fat.
Turn often.

title: crawfish jambalaya
directions: Cut sausage in small pieces.
Brown in microwave oven on High. Saute jalapeno peppers, garlic, onions and celery in oleo in large pot.
Add peeled crawfish tails, fat and sausage.
Season highly.
Cook for 30 minutes over low fire.
Add chopped green onions and rice, mixing well.
Cook for 5 more minutes.
Serve hot with French bread and green salad.

title: honey dijon chicken
directions: Rinse chicken, desired amount chicken breasts.
Pat dry. Place on lightly buttered foil covered baking sheet.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour 1 to 2 tablespoons of dressing over each one. Cover sheet loosely with aluminum foil.
Seal edges.
Bake 25 minutes.
Uncover.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.

title: seacoast salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package.
Mix other ingredients. Add to macaroni.
Mix lightly; chill.
Add more salad dressing before serving (if needed).
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: iced tea
directions: Pour boiling water over tea and strain over sugar.
Makes about 2 gallons.

title: vidalia onion and cheese spread
directions: Use equal parts of all three ingredients.
Mix together and bake at 350° until bubbly.
Serve with Triscuits or wheat crackers.
Important to keep hot while serving.

title: bourbon slush
directions: Mix together and freeze overnight.
Scoop into glasses and pour ginger ale over.
Serve immediately.

title: amaretto cheese cake with chocolate chips
directions: *Or use 1/2 stick melted butter and 3/4 cup Amaretto cookie crumbs.

title: party punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except garnish.
Garnish with fruit.

title: molasses candy
directions: Put molasses, sugar and vinegar in pan until the mixture hardens when dipped into cold water.
Pour into buttered pans and mark into squares and set aside to harden; or cool slightly, butter your hands and pull the candy until it is light.

title: beef macaroni skillet
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet.
Add remaining ingredients and cook, covered, until macaroni is done.
Stir occasionally while cooking.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in tomato soup; let cool.
Mince onion.
Add all together.
Add salt if needed.
Pour into mold and chill. Turn mold out on lettuce.
Eat with crackers.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Prepare two cookie sheets with butter or margarine.

title: lemon tarts
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and salt. Add lemon juice and rind. Add egg yolks, slightly beaten.
Fold in stiff egg whites.
Pour into unbaked tart shells.
Bake in
a 350° oven until set.

title: pickled pepper and green tomatoes
directions: Bring to boil and add peppers, tomatoes (cut in quarters) or use small green tomatoes.
Cook until they change color and pack in clean hot jars.
Seal at once.

title: baked ham
directions: You also need 1 large aluminum cake pan.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix and put in a 9 x 12-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle dry yellow cake mix over pumpkin mix.
Sprinkle 2 cups walnut meats over cake mix.
Drizzle 3/4 cup melted butter or oleo over nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 325° to 350°.
When cool, top with whipped topping.

title: good hot and cold okra
directions: Add all ingredients together. Mix well.
In large skillet, heat cooking oil.
Pour okra in hot oil.
Cook until golden brown. Good cold or hot!!

title: oatmeal carmellettos
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt caramels in milk; cool slightly. Combine all other ingredients except chocolate chips and nuts. This will be crumbly.
Press half of mixture in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread caramel mixture carefully. Spread on remaining crumb mixture.
Bake 20 minutes and cool.
Cut before cooling.

title: greek salad
directions: Break lettuce leaves into small pieces and place in large salad bowl.
Add tomatoes, black olives and crumbled Feta cheese. Combine wine vinegar, olive oil, garlic and oregano.
Pour over the salad the toss lightly.
Garnish with pepperoni and olives, if desired.

title: deer burgers
directions: Place bacon on bottom of pan.
Mix ground venison with onion. Make into burgers; cook over medium-low heat until done.
Turn as needed.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: scallops a l'orange
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Place scallops in a single layer in open oven pan.
Pour sauce over scallops and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Have butcher grind very coarsely round steak in amount needed (about 1/4 pound or more per person).
When ready to cook, form meat into fillet shapes, molding very lightly (so as not to pack) and wrap with a bacon strip.
Broil as you would steak fillets under the broiler.
Season with salt just before they have finished cooking.

title: doris and tula's cookies
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Fold in chopped nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: fruit bowl
directions: Open chunk pineapple.
Cut bananas; put in pineapple juice. Clean and slice strawberries.
Peel and slice kiwi.
Add drained oranges.
Take bananas out of juice; add them to other ingredients.
Last, add peach pie filling.
Refrigerate.

title: oven stew
directions: Use as many vegetables as wanted.
Mix in 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: ham and broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli according to package; drain well.
In saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender, but not brown.
In large bowl, stir together soups, milk and cheese.
Add broccoli, onion, ham, uncooked rice and Worcestershire sauce; mix well.
Divide between 2 (2 1/2-quart) casseroles.
Bake uncovered at 350° until rice is done, 45 to 50 minutes.
Garnish each with a sprig of watercress if desired.
Makes two casseroles.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together dry.
Add salt.
Mix boiling water and then add milk.
Separate eggs.
Add yolks to milk and sugar.
Cook in a double boiler until it begins to thicken.
Add butter, coconut and vanilla.
Stir constantly until thick enough for pie.
Pour into cooked crust.
Make meringue of whites, using 2 tablespoons sugar.
Put on top of pie and bake in a slow oven until brown.

title: barbecued chicken 2
directions: Combine all of the ingredients.
Place young chicken, cut in half, in shallow pan.
Cover with sauce.
Place in 350° oven and bake 30 minutes.
Turn chicken over and baste.
Bake 30 more minutes.
Turn again and baste.
Cook in all 1 1/2 hours, turning every half hour.

title: bacon wrapped chestnuts
directions: Drain whole chestnuts and wrap 1/2 strips of bacon around each; fasten with toothpicks. Fry until bacon is crisp. Drain off grease.
Mix together white sugar, catsup and baby food peaches. Put in pan with wrapped chestnuts and simmer. Keep hot.

title: mixed vegetable salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in bowl and set aside.
Combine next 5 ingredients in a heavy pan.
Stir and cook until thick and clear. Mix with other vegetables and chill until ready to serve.

title: saturday night spread
directions: Heat fat in skillet.
Brown beef and onions in fat.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 25 minutes.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook sliced squash; drain.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Stir in carrots, drained squash and onion.
Combine stuffing and melted margarine.
Spread half of stuffing on bottom, then place vegetable mixture and stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spencer's beer batter fish fry
directions: Very good as a condiment with chicken, turkey, ham and pork. Some like it even on a sandwich.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in hot water.
Let cool and add remaining ingredients. Add ginger ale just before serving.
Makes about 1 1/2 gallons.

title: orange-ginger halibut
directions: Place fish in a single layer on a greased unheated rack of a broiler pan.
Brush fish with half of the margarine.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Broil fish 4-inches from heat for 8 to 12 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork, turning fish once and brushing with remaining margarine.

title: oyster stew
directions: Put oysters and margarine in saucepan on medium-high.
Cook until oysters curl.
Add milk and flour.
Heat until hot; simmer on low.

title: artichoke squares
directions: Drain marinade from artichokes and reserve.
Chop artichokes. Saute onion and garlic in marinade for 5 minutes.
In a separate bowl, beat eggs.
Add all other ingredients to eggs.
Bake in a greased 9 x 9-inch pan at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares and serve hot.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix chicken, vegetables & soup together, pour into pie crust in pie tin, place second crust over filling, vent top layer by making slits with a knife. Bake at 450 for 10-15 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll in balls; press with spoon.
Bake at 350° for 16 to 18 minutes.

title: tortellini minestrone
directions: Heat beef broth, tomato and water to boiling.
Add tortellini; cook for 15 minutes after return to boiling.
Add frozen vegetables; return to boil and cook for 15 minutes.
Add 1/2 teaspoon Italian seasoning and white kidney beans.
Cover; lower heat to low.
Steam for 10 minutes.
Serve with bread sticks or a garlic bread, toasted.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in unbaked pie shell for about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: crab and shrimp(fit for an embassy buffet!)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Toss lightly.
Place in greased casserole.
Refrigerate covered.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, covered. Serves 6.

title: strawberry tall cake
directions: A day ahead of serving, prepare angel food cake as package directs, using a tube pan.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in a heavy boiler.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in chocolate until it melts.
Add marshmallow cream, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into a greased pan. Cool.

title: fried chicken
directions: Take chicken breast, wash in cold water.
Sprinkle with meat tenderizer, paprika, salt and pepper.
Place in Teflon skillet on low heat; cook 50 minutes.
Last ten minutes, turn heat up to brown.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Fry onion and pepper until soft.
Add ground beef; cook until brown.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake in slow oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: quick, easy-n-fast reese's bars
directions: Combine and pat into 9 x 13 pan. Melt 12 ounces milk chocolate chips with 2 tablespoons oil and frost. Refrigerate.

title: yankee doodle salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except beans and peas.
Add them last. Marinate 24 hours in refrigerator.
Drain and serve on lettuce. Serves 6 to 8.

title: blackberry salad
directions: Mix the items very easy.
Add the jell and chill.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Take 5 pounds of fervent devotion, 3 pounds of extract of faithfulness, 4 quarts of heartfelt satisfaction, 1 pound each of prudence and good nature, 6 scruples each of confidence and mature deliberation, 8 ounces each of gentleness and modesty, 12 scruples of matrimonial fidelity, 2 pounds connubial felecity, 3 quarts ecstatic enjoyment, 1 pound each of patience, industry and economy, 9 ounces each of discretion and benevolence, 4 ounces of neatness, 1/2 pound seeds of virture, 1 ounce essence of purity, 7 pints of sweetness of disposition.
Add to this 1 quart balm of 1000 ills, 5 pints of cream of excellence, 1 gallon milk of human kindness, 100 grains common sense.
Mix thoroughly with cheerfulness.
Pour into a golden bowl of domestic happiness, lubricated with the oil of gladness and bake in the oven of blessedness heated with the fire of true love.

While warm, spread with a frosting of gracefulness. In the center, place the star of hope, encircled with a wreath of smiles, interwoven with pinks of perfection and fasten wreath with golden cords of harmony and silver thread of discord.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Mix first five ingredients well.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: creamy mocha pie
directions: Pour milk into medium bowl.
Add pudding mixes and flavored coffee mix.
Beat with wire whisk for 1 minute or until well blended.
(Mixture will be thick.)
Gently stir in one-half of the Cool Whip.
Spoon into crust.
Spread remaining topping over top of pudding in crust.
Refrigerate 3 hours or until set.
Garnish as desired.
Serves 8.
*Can substitute 2 or 3 tsp. instant coffee granules.

title: squash au gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook squash and onion in water over medium heat until squash is tender, but still firm.
Remove from heat and drain.
Add salt, pepper and butter to squash.
Then add cracker crumbs, half of the cheese, the milk and egg.
Stir carefully until well blended.
Pour mixture into a 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole dish and sprinkle the top with remaining cheese. Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: trash
directions: Melt the chocolate and pour over mixture. Drop on waxed paper.

title: crispy oat cookies
directions: Cream oleo; gradually add sugars, beating well at medium speed with electric mixer.
Add egg and beat well.
Add oil and vanilla; mix well.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Stir in oats and remaining ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet; flatten each ball with a fork.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes; cool slightly and remove from cookie sheet and cool.
Yields 10 dozen.

title: creamy dream fudge
directions: In a large 4-quart saucepan, melt butter.
Add cocoa and blend well.
Stir in Pet milk.
Gradually mix in powdered sugar and salt until smooth and creamy.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Stir until well blended.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread evenly. Refrigerate until cool and firm, about 1 hour, or freeze for 20 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Beat eggs, margarine and cottage cheese together.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in 9-inch iron skillet at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sesame chicken pasta
directions: Cook chicken; cut into strips, then half the strips.
Mix all ingredients except veggies.
Add chicken.
Marinate overnight. Cook pasta; keep cool.
Mix pasta and chicken together.
Right before serving, put veggies in mixture.
Strain marinade, saving a small amount to put back in.
This recipe will keep in the refrigerator for a couple of weeks.

title: water chestnut casserole
directions: Cook celery in broth until nearly tender, not soft.
Thicken broth with cornstarch. Pour into casserole. Add chestnuts and almonds. Sprinkle with bread crumbs. Dot with butter. Bake in 350° oven for 1/2 hour. Good with fowl or cold roast.

title: zesty carrots
directions: Cook carrots for 10 to 12 minutes.
Arrange in baking dish. Add mayonnaise and next 4 ingredients.
Melt butter.
Add bread crumbs.
Spread on top of carrots.
Bake 15 minutes or until bubbly at 350° .
Garnish.

title: triple decker sandwich
directions: Blend chicken spread and sour cream; spread on 3 slices of toast.
Top with lettuce.
Cover with another slice of toast. Spread with ham.
Top with tomato and toast.
Makes 3 sandwiches.

title: pork with roasted peppers and potatoes
directions: Sprinkle pork chops with salt and pepper. In a large nonstick skillet over medium high heat, cook chops in oil for 10 minutes or until well browned (I use electric skillet set on 350°). Remove chops, set aside. Add potatoes, onions to skillet.
Cook 5 minutes or until browned, stirring occasionally.
Add chops, broth and red peppers. Bring to a boil; cover and cook over low heat for 5 minutes or until meat juices run clear.

title: french rarebit
directions: Butter bread slices & cut into small squares.
Sprinkle cheese over bread in a baking dish.
Mix milk, eggs, salt, pepper & mustard.
Pour over bread.
Bake until custard is set.
Serves 6.

title: peggy dring's carrot cake
directions: In separate container, follow next 3 steps.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Mix together raisins and nuts with 2 tablespoons of flour mixture. Beat together the sugar, oil and vanilla.
Thoroughly beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in sifted ingredients in several additions alternately with carrots.
Stir in floured raisins and nut mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans.

title: brown sack caramel corn
directions: Place popcorn in large brown paper bag.
Combine brown sugar, syrup and butter.
Cook 3 1/2 minutes on High in microwave.
Stir 1/2 teaspoon soda and a little salt into this mixture.
Add nuts. Pour this mixture over popcorn in brown paper bag and stir.
Fold over top.
Cook 4 1/2 minutes on High in microwave, stirring every 45 seconds with a long wooden spoon.
Pour out on waxed paper and cool.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Scald milk; add shortening, sugar and salt. Cool to lukewarm. Crumble yeast and soften in lukewarm water; add to lukewarm milk mixture. Add 3 cups flour; beat until smooth. Add eggs and stir; add flour to soft dough. Knead until smooth. Place in greased bowl; cover and let rise in a warm place until double (1 hour). Shape into rolls. Place in greased pan; brush with butter. Cover and let rise until light (30 to 45 minutes). Bake at 400°. Yields 4 dozen.

title: cucumbers and sour cream
directions: Mix together.
Alternate slices of new cucumbers and new onions.
Marinate for several hours in refrigerator.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: Stir cider and brown sugar in a large mug or cup.
Add the cinnamon stick.
Microwave at High (100%) until cider boils, 2 to 2 1/2 minutes.
Stir in rum. Top with butter and ground nutmeg. Makes 1 serving.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: *Six to ten slices of cooked, crumbled bacon may be used instead of sausage.

title: easy white cake
directions: Add dry ingredients.
Add shortening and 1 cup milk.
Gradually turn to speed 6 and beat 1 minute.
Scrape bowl.
Add whites, 1/2 cup milk and white vanilla.
Beat 1 minute or until smooth.
Place in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Grind vegetables; mix with salt.
Cover with plastic and let stand in nonmetal bowl overnight.
Use 2 bowls if necessary.
Next day, rinse and drain well.

title: pizza(katie langon's version of mom's pizza)
directions: First let the dough rise, then cook it at 35° for 20 minutes. Take it out of oven and put the sauce on it, and cheese and all that other stuff.
Cook it again at 35° for 35 minutes more.
Take it out again and cool it.
Cut it up and cool it.
Eat it until it's gone, but don't get a belly ache.

title: swiss fondue
directions: Use a chafing dish over very low heat.
Rub the dish with a clove of garlic, split.
Pour in dry white wine.
Heat until it bubbles.
Add diced Swiss cheese.
Cook and stir with a wooden spoon until melted and smooth.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Thin, if necessary, with more wine.
Serve hot and do not allow to cool.
Dip cubes of French bread into the fondue with long forks.
An interesting party dish.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Using a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, pour green beans in and spread around evenly. Mix your cream soups together and spread evenly on top of green beans. Place onion rings on top, enough to cover entire pan. Sprinkle sharp Cheddar cheese on top, covering completely. Cut 1-inch slices of cheese from block cheese (American) and place on top of casserole (more or less if you like). You may repeat layers. Bake in oven for 30 minutes or until cheese on top melts and soups begin to boil through. ENJOY!

title: liverwurst mold
directions: Heat consomme and dissolve gelatin.
Oil a 1-quart mold with Pam.
Slice olives and arrange in mold.
Pour thin layer of consomme over olives and put in freezer a few minutes to set.
Mix liverwurst and cream cheese together.
Pour mixture into consomme and add seasonings.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Pour into mold and refrigerate overnight.
Unmold and serve with crackers.
Will keep 3 weeks in refrigerator.

title: onion bake
directions: Saute 3 thinly sliced Spanish onions in butter.
Lay in bottom of greased casserole.
Sprinkle Swiss cheese over onions.
Pour 2 cans cream of chicken soup over onions.
Place 1/2-inch slices French bread on top of onion mixture.
Put pat of butter on each round of bread.
Bake, covered, for 25 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover.
With slotted spoon, press down on each bread slice until juices almost reach top of each slice.
Bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: shrimp scampi over linguine
directions: In large pan, saute shallots and garlic in butter and oil. Add shrimp and cook until pink and then remove shrimp and set aside.
Add flour to pan with sauteed shallots and garlic and cook 1 to 2 minutes.
Add chicken broth, wine and parsley and cook until thickened.
Add heavy cream and continue to cook 4 to 5 minutes.
Simmer gently.
Add cooked shrimp to sauce and simmer gently until warmed and sauce is bubbling.
Serve over 1 pound cooked linguine.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, oil, eggs and mandarin oranges. Bake in 325° oven 25 to 30 minutes. Cool completely.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix oatmeal and boiling water in bowl; let set 20 minutes. Beat white sugar, brown sugar, vegetable oil and egg together well.
Add flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
While cake is warm, put on Topping.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Stir in 2 to 4 packages Italian dressing mix, made to directions (amount depends on the amount of vegetables you have). Sprinkle with 1/2 cup or more of Parmesan cheese. Refrigerate 4 hours or more before serving.

title: red salmon quiche
directions: Combine salmon, pepper, onion, flour and cheese; mix.
In separate bowl, beat eggs and milk.
Put salmon mixture in unbaked pie shell.
Pour egg and milk over the salmon mixture.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until you can insert knife and it comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes, then serve.

title: apple pecan bake
directions: Core and mince apples, leaving on the skins.
Beat the egg yolks.
Add apples, pecans, lemon juice, cinnamon and sugar and mix well.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into apple mixture. Pour mixture into a flat, buttered baking dish and set the dish in a pan filled deep with hot water.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes or until tester comes out clean.
Serve hot with heavy or whipped cream.

title: strawberry banana salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except sour cream and bananas.
Pour half of Jell-O mixture into baking dish and quick freeze.
Spread sour cream over set Jell-O.
Slice bananas and arrange on top of sour cream.
Pour the rest of Jell-O mix on top and freeze.

title: cookout hamburgers
directions: Blend all together.
Makes 6 patties.
Broil 5 to 7 minutes. Baste toward last of cooking time with barbecue sauce.

title: apricot or orange salad
directions: Sprinkle pineapple, oranges, Cool Whip and cottage cheese with apricot or orange jello.
Top with pecans.
Stir well and chill.

title: pizza casserole(makes 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans.  freeze 1.)
directions: Saute peppers and onions in butter.
Drain off butter into bottoms of pans.
Cook and drain spaghetti.
Spread in pans.
Pour 1 can sauce over each pan.
Mix the 3 pounds of cheese together. Sprinkle a layer (1/2 of cheese) on each pan.
Spread a layer of pepperoni.
Spread on layers of peppers and onions (all of them). Sprinkle with oregano to taste.
Spread on mushrooms, then a layer of remaining mixed cheese.
Put another can of sauce on each pan. Top with layer of pepperoni.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Broil to crisp up top.

title: bacon roll
directions: Place flour and 1 teaspoon salt into a bowl.
Stir in the suet and add water to make a soft dough.
Turn onto a floured pastry board and knead until smooth.
Roll into a rectangle about 10 x 12-inches.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in buttered casserole.
Crumble Ritz crackers on top and dot with butter.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: chili con carne
directions: Boil the meat.
When done, cut into cubes no larger than 1/2-inch.
Saute the onions until they are soft.
In the hot oil, brown the boiled beef.
Add all other ingredients and simmer 30 minutes with pan covered.
Remove any fats prior to serving.

title: chunky pizza soup
directions: In saucepan, heat oil over medium heat. Stir-fry onion, mushrooms and green pepper until soft, but not browned. Add tomatoes, stock, pepperoni and basil. Cook until heated through. Ladle soup into 4 ovenproof bowls.
Sprinkle with cheese. Broil until cheese melts and is bubbly or microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes.

title: beef brisket
directions: If you buy a packer-trimmed beef brisket, trim fat.
Store- trimmed brisket usually doesn't need trimming.
Marinate beef brisket with Italian dressing (enough to cover).
Can marinate for as little as 1 hour or so or up to 3 or 4 hours or more, turning every so often in pan you are going to cook in.
Pour 1 jar mushrooms (juice and all), beefy onion soup mix (mixed with 1/2 cup water) and brown gravy over meat.

title: spicy egg casserole
directions: The day before serving, beat eggs in a large bowl with a whisk.
Add flour, baking powder and milk.
Cut cream cheese in small cubes; add to egg mixture with the cottage cheese.
Add grated cheeses, sausage, salt, onions and mushrooms.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch casserole and pour mixture into dish.
Dot with butter and a sprinkle of paprika.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, bring to room temperature and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: scallops and shrimp george v
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Cook shrimp; peel.
Heat oil or butter. Stir in cornstarch, salt, pepper and milk.
Let bubble about 2 minutes.
Stir in macaroni, shrimp, scallops, 1 1/2 cups cheese and wine.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: texas chili
directions: Brown beef, onion, green pepper and garlic; drain fat. Add to beans, tomato paste and other ingredients. Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: burger and bean pie
