directions: In skillet, brown meat and onion.
Peel, slice and cook potatoes in boiling water until
tender.
To meat mixture, add soup, sugar, salt and pepper and green beans.
Mix well.
Mash potatoes when done and add milk
and
egg.	In large casserole dish, put meat
mixture;
smooth
potatoes on top and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: a bowl of texas red
directions: In a large bowl, combine the Masa Harina with 1 Tbsp. of the ground chili. Dredge the cubed beef in this mixture.

title: buttermilk fried chicken with gravy
directions: Place chicken in a large flat dish.
Pour buttermilk over. Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Combine flour, salt and pepper in a double-strength paper bag.
Drain chicken pieces.
Toss one at a time in flour mixture.
Shake off excess.
Place on waxed paper for 15 minutes to dry.
Heat 1/8 to 1/4 inch of oil in a large skillet.
Fry chicken until brown on all sides.
Cover and simmer, turning occasionally for 40 to 45 minutes or until juices are clear and chicken is tender.

title: babes chocolate swirls
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking soda; set aside.
Cream Crisco and sugar until light.
Add egg, milk and peanut butter. Add flour mixture slowly.
Melt chocolate and set aside to cool. Roll dough between 2 sheets of waxed paper (sprinkle bottom sheet with flour to stop sticking). Spread chocolate onto dough, go all the way to the edge of dough.
Roll dough into "log-like" cookie. Refrigerate for 1/2 hour.
Cut "log" into slices and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes, until golden brown.

title: spanish rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In heavy iron skillet, brown ground beef.
Add salt, pepper, green pepper and onions and brown.
Pour off fat.
Add rice and tomatoes and ketchup.
Grease a large casserole dish, pour mixture in and bake for 45 minutes.
May be baked in same iron skillet.

title: double chocolate cake
directions: Cook and cool pudding.
In a large bowl, blend cake.
Mix pudding and 2 eggs.
Pour into buttered prepared angel cake pan. Sprinkle with nuts and chips.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: famous wesson fruit cake
directions: Heat oven to 275°.
Line 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) pans with lightly greased wax paper.
Combine Wesson oil, sugar and eggs.
Beat 2 minutes.
In large bowl, combine 1 cup flour with fruits and nuts. Sift remaining ingredients: flour, baking powder, salt and spices.
Beat eggs, sugar and oil.
Add flour to Wesson mixture; alternate with orange juice.
Pour batter over fruit mixture. Blend well.
Turn into pans.
Place pan of water on lower rack of oven.
Bake cakes 2 1/2 to 3 hours, until done.
Cool on wire racks.
Remove from pans.
Peel off paper.
Wrap in cloth dampened with brandy, fruit juice or wine and wrap in foil.

title: fruit cocktail cookies
directions: Mix together first 9 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients. Drop from a spoon on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until golden brown and set.

title: shrimp cheese spread
directions: Mix well and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: french toast
directions: Beat eggs and cream together.
Slice bread into halves.
Put skillet on fire with 1 tablespoon butter or shortening to get hot. Dip bread into egg mixture until covered.
Place in skillet. Sprinkle lightly with cinnamon.
Let both sides of bread get lightly browned.
Serve with syrup.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Heat milk. Add butter.
Mix sugar, cocoa, salt, flour and beaten egg yolks. Add to milk and butter mixture. Cook until thickens.
Stir constantly.
When thick, pour into baked pie shell. Add meringue and brown.
In the beaten egg whites, add 1 teaspoon sugar per egg and 1 teaspoon vanilla flavoring.

title: octopus salad
directions: Place octopus with dash of sugar in water to cover in medium size saucepan.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat and simmer, covered, until tender, about 45 minutes.
Cool completely.
Remove octopus; drain.
Peel dark skin from octopus; discard.
Coarsely chop body and tentacles.
Combine octopus, onion, oil and vinegar in a small bowl.
Refrigerate, covered, 1 hour.
Toss well.
Season to taste with pepper and salt.
Garnish.

title: pan de polvo(cinnamon tea cookies)
directions: Make cinnamon tea with tea bag and water.
Cool to room temperature.
In large mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar and salt. Cut in the shortening until mixture is very crumbly and fine textured.
Add 1/2 to 2/3 cup of the cooled cinnamon tea; just enough to make a moist but stiff dough.
Wrap dough in waxed paper and chill several hours.
Working with about 1/4 of the dough at a time, roll on floured board to thickness of about 1/8-inch.
Cut with a 2 3/4-inch round cookie cutter (or if you prefer, with star or heart cutters of approximately same size).

title: boiled custard
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar and milk.
Cook slowly, stirring all the time.
Let cool to a boil.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients, except chocolate chips.
Sprinkle top with chocolate chips before baking.
Bake in greased and floured pan (9 x 13-inch) at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: In a large saucepan, stir together all the ingredients except the rice.
Bring the mixture to a boil and reduce the heat; simmer, while covered, for 5 minutes or until shrimp turn pink. Serve over rice or with rice aside.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Separate eggs and add yolks, one at a time, to shortening and sugar mixture.
Add German chocolate, melted in boiling water.
Add alternately the flour and buttermilk.
Dissolve soda in last 1/4 cup milk.
Add vanilla and salt.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into 3 well-greased 9-inch pans and bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly spray cookie sheet with vegetable oil.
Soften margarine.
In a large bowl, sift together first 6 ingredients.
Cut in margarine with pastry blender until mixture resembles cornmeal.
Add buttermilk and stir only until moistened.
Mix currants or raisins in lightly.
Shape into ball and knead about 15 seconds. Place dough

on prepared cookie sheet. With palm of hand, flatten dough into circle about 7-inches in diameter and 1 1/2-inches thick. With sharp knife, cut a cross on top across about 1/4-inch deep and 5-inches long to prevent cracking during baking.
Spray dough with vegetable oil spray. Bake 40 to 50 minutes. Cool on wire rack.
Contains 113 calories, 1 mg. cholesterol, 3 gms. total fat and 184 mg. sodium.

title: spinach quiche
directions: In a large bowl, combine eggs, milk, cheese, soup mix and spinach. Spoon into pie crust. Bake in a 375° oven for 50 minutes until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Preheat
oven to 350°.
Mix all together and cook about 20 minutes.
Then increase heat to 400° and cook until done.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt, ginger and cinnamon together.
Add to can of pumpkin and mix.
Add eggs and mix.
Last, add milk.
Pour in 2 (9-inch) pie shells.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes and at 375° for 50 minutes or when set when tested with knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: mud pie
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease 8-inch pie plate.
Mix first 8 ingredients with wooden spoon.
Pour into pan and bake 25 minutes. Immediately prick holes in pie and spread fudge sauce over top. Cool completely and top with whipped topping.

title: pecan pie
directions: Allow butter to soften at room temperature.
Mix sugar and flour, cream butter with sugar and flour mixture.
Add corn syrup and eggs.
Beat with mixer until frothy.
Add salt, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into unbaked
9 inch pie shell and bake 45 minutes at 325 degrees.

title: italian sausage and peppers
directions: In frying pan, cook sausage until mostly done.
Place on baking dish and add pepper and onions.
Next, add the Italian tomatoes and Italian seasoning.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: macaroon pudding
directions: Line a deep pudding mold (or dish with straight sides) with macaroons; pour sherry over them.
Beat egg yolks and sugar until light; add salt and milk and cook over hot water until sightly thickened.
Soften gelatin in cold water, then stir into hot custard until dissolved.
Remove from heat; add 1 teaspoon vanilla extract and 1 teaspoon almond extract and allow to cool slightly. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and flavorings.
Pour over macaroons in mold and chill until firm.

title: aunt rita's pizza dough
directions: Mix all ingredients together; knead on floured board for about 10 minutes.
Cover with plastic wrap and let rise about 2 hours. Oil 2 (14-inch) pizza pans.
Sprinkle with a little cornmeal.
Pat and stretch dough in pans.
Prick dough with fork.
Brush each dough with a small amount of oil to prevent dough from becoming soggy.
Spread with your favorite sauce and toppings.
Let rise about 10 minutes.
Bake about 25 minutes at 400°.
"May be frozen for 1 week before baking."

title: shrimp creole
directions: Boil shrimp until they float.
Peel and devein.
Saute onion, garlic, celery and pepper in oil. Add tomatoes, tomato paste, thyme, bay leaf, parsley, sugar, salt and pepper.
Mix, cover and simmer 30 minutes. Add shrimp and simmer 5 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: whoopee pies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by level tablespoon onto baking sheet.
Cook for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: sliced beef in onion sauce
directions: Season meat with salt and pepper.
Brown on both sides in melted shortening.
Add 1/4 cup of water and cover tightly. Simmer gently 1 to 1 1/2 hours, or until meat is tender.
Add remaining water, a 1/4 cup at a time to keep pan from drying out. Push meat to one side of pan and carefully place onions in the juice.
Cover.
Simmer 1/2 hour or longer until onions are transparent and tender.
Transfer meat and onions to hot platter and cover.
Stir combined sugar and flour into juice, adding more water if desired.
Heat to boiling and pour over meat and onions. Serve at once.
Yields 4 servings.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mix and pour into uncooked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: believe it or not chicken
directions: Brown chicken in hot oil just enough to sear in juices.
Mix the other ingredients together.
Put chicken in casserole or oven-safe dish.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Place in oven and bake at 375° for 1 hour. Delicious. Good also with Catalina dressing.

title: orange salad with honey dressing
directions: In a blender or food processor, combine the first 9 ingredients; blend until slightly thickened. Pour into a jar or airtight container; chill. Line a serving platter or individual salad plates with lettuce. Arrange orange slices on top. Shake dressing; drizzle over oranges. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: paprika chicken with sour cream gravy
directions: Mix flour and seasoning. Coat chicken. Melt butter in skillet. Add chicken and cook until browned. Add soup and onions. Cover and cook over low heat 10 minutes or until done. Stir in sour cream. Serve with mashed potatoes or rice if desired.

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening, add sugar and eggs, one at a time.
Mix flour and baking powder, alternate adding to mixture with milk.
Add flavoring and walnuts.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 80 minutes.

title: fruit pies
directions: Cream the cream cheese, Cool Whip, vanilla flavor and confectioners sugar together until smooth.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: In medium bowl, combine peanut butter and honey.
Stir in rice cereal, coating cereal evenly with peanut butter.
Spray 9-inch pie plate with nonstick cooking spray.
With back of spoon, press cereal mixture into bottom and up sides of pie plate.
Freeze, uncovered, for 1/2 hour.

title: cherry delight
directions: Roll crackers very fine.
Add butter and make a pie crust. Then chill.
Mix cheese and sugar. Mix in Dream Whip.
Add milk and blend.
Pour over pie crust, then add the cherries.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Makes 15 servings.

title: lemon cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and butter.
Press in pan, leaving 2 tablespoons aside.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
In another bowl, beat cheese.
Add filling and lemon juice.
Pour into baked graham crust.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Chill 4 hours.

title: frosted cauliflower
directions: Remove woody base from cauliflower, leaving cauliflower whole. Cook cauliflower in 1 1/2-quart glass dish with 2 tablespoons of water and 1/2 teaspoon salt for 6 to 7 minutes per pound, covered. Rotate dish 1/4 turn halfway through cooking time.
Rest, covered, for 5 minutes and season as desired.

title: potato salad with parsley pesto dressing
directions: In saucepan, cook potatoes and fresh beans in boiling, lightly salted water 12 to 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Drain.
Toss together potatoes, beans, squash, red pepper and green beans.

title: raw tomato relish
directions: Mix together sugar, vinegar, mustard seed and salt.
Pour mixture over vegetables.
Put in jars.
Keep in refrigerator up to 1 year.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: In a small bowl combine flour, baking powder, soda, and salt. Set aside.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cut salt pork into cubes and brown in large saucepan.
Add onion.
Cook until tender and lightly browned.
Add potatoes and water.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Soak crackers in milk. Add corn, salt, pepper and soaked crackers to cooked potato mixture.
Heat to boiling.
Serves 4.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and celery.
Drain off grease.
Add package of Texas hot chili seasoning, 1/2 package of regular chili seasoning and 1 cup V-8 juice.
Bring to boil.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add V-8 juice, chili beans, kidney beans and stewed tomatoes (do not drain beans).
Simmer for a couple of hours.
Add cooked noodles, if desired.

title: chile egg puffs
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs until light.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: pound cake
directions: Put all dry ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Add margarine, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed for 15 minutes. Pour in well-greased Bundt pan and bake at 325°
for
1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: sauteed mushrooms
directions: Wipe mushrooms with clean damp cloth.
Do not wash.
They must be dry.
Slice or quarter large mushrooms; leave small ones whole. Place butter and oil in pan over high heat.
When butter begins to foam, then subsides, add the mushrooms.
Toss and shake pan 4 to 5 minutes.
Once mushrooms have browned, remove from heat. Sauteed mushrooms can be cooked in advance, set aside and reheated.
Season only before serving.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: lemon gems
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 13 x 9-inch pan, combine 2 cups flour, 1/2 cup sugar and lemon peel.
With pastry blender, cut in butter (margarine) until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Pat crumbs evenly in pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: mexican stuffed bell peppers
directions: Remove tops from peppers, take out seeds.
In a large Dutch oven, boil peppers in water, 5 to 7 minutes.
(Water should already be boiling.)
Remove to casserole.

title: roast leg of lamb
directions: Rub lamb with salt and pepper.
Arrange fat side up on rack in roasting pan.
Roast at 325° for 28 minutes per pound for medium or until meat thermometer registers 165°.
Baste during last hours of cooking with either Mint or Honey-Mustard Glaze.
Serve with Mint Sauce after roast has set for 20 minutes to retain juices.

title: apple nut treats
directions: Place apple slices on a plate with 2 tablespoons crunchy peanut butter.
Sprinkle peanut butter with sprinkle decorations or colorful nonpareils.
Dip apple slices into peanut butter for a delicious treat.

title: ranch dressing dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.
Use with raw vegetables.
Makes 4 cups.

title: orange juice-lious
directions: Put ingredients into blender in order listed.
Blend 30 seconds.
Makes 3 cups.

title: apple crunch
directions: In a large bowl, combine apples, cranberries, granulated sugar and 1/3 cup brown sugar.
Toss together well.
Pour fruit mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan coated with vegetable cooking spray.
In a small bowl combine margarine, 1/4 cup brown sugar, oatmeal, flour and nuts.
Mix together with a fork to achieve a crumbled texture. Sprinkle topping mixture over the fruit.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Yields 16 squares.

title: high fiber bars
directions: Mix Bran cereal, oats, cinnamon, baking soda and salt in medium mixing bowl.
Add dates or raisins and walnuts.
In small bowl, lightly beat 2 eggs.
Mix in yogurt, oil and honey.
Add liquid ingredients and mix together well.
Pour into well buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Cut into bars after cooled.

title: skillet beef and macaroni
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in a skillet until browned; drain well.
Stir in next 5 ingredients. Simmer, stirring occasionally, 5 to 10 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Stir in Cheddar cheese.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix the graham cracker crumbs, 1 stick oleo and 1 cup powdered sugar.
Pour into greased dish.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Can be cooked in crock-pot on high for 4 hours.

title: stuffed ham steaks
directions: Combine all ingredients, except ham.
Place 1 slice of ham in a shallow baking pan.
Spread stuffing over ham and top with 2nd slice of ham.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
You can put whole cloves in fat around ham steaks for added flavor.
Serves 3.

title: homemade split pea soup
directions: Put all ingredients in a 5-quart crock-pot or pan.
Fill with water and cook, covered, all day on low heat.
One hour before serving, remove ham hocks.
Debone and de-fat meat.
Cut up and put back in pot.
Uncover and cook at medium-high heat until thickened.
Stir frequently to keep from sticking.
Serve with pear and cottage cheese salad.

title: steamed slaw
directions: Shred cabbage.
Layer shredded cabbage with onions in glass or ceramic dish.
Sprinkle sugar over layers.
Do not stir.
Mix and bring to a boil oil, vinegar, salt, pepper, celery salt and dry mustard.
Pour over layered cabbage dish.
Seal lightly. Refrigerate.
Mix well before serving.

title: fritter batter
directions: Beat eggs and milk into a medium size bowl until well blended. Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Add salad oil and mix. Cut up fruit or vegetable.
Dip into fritter batter.
Drop into hot deep fat (375°) and fry until brown.
Do not crowd.
Drain on a paper towel.

title: tropical tea
directions: Bring water to a boil. Add tea bags and let steep for 10 minutes. Pour into a gallon jar with other ingredients. Finish filling jar with water to make 1 gallon.

title: burrito roll-ups
directions: Combine all ingredients (except tortillas), beating until smooth.
Spread thin layer on each tortilla and roll up, jelly roll style.
Place on cookie sheet; freeze for about 20 minutes. Slice and secure with a toothpick.
Dip in picante sauce for extra South-of-the-Border flavor!

title: amish country-style scrambled eggs
directions: In a large skillet, saut potatoes, onions and green peppers in butter until tender, stirring often.
Beat together eggs, milk and pepper.
Stir in ham.
Pour over potato mixture.
Cook without stirring until mixture begins to set on bottom and around sides. Using a large spatula, lift and fold the partially cooked mixture so the uncooked portion flows underneath.
Continue cooking until done.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: marbled cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Stir together margarine and cocoa until smooth.
In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in milk until smooth.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Beat in flour.
Put 1 1/2 cups batter in medium bowl.
Beat in cocoa.
Spoon 1/2 vanilla batter into crust, then 1/2 chocolate batter.
Repeat.
With spatula, cut through batters to marble. Bake for 50 to 60 minutes or until center is set.
Cool; chill.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Put pineapple with jello in pan.
Heat and let boil for 1 minute, stirring often.
Let cool for 10 minutes and stir in buttermilk, Cool Whip, nuts and mandarin oranges.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Congeals very quickly.

title: dillie bread
directions: Soften yeast 10 minutes.
Combine in large bowl the cheese, butter, sugar, salt, soda, onion, dill, egg and yeast.
Beat well. Add flour gradually.
Cover; let rise in warm place until double (about 1 hour).
Punch down.
Turn into well-greased loaf pan. Let rise until light, 35 to 40 minutes.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat; add all ingredients but beans.
Stir.
Cover and cook 2 hours at 225°.
Add beans and cook 30 minutes.
Serve.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops.
Place uncooked rice in casserole dish. Dissolve bouillon cube in water; pour over rice.
Place browned chops on top.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over rice and pork chops. Pour mushroom soup, diluted with 1/2 can water, over pork chops. Cover; bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: pat's pink stuff
directions: Mix all the ingredients and refrigerate.
Best when left overnight refrigerated.

title: 98 octane chili
directions: 1. Drink all but 1 cup of the wine; this is necessary to ensure communion. with the appropriate fire gods.
2. Saute ingredients 2-12 in a large pot until all the
meat is browned. Add remaining wine and other
ingredients. Simmer 2-3 hours.

title: angel buns
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water. Mix in baking mix and milk
until dough forms.
Smooth into ball and dust with baking mix. Knead 10 times.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with 2-inch biscuit cutter dipped in baking mix.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Let rise about 30 minutes in warm place. Bake at 425° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: tart baked pork chops or pork steaks
directions: Place pork chops in baking dish or pan, topping each with a slice of lemon, onion, green pepper and a whole tomato.
Cover pork chops with juice from canned tomatoes.
Add salt and pepper to taste and bake in a covered dish until done.

title: shrimp biscuits
directions: Season meat to your taste.
Put meat into heavy pan over medium heat.
(You need not use butter or oil, inasmuch as the ground meat will be somewhat fatty.)

title: fried deer steak
directions: Marinate steak overnight in a mixture of Italian dressing, lemon juice, cooking wine, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper to taste.
Cut bell pepper and onion up and place in marinade.
Take steak and beat with a meat mallet; flour.
Pour enough oil in skillet to almost cover meat.
Get grease hot.
Fry meat fast with onion and bell pepper.

title: quick 'n easy chicken
directions: In plastic bag, mix by shaking about 1/2 cup flour, salt and pepper to taste, onion salt and paprika.
Dredge chicken pieces by shaking in bag a couple of pieces at a time.
In skillet with small portion of cooking oil, lightly brown coated chicken portions.
Place chicken in bottom of greased casserole dish.
In blender, mix soup, half and half and sherry.
Pour over chicken and mushrooms.
Cover casserole dish with foil.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: creamy fruit dip
directions: In a small mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese and brown sugar until smooth.
Beat in the sour cream, extracts and cinnamon until smooth.
Add milk; mix well.
Add pudding mix; beat on low speed for 2 minutes.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Serve with fruit.
Yield: 3 1/2 cups.

title: easy potato salad
directions: Peel, cube and cook potatoes.
Cook eggs.
Chop up onion.
Mix cooked potatoes (drained), onion, 2 tablespoons sweet pickles and 4 tablespoons mayo (or to taste).
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix together.

title: cindy's spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburger with salt and onion until done.
Drain all grease from meat.
Meanwhile, cook the spaghetti until done; drain and add to hamburger.
Add tomatoes and sauce.
Stir together to mix well and you are ready to eat!

title: dot and don's chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan. Mix all ingredients except water.
Beat 2 minutes.
Turn mixer on low and blend boiling water into batter.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes. Start testing cake after 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix water and jello.
Refrigerate until it begins to set. Remove from refrigerator and add Cool Whip and strawberries.
Then whip to break into chunks.
Cube cake and mix with jello. Refrigerate.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter, eggs and sugar.
Reserve 3 tablespoons flour.
In separate bowl, combine remaining flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Add vanilla to milk.
Alternately add milk and flour mixture to creamed butter and egg mixture.
Place berries in separate bowl; sprinkle with reserved flour and turn gently with spoon until berries are lightly coated.
Fold berries into batter. Fill 2 (12 hole) greased (or use paper muffin cups) muffin pans 2/3 full and sprinkle tops with sugar.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes, until tester comes out clean.
Makes 24 muffins.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Cook until onion is tender.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Top with cheese.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into a greased and floured cake pan. Use three pans for 3 layers.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: texas chili with cornbread topping
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Cook and stir ground beef and onions in 10-inch skillet until beef is light brown and onions tender; drain. Stir in macaroni, sauce mix, beans (with liquid), water and chili powder.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Stir baking mix, 1/3 cup cornmeal, the cheese, milk and egg vigorously until well blended.
Pour bean mixture into ungreased 3-quart casserole.
Drop dough by spoonfuls around edges of casserole.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon cornmeal.
Bake uncovered until golden brown, about 15 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Place in bowl or muffin liners for individual servings.
Refrigerate.
Enjoy!!

title: filled strawberries
directions: This recipe can be for as many strawberries as you want to fix.
From a few to a whole quart.	Clean and hull your strawberries.
Fill with Cool Whip (a pastry tool works well) roll in powdered sugar and enjoy.

title: sausage bread
directions: Wrap frozen dough in Reynolds wrap until dough rises.
Roll out dough.
Fry sausage.
Layer sausage, pepperoni and cheese. Pull dough together and bake at 350° until brown.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: broccoli - cauliflower salad
directions: Mix well and let sit overnight.

title: bailey's irish cream
directions: Combine all ingredients well in blender.
Store in refrigerator.

title: meatball stew
directions: After mixing cheese mixture well, add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spoon some spaghetti sauce in bottom of 9 X 13 pan. Spoon ingredients over sauce and spread evenly.
Cover with more sauce.
Bake at 350 for 30 minutes or until center is heated thru. Use extra sauce at table.
Can be divided and frozen.

title: cocktail nibbles
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Stir in onion salt, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Add walnuts.
Toss lightly to coat with seasoned butter.
Stir over low heat 3 to 5 minutes to lightly toast.
Remove from heat.
Sprinkle with cheese, tossing lightly as cheese melts.
Turn out onto flat pan to cool.

title: quick beef stroganoff
directions: Cut minute steaks into strips.
Brown in hot fat.
Add onion. Add garlic powder.
Cook 5 minutes.
In separate bowl, combine mushroom soup, sour cream, mushrooms, ketchup and Worcestershire sauce.
Add to meat; heat through and serve over cooked egg noodles.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Roll cookie dough onto pizza pan or cookie sheet with sides. Bake at 350° until brown.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese and confectioners sugar; spread over baked cookie dough.
Add fruit to top.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and juice; bring to a boil.
Boil until clear.
Stir in gelatin mix.
Cool and pour over fruit. Refrigerate.
Top with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: crock-pot ham and scalloped potatoes
directions: Layer ham, onions, potatoes and cheese in crock-pot.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used.
Mix soup and water. Pour over all ingredients.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours or on high for 4 hours.

title: fun cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
Cream together shortening and sugars until light and fluffy; beat in egg and vanilla.
Blend in flour mixture slowly. Stir in M&M's and nuts.

title: tuna-noodle casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients reserving some of the noodles for topping. Place in casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: ham chowder
directions: Melt margarine.
Add ham and saute on low for 5 minutes.
Add celery and onion.
Saute until tender (not brown).
Cook potatoes in boiling salted water until nearly tender.
Drain.
Blend flour in ham and vegetable mixture.
Add milk slowly.
Cook and stir until smooth and thickened.
Add potatoes.
Cook over low heat until potatoes are just tender.
Serve with parsley added.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Pour in 1 cup of graham cracker crumbs and pat to make crust.
Layer coconut, chocolate chips, nuts and milk.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: he-man casserole
directions: Brown the ground meat, onion, garlic, parsley flakes, salt and pepper. Grease crock-pot with butter.
Make layers of potatoes (sliced), carrots (sliced) and ground meat.
Dot each layer with butter.
Repeat layers; approximately 3 layers.
Put in blender the tomatoes, soup, tomato sauce and ketchup.
Blend.
Pour over potatoes, carrots and ground meat, just enough to cover. Cook in crock-pot for 7 hours on high.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cake
directions: Pour 1 3/4 cup boiling water over 1 cup uncooked oatmeal. Let stand 10 minutes.
Add brown sugar, white sugar and butter. Mix well.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Sift flour, soda, salt and cocoa. Add to sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Add chocolate chips.
Pour into 9 x 13 greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle with remaining chips. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pea salad
directions: Cook peas until done, then cool.
Mix in onion, egg and cheese and then mix in mayonnaise.
Add salt to taste.
Let stand in refrigerator for about 1/2 hour and then serve.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: quick beef and gravy
directions: Shape beef into loaf and place in shallow baking dish.
Pour soups over meat.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: pink fruit
directions: Drain fruit and pineapple.
Then mix all ingredients together. Refrigerate.

title: pretzel jello
directions: Mix and let stand for 10 minutes.
Pour over cream cheese mixture and refrigerate.

title: healthy diabetic muffins
directions: In medium bowl, combine Bran and milk; let stand 5 minutes. In small bowl, combine flour, Sugar Twin, baking powder and soda; set aside.
Mix margarine and egg into Bran mixture.
Stir in flour mixture just until blended.
Spoon batter into 12 greased (2 1/2-inch) muffin pan cups or use papers.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes or until done.
Serve warm.

title: pecan butterballs
directions: Cream butter and gradually add honey. Add flour, salt and vanilla. Add chopped nuts. Mix well. Form into small balls. Place on a greased baking sheet. Bake in a moderate 300° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: little pizzas
directions: Use heavy-duty large pan. Crumble Italian sausage, after taking casing off sausage, into a skillet. Add bulk sausage. Stir and cook on medium heat until well mixed. Then add all the other ingredients. Turn heat down to low. Cook until all the cheese is melted and all the ingredients are well done.
When done, use a tablespoon to cover slices of bread. Place on a cookie sheet and freeze. When frozen, place in freezer bags. Take out of the freezer when ready to bake.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Dip cutlets in egg and bread crumbs; cook 8 minutes on each side.
Lay slice of Mozzarella cheese on top with sauce surrounding in shallow dish.
Serve with spaghetti.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Cream shortening, margarine, egg yolks and vanilla in a bowl and set aside.
In separate bowl combine flour and salt.
Combine both bowls and mix well.
In the palms of your hands roll dough into about 1 inch balls.
Use the remaining egg whites to dip the dough balls in and roll in chopped nuts.
Place dough balls on ungreased cookie sheet and press down on each dough ball with your thumb, creating a thumbprint.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
After cookies have cooled, fill each thumbprint with icing.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, flour, salt and water in double boiler.
Dissolve all cornstarch and flour. Add beaten eggs, slowly stirring in.
Also add butter and lemon juice, stirring all the time.
When thick, pour into pie shell.

title: mushroom logs
directions: Separate each can of crescent rolls into 4 rectangles by pinching triangular perforations together to make a rectangle. Mix together cream cheese, mushrooms and seasoned salt. Spread mixture on edge of each rectangle. Roll into log with seam side down. Cut each log into 6 pieces. Arrange on cookie sheet. Brush each log with egg and sprinkle each log with poppy seeds. Bake 10 to 12 minutes in 375° oven. Yields 4 to 8 logs.

title: lemon squares
directions: Combine flour, butter and powdered sugar; press into ungreased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Beat eggs, sugar, baking powder, salt and lemon juice together. Pour over hot crust and bake for 25 minutes.

title: cranberry-grape salad
directions: Refrigerate cranberries and sugar overnight.
Dissolve raspberry jello in
the boiling water. Cool. Add cranberries, red grapes and nuts. Fold in the whipping cream which has been sweetened.
Chill.

title: chocolate torte - 4 layer delight
directions: 1st Layer: In a bowl, mix flour, nuts and margarine. Put in 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: baked potato
directions: First, boil your broccoli about 30 minutes. Then drain water, while cooling in pan a stick of butter or margarine. Then cut thick slices Velveeta cheese over the broccoli. Simmer until melted, then let cool. Now, take ground beef and brown in skillet. Then add onions, bell pepper, garlic salt and black pepper. Cook until golden brown, then drain grease and let cool. After boiling potatoes for 30 minutes, drain water; let cool.
Then place potato in bowl or styrofoam plate. Bust potato open, then place broccoli inside, then place ground beef on top. Then place a tablespoon of sour cream on top, then Ranch dressing, then eat.

title: ham casserole supper
directions: Arrange potatoes and ham in light greased 1-quart casserole and top with apple rounds.
Blend mustard and brown sugar.
Pour water or juice over apples and sprinkle brown sugar on top.
Cover and bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer.
Serves 4.
